40 namespace {
41 const char* BuiltinIncludesMarker = "// __BUILTIN_INCLUDES_MARKER__\n";
42 } // namespace
43 
44 VisitResult ImplementationVisitor::Visit(Expression* expr) {
45  CurrentSourcePosition::Scope scope(expr->pos);
46  switch (expr->kind) {
47 #define ENUM_ITEM(name) \
48  case AstNode::Kind::k##name: \
49  return Visit(name::cast(expr));
50  AST_EXPRESSION_NODE_KIND_LIST(ENUM_ITEM)
51 #undef ENUM_ITEM
52  default:
53  UNREACHABLE();
54  }
55 }
56 
57 const Type* ImplementationVisitor::Visit(Statement* stmt) {
58  CurrentSourcePosition::Scope scope(stmt->pos);
59  StackScope stack_scope(this);
60  const Type* result;
61  switch (stmt->kind) {
62 #define ENUM_ITEM(name) \
63  case AstNode::Kind::k##name: \
64  result = Visit(name::cast(stmt)); \
65  break;
66  AST_STATEMENT_NODE_KIND_LIST(ENUM_ITEM)
67 #undef ENUM_ITEM
68  default:
69  UNREACHABLE();
70  }
71  DCHECK_EQ(result == TypeOracle::GetNeverType(),
72  assembler().CurrentBlockIsComplete());
73  return result;
74 }
75 
76 void ImplementationVisitor::BeginGeneratedFiles() {
77  std::set<SourceId> contains_class_definitions;
78  std::set<SourceId> contains_class_asserts;
79  for (const ClassType* type : TypeOracle::GetClasses()) {
80  if (type->ShouldGenerateCppClassDefinitions()) {
81  contains_class_definitions.insert(type->AttributedToFile());
82  }
83  if (type->ShouldGenerateCppObjectDefinitionAsserts() ||
84  type->ShouldGenerateCppObjectLayoutDefinitionAsserts()) {
85  contains_class_asserts.insert(type->AttributedToFile());
86  }
87  }
88 
89  for (SourceId source : SourceFileMap::AllSources()) {
90  auto& streams = GlobalContext::GeneratedPerFile(source);
91  // Output beginning of CSA .cc file.
92  {
93  cpp::File& file = streams.csa_cc;
94 
95  for (const std::string& include_path : GlobalContext::CppIncludes()) {
96  file << "#include " << StringLiteralQuote(include_path) << "\n";
97  }
98  file << "#include \"src/codegen/code-stub-assembler-inl.h\"\n";
99 
100  file << "// Required Builtins:\n";
101  file << "#include \"torque-generated/" +
102  SourceFileMap::PathFromV8RootWithoutExtension(source) +
103  "-tq-csa.h\"\n";
104  // Now that required include files are collected while generating the
105  // file, we only know the full set at the end. Insert a marker here that
106  // is replaced with the list of includes at the very end.
107  // TODO(nicohartmann@): This is not the most beautiful way to do this,
108  // replace once the cpp file builder is available, where this can be
109  // handled easily.
110  file << BuiltinIncludesMarker;
111  file << "\n";
112 
113  streams.csa_cc.BeginNamespace("v8", "internal");
114  streams.csa_ccfile << "\n";
115  }
116  // Output beginning of CSA .h file.
117  {
118  cpp::File& file = streams.csa_header;
119  std::string header_define =
120  "V8_GEN_TORQUE_GENERATED_" +
121  UnderlinifyPath(SourceFileMap::PathFromV8Root(source)) + "_CSA_H_";
122  streams.csa_header.BeginIncludeGuard(header_define);
123  file << "#include \"src/builtins/torque-csa-header-includes.h\"\n";
124  file << "\n";
125 
126  streams.csa_header.BeginNamespace("v8", "internal");
127  streams.csa_headerfile << "\n";
128  }
129  // Output beginning of class definition .cc file.
130  {
131  cpp::File& file = streams.class_definition_cc;
132  if (contains_class_definitions.count(source) != 0) {
133  file << "#include \""
134  << SourceFileMap::PathFromV8RootWithoutExtension(source)
135  << "-inl.h\"\n\n";
136  file << "#include \"torque-generated/class-verifiers.h\"\n";
137  file << "#include \"src/objects/objects-inl.h\"\n\n";
138  file << "#include \"src/objects/instance-type-inl.h\"\n\n";
139  }
140  if (contains_class_asserts.count(source) != 0) {
141  file << "#include \""
142  << SourceFileMap::PathFromV8RootWithoutExtension(source)
143  << ".h\"\n\n";
144  }
145 
146  streams.class_definition_cc.BeginNamespace("v8", "internal");
147  streams.class_definition_ccfile << "\n";
148  }
149  }
150 }
151 
152 void ImplementationVisitor::EndGeneratedFiles() {
153  for (SourceId file : SourceFileMap::AllSources()) {
154  auto& streams = GlobalContext::GeneratedPerFile(file);
155 
156  // Output ending of CSA .cc file.
157  streams.csa_cc.EndNamespace("v8", "internal");
158 
159  // Output ending of CSA .h file.
160  {
161  std::string header_define =
162  "V8_GEN_TORQUE_GENERATED_" +
163  UnderlinifyPath(SourceFileMap::PathFromV8Root(file)) + "_CSA_H_";
164 
165  streams.csa_header.EndNamespace("v8", "internal");
166  streams.csa_headerfile << "\n";
167  streams.csa_header.EndIncludeGuard(header_define);
168  }
169 
170  // Output ending of class definition .cc file.
171  streams.class_definition_cc.EndNamespace("v8", "internal");
172  }
173 }

175 void ImplementationVisitor::BeginDebugMacrosFile() {
176  // TODO(torque-builer): Can use builder for debug_macros_*_

178  std::ostream& header = debug_macros_h_;
179 
180  source << "#include \"torque-generated/debug-macros.h\"\n\n";
181  source << "\n";

183  "definitions.\n";
184  source << "#include \"src/objects/swiss-name-dictionary.h\"\n";
185  source << "#include \"src/objects/ordered-hash-table.h\"\n";
186  source << "#include \"src/objects/prototype-info.h\"\n";
187  source << "\n";
188  source << "#include \"src/torque/runtime-support.h\"\n";
189  source << "#include \"tools/debug_helper/debug-macro-shims.h\"\n";
190  source << "#include \"include/v8-internal.h\"\n";
191  source << "\n";
192 
193  source << "namespace v8 {\n"
194  << "namespace internal {\n"
195  << "namespace debug_helper_internal {\n"
196  << "\n";
197 
198  const char* kHeaderDefine = "V8_GEN_TORQUE_GENERATED_DEBUG_MACROS_H_";
199  header << "#ifndef " << kHeaderDefine << "\n";
200  header << "#define " << kHeaderDefine << "\n\n";
201  header << "#include \"tools/debug_helper/debug-helper-internal.h\"\n";
202  header << "#include \"src/numbers/integer-literal.h\"\n";
203  header << "\n";
204 
205  header << "namespace v8 {\n"
206  << "namespace internal {\n"
207  << "namespace debug_helper_internal {\n"
208  << "\n";

211 void ImplementationVisitor::EndDebugMacrosFile() {
212  // TODO(torque-builder): Can use builder for debug_macros_*_
213  std::ostream& source = debug_macros_cc_;
214  std::ostream& header = debug_macros_h_;
215 
216  source << "} // namespace internal\n"
217  << "} // namespace v8\n"
218  << "} // namespace debug_helper_internal\n"
219  << "\n";
220 
221  header << "\n} // namespace internal\n"
222  << "} // namespace v8\n"
223  << "} // namespace debug_helper_internal\n"
224  << "\n";
225  header << "#endif // V8_GEN_TORQUE_GENERATED_DEBUG_MACROS_H_\n";
226 }

228 void ImplementationVisitor::Visit(NamespaceConstant* decl) {
229  Signature signature{{}, std::nullopt, {{}, false}, 0,
230  decl->type(), {}, false};
231 
232  BindingsManagersScope bindings_managers_scope;
233 
234  cpp::Function f =
235  GenerateFunction(nullptr, decl->external_name(), signature, {});
236 
237  f.PrintDeclaration(csa_headerfile());
238 
239  f.PrintDefinition(csa_ccfile(), [&](std::ostream& stream) {
240  stream << " compiler::CodeAssembler ca_(state_);\n";
241 
242  DCHECK(!signature.return_type->IsVoidOrNever());
243 
244  assembler_ = CfgAssembler(Stack<const Type*>{});
245 
246  VisitResult expression_result = Visit(decl->body());
247  VisitResult return_result =
248  GenerateImplicitConvert(signature.return_type, expression_result);
249 
250  CSAGenerator csa_generator{assembler().Result(), stream};
251  Stack<std::string> values = *csa_generator.EmitGraph(Stack<std::string>{});
252 
253  assembler_ = std::nullopt;
254 
255  stream << " return ";
256  CSAGenerator::EmitCSAValue(return_result, values, stream);
257  stream << ";";
258  });
259 }
260 
261 void ImplementationVisitor::Visit(TypeAlias* alias) {
262  if (alias->IsRedeclaration()) return;
263  if (const ClassType* class_type = ClassType::DynamicCast(alias->type())) {
264  if (class_type->IsExtern() && !class_type->nspace()->IsDefaultNamespace()) {
265  Error(
266  "extern classes are currently only supported in the default "
267  "namespace");
268  }
269  }
270 }
271 
272 class ImplementationVisitor::MacroInliningScope {
273  public:
274  MacroInliningScope(ImplementationVisitor* visitor, const Macro* macro)
275  : visitor_(visitor), macro_(macro) {
276  if (!visitor_->inlining_macros_.insert(macro).second) {
277  // Recursive macro expansion would just keep going until stack overflow.
278  // To avoid crashes, throw an error immediately.
279  ReportError("Recursive macro call to ", *macro);
280  }
281  }
282  ~MacroInliningScope() { visitor_->inlining_macros_.erase(macro_); }
283 
284  private:
285  ImplementationVisitor* visitor_;
286  const Macro* macro_;
287 };
288 
289 VisitResult ImplementationVisitor::InlineMacro(
290  Macro* macro, std::optional<LocationReference> this_reference,
291  const std::vector<VisitResult>& arguments,
292  const std::vector<Block*> label_blocks) {
293  MacroInliningScope macro_inlining_scope(this, macro);
294  CurrentScope::Scope current_scope(macro);
295  BindingsManagersScope bindings_managers_scope;
296  CurrentCallable::Scope current_callable(macro);
297  CurrentReturnValue::Scope current_return_value;
298  const Signature& signature = macro->signature();
299  const Type* return_type = macro->signature().return_type;
300  bool can_return = return_type != TypeOracle::GetNeverType();
301 
302  BlockBindings<LocalValue> parameter_bindings(&ValueBindingsManager::Get());
303  BlockBindings<LocalLabel> label_bindings(&LabelBindingsManager::Get());
304  DCHECK_EQ(macro->signature().parameter_names.size(),
305  arguments.size() + (this_reference ? 1 : 0));
306  DCHECK_EQ(this_reference.has_value(), macro->IsMethod());
307 
308  // Bind the this for methods. Methods that modify a struct-type "this" must
309  // only be called if the this is in a variable, in which case the
310  // LocalValue is non-const. Otherwise, the LocalValue used for the parameter
311  // binding is const, and thus read-only, which will cause errors if
312  // modified, e.g. when called by a struct method that sets the structs
313  // fields. This prevents using temporary struct values for anything other
314  // than read operations.
315  if (this_reference) {
316  DCHECK(macro->IsMethod());
317  parameter_bindings.Add(kThisParameterName, LocalValue{*this_reference},
318  true);
319  // TODO(v8:12261): Tracking 'this'-binding for kythe led to a few weird
320  // issues. Review to fully support 'this' in methods.
321  }
322 
323  size_t count = 0;
324  for (const auto& arg : arguments) {
325  if (this_reference && count == signature.implicit_count) count++;
326  const bool mark_as_used = signature.implicit_count > count;
327  const Identifier* name = macro->parameter_names()[count++];
328  Binding<LocalValue>* binding =
329  parameter_bindings.Add(name,
330  LocalValue{LocationReference::Temporary(
331  arg, "parameter " + name->value)},
332  mark_as_used);
333  if (GlobalContext::collect_kythe_data()) {
334  KytheData::AddBindingDefinition(binding);
335  }
336  }
337 
338  DCHECK_EQ(label_blocks.size(), signature.labels.size());
339  for (size_t i = 0; i < signature.labels.size(); ++i) {
340  const LabelDeclaration& label_info = signature.labels[i];
341  Binding<LocalLabel>* binding = label_bindings.Add(
342  label_info.name, LocalLabel{label_blocks[i], label_info.types});
343  if (GlobalContext::collect_kythe_data()) {
344  KytheData::AddBindingDefinition(binding);
345  }
346  }
347 
348  Block* macro_end;
349  std::optional<Binding<LocalLabel>> macro_end_binding;
350  if (can_return) {
351  Stack<const Type*> stack = assembler().CurrentStack();
352  std::vector<const Type*> lowered_return_types = LowerType(return_type);
353  stack.PushMany(lowered_return_types);
354  if (!return_type->IsConstexpr()) {
355  SetReturnValue(VisitResult(return_type,
356  stack.TopRange(lowered_return_types.size())));
357  }
358  // The stack copy used to initialize the _macro_end block is only used
359  // as a template for the actual gotos generated by return statements. It
360  // doesn't correspond to any real return values, and thus shouldn't contain
361  // top types, because these would pollute actual return value types that get
362  // unioned with them for return statements, erroneously forcing them to top.
363  for (auto i = stack.begin(); i != stack.end(); ++i) {
364  if ((*i)->IsTopType()) {
365  *i = TopType::cast(*i)->source_type();
366  }
367  }
368  macro_end = assembler().NewBlock(std::move(stack));
369  macro_end_binding.emplace(&LabelBindingsManager::Get(), kMacroEndLabelName,
370  LocalLabel{macro_end, {return_type}});
371  } else {
372  SetReturnValue(VisitResult::NeverResult());
373  }
374 
375  const Type* result = Visit(*macro->body());
376 
377  if (result->IsNever()) {
378  if (!return_type->IsNever() && !macro->HasReturns()) {
379  std::stringstream s;
380  s << "macro " << macro->ReadableName()
381  << " that never returns must have return type never";
382  ReportError(s.str());
383  }
384  } else {
385  if (return_type->IsNever()) {
386  std::stringstream s;
387  s << "macro " << macro->ReadableName()
388  << " has implicit return at end of its declartion but return type "
389  "never";
390  ReportError(s.str());
391  } else if (!macro->signature().return_type->IsVoid()) {
392  std::stringstream s;
393  s << "macro " << macro->ReadableName()
394  << " expects to return a value but doesn't on all paths";
395  ReportError(s.str());
396  }
397  }
398  if (!result->IsNever()) {
399  assembler().Goto(macro_end);
400  }
401 
402  if (macro->HasReturns() || !result->IsNever()) {
403  assembler().Bind(macro_end);
404  }
405 
406  return GetAndClearReturnValue();
407 }
408 
409 void ImplementationVisitor::VisitMacroCommon(Macro* macro) {
410  CurrentCallable::Scope current_callable(macro);
411  const Signature& signature = macro->signature();
412  const Type* return_type = macro->signature().return_type;
413  bool can_return = return_type != TypeOracle::GetNeverType();
414  bool has_return_value =
415  can_return && return_type != TypeOracle::GetVoidType();
416 
417  cpp::Function f = GenerateMacroFunctionDeclaration(macro);
418  f.PrintDeclaration(csa_headerfile());
419  csa_headerfile() << "\n";
420 
421  cpp::File csa_cc(csa_ccfile());
422 
423  // Avoid multiple-definition errors since it is possible for multiple
424  // generated -inl.inc files to all contain function definitions for the same
425  // Torque macro.
426  std::optional<cpp::IncludeGuardScope> include_guard;
427  if (output_type_ == OutputType::kCC) {
428  include_guard.emplace(&csa_cc, "V8_INTERNAL_DEFINED_"s + macro->CCName());
429  } else if (output_type_ == OutputType::kCCDebug) {
430  include_guard.emplace(&csa_cc,
431  "V8_INTERNAL_DEFINED_"s + macro->CCDebugName());
432  }
433 
434  f.PrintBeginDefinition(csa_ccfile());
435 
436  if (output_type_ == OutputType::kCC) {
437  // For now, generated C++ is only for field offset computations. If we ever
438  // generate C++ code that can allocate, then it should be handlified.
439  csa_ccfile() << " DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;\n";
440  } else if (output_type_ == OutputType::kCSA) {
441  csa_ccfile() << " compiler::CodeAssembler ca_(state_);\n";
442  csa_ccfile()
443  << " compiler::CodeAssembler::SourcePositionScope pos_scope(&ca_);\n";
444  }
445 
446  Stack<std::string> lowered_parameters;
447  Stack<const Type*> lowered_parameter_types;
448 
449  std::vector<VisitResult> arguments;
450 
451  std::optional<LocationReference> this_reference;
452  if (Method* method = Method::DynamicCast(macro)) {
453  const Type* this_type = method->aggregate_type();
454  LowerParameter(this_type, ExternalParameterName(kThisParameterName),
455  &lowered_parameters);
456  StackRange range = lowered_parameter_types.PushMany(LowerType(this_type));
457  VisitResult this_result = VisitResult(this_type, range);
458  // For classes, mark 'this' as a temporary to prevent assignment to it.
459  // Note that using a VariableAccess for non-class types is technically
460  // incorrect because changes to the 'this' variable do not get reflected
461  // to the caller. Therefore struct methods should always be inlined and a
462  // C++ version should never be generated, since it would be incorrect.
463  // However, in order to be able to type- and semantics-check even unused
464  // struct methods, set the this_reference to be the local variable copy of
465  // the passed-in this, which allows the visitor to at least find and report
466  // errors.
467  this_reference =
468  (this_type->IsClassType())
469  ? LocationReference::Temporary(this_result, "this parameter")
470  : LocationReference::VariableAccess(this_result);
471  }
472 
473  for (size_t i = 0; i < macro->signature().parameter_names.size(); ++i) {
474  if (this_reference && i == macro->signature().implicit_count) continue;
475  const std::string& name = macro->parameter_names()[i]->value;
476  std::string external_name = ExternalParameterName(name);
477  const Type* type = macro->signature().types()[i];
478 
479  if (type->IsConstexpr()) {
480  arguments.push_back(VisitResult(type, external_name));
481  } else {
482  LowerParameter(type, external_name, &lowered_parameters);
483  StackRange range = lowered_parameter_types.PushMany(LowerType(type));
484  arguments.push_back(VisitResult(type, range));
485  }
486  }
487 
488  DCHECK_EQ(lowered_parameters.Size(), lowered_parameter_types.Size());
489  assembler_ = CfgAssembler(lowered_parameter_types);
490 
491  std::vector<Block*> label_blocks;
492  for (const LabelDeclaration& label_info : signature.labels) {
493  Stack<const Type*> label_input_stack;
494  for (const Type* type : label_info.types) {
495  label_input_stack.PushMany(LowerType(type));
496  }
497  Block* block = assembler().NewBlock(std::move(label_input_stack));
498  label_blocks.push_back(block);
499  }
500 
501  VisitResult return_value =
502  InlineMacro(macro, this_reference, arguments, label_blocks);
503  Block* end = assembler().NewBlock();
504  if (return_type != TypeOracle::GetNeverType()) {
505  assembler().Goto(end);
506  }
507 
508  for (size_t i = 0; i < label_blocks.size(); ++i) {
509  Block* label_block = label_blocks[i];
510  const LabelDeclaration& label_info = signature.labels[i];
511  assembler().Bind(label_block);
512  std::vector<std::string> label_parameter_variables;
513  for (size_t j = 0; j < label_info.types.size(); ++j) {
514  LowerLabelParameter(label_info.types[j],
515  ExternalLabelParameterName(label_info.name->value, j),
516  &label_parameter_variables);
517  }
518  assembler().Emit(
519  GotoExternalInstruction{ExternalLabelName(label_info.name->value),
520  std::move(label_parameter_variables)});
521  }
522 
523  if (return_type != TypeOracle::GetNeverType()) {
524  assembler().Bind(end);
525  }
526 
527  std::optional<Stack<std::string>> values;
528  if (output_type_ == OutputType::kCC) {
529  CCGenerator cc_generator{assembler().Result(), csa_ccfile()};
530  values = cc_generator.EmitGraph(lowered_parameters);
531  } else if (output_type_ == OutputType::kCCDebug) {
532  CCGenerator cc_generator{assembler().Result(), csa_ccfile(), true};
533  values = cc_generator.EmitGraph(lowered_parameters);
534  } else {
535  CSAGenerator csa_generator{assembler().Result(), csa_ccfile()};
536  values = csa_generator.EmitGraph(lowered_parameters);
537  }
538 
539  assembler_ = std::nullopt;
540 
541  if (has_return_value) {
542  csa_ccfile() << " return ";
543  if (output_type_ == OutputType::kCCDebug) {
544  csa_ccfile() << "{d::MemoryAccessResult::kOk, ";
545  CCGenerator::EmitCCValue(return_value, *values, csa_ccfile());
546  csa_ccfile() << "}";
547  } else if (output_type_ == OutputType::kCC) {
548  CCGenerator::EmitCCValue(return_value, *values, csa_ccfile());
549  } else {
550  CSAGenerator::EmitCSAValue(return_value, *values, csa_ccfile());
551  }
552  csa_ccfile() << ";\n";
553  }
554  f.PrintEndDefinition(csa_ccfile());
555 
556  include_guard.reset();
557 }
558 
559 void ImplementationVisitor::Visit(TorqueMacro* macro) {
560  VisitMacroCommon(macro);
561 }
562 
563 void ImplementationVisitor::Visit(Method* method) {
564  DCHECK(!method->IsExternal());
565  VisitMacroCommon(method);
566 }

568 namespace {
569 
570 std::string AddParameter(size_t i, Builtin* builtin,
571  Stack<std::string>* parameters,
572  Stack<const Type*>* parameter_types,
573  BlockBindings<LocalValue>* parameter_bindings,
574  bool mark_as_used) {
575  const Identifier* name = builtin->signature().parameter_names[i];
576  const Type* type = builtin->signature().types()[i];
577  std::string external_name = "parameter" + std::to_string(i);
578  parameters->Push(external_name);
579  StackRange range = parameter_types->PushMany(LowerType(type));
580  Binding<LocalValue>* binding = parameter_bindings->Add(
581  name,
582  LocalValue{LocationReference::Temporary(VisitResult(type, range),
583  "parameter " + name->value)},
584  mark_as_used);
585  if (GlobalContext::collect_kythe_data()) {
586  KytheData::AddBindingDefinition(binding);
587  }
588  return external_name;
589 }
590 
591 } // namespace
592 
593 void ImplementationVisitor::Visit(Builtin* builtin) {
594  if (builtin->IsExternal()) return;
595  CurrentScope::Scope current_scope(builtin);
596  CurrentCallable::Scope current_callable(builtin);
597  CurrentReturnValue::Scope current_return_value;
598 
599  const std::string& name = builtin->ExternalName();
600  const Signature& signature = builtin->signature();
601  csa_ccfile() << "TF_BUILTIN(" << name << ", CodeStubAssembler) {\n"
602  << " compiler::CodeAssemblerState* state_ = state();"
603  << " compiler::CodeAssembler ca_(state());\n";
604 
605  Stack<const Type*> parameter_types;
606  Stack<std::string> parameters;
607 
608  BindingsManagersScope bindings_managers_scope;
609 
610  BlockBindings<LocalValue> parameter_bindings(&ValueBindingsManager::Get());
611 
612  if (builtin->IsVarArgsJavaScript() || builtin->IsFixedArgsJavaScript()) {
613  if (builtin->IsVarArgsJavaScript()) {
614  DCHECK(signature.parameter_types.var_args);
615  if (signature.ExplicitCount() > 0) {
616  Error("Cannot mix explicit parameters with varargs.")
617  .Position(signature.parameter_names[signature.implicit_count]->pos);
618  }
619 
620  csa_ccfile() << " TNode<Word32T> argc = UncheckedParameter<Word32T>("
621  << "Descriptor::kJSActualArgumentsCount);\n";
622  csa_ccfile() << " TNode<IntPtrT> "
623  "arguments_length(ChangeInt32ToIntPtr(UncheckedCast<"
624  "Int32T>(argc)));\n";
625  csa_ccfile() << " TNode<RawPtrT> arguments_frame = "
626  "UncheckedCast<RawPtrT>(LoadFramePointer());\n";
627  csa_ccfile()
628  << " TorqueStructArguments "
629  "torque_arguments(GetFrameArguments(arguments_frame, "
630  "arguments_length, FrameArgumentsArgcType::kCountIncludesReceiver"
631  << "));\n";
632  csa_ccfile()
633  << " CodeStubArguments arguments(this, torque_arguments);\n";
634 
635  parameters.Push("torque_arguments.frame");
636  parameters.Push("torque_arguments.base");
637  parameters.Push("torque_arguments.length");
638  parameters.Push("torque_arguments.actual_count");
639  const Type* arguments_type = TypeOracle::GetArgumentsType();
640  StackRange range = parameter_types.PushMany(LowerType(arguments_type));
641  parameter_bindings.Add(*signature.arguments_variable,
642  LocalValue{LocationReference::Temporary(
643  VisitResult(arguments_type, range),
644  "parameter " + *signature.arguments_variable)},
645  true);
646  }
647 
648  for (size_t i = 0; i < signature.implicit_count; ++i) {
649  const std::string& param_name = signature.parameter_names[i]->value;
650  SourcePosition param_pos = signature.parameter_names[i]->pos;
651  std::string generated_name = AddParameter(
652  i, builtin, &parameters, &parameter_types, &parameter_bindings, true);
653  const Type* actual_type = signature.parameter_types.types[i];
654  std::vector<const Type*> expected_types;
655  if (param_name == "context") {
656  csa_ccfile() << " TNode<NativeContext> " << generated_name
657  << " = UncheckedParameter<NativeContext>("
658  << "Descriptor::kContext);\n";
659  csa_ccfile() << " USE(" << generated_name << ");\n";
660  expected_types = {TypeOracle::GetNativeContextType(),
661  TypeOracle::GetContextType()};
662  } else if (param_name == "receiver") {
663  csa_ccfile()
664  << " TNode<JSAny> " << generated_name << " = "
665  << (builtin->IsVarArgsJavaScript()
666  ? "arguments.GetReceiver()"
667  : "UncheckedParameter<JSAny>(Descriptor::kReceiver)")
668  << ";\n";
669  csa_ccfile() << " USE(" << generated_name << ");\n";
670  expected_types = {TypeOracle::GetJSAnyType()};
671  } else if (param_name == "newTarget") {
672  csa_ccfile() << " TNode<JSAny> " << generated_name
673  << " = UncheckedParameter<JSAny>("
674  << "Descriptor::kJSNewTarget);\n";
675  csa_ccfile() << " USE(" << generated_name << ");\n";
676  expected_types = {TypeOracle::GetJSAnyType()};
677  } else if (param_name == "target") {
678  csa_ccfile() << " TNode<JSFunction> " << generated_name
679  << " = UncheckedParameter<JSFunction>("
680  << "Descriptor::kJSTarget);\n";
681  csa_ccfile() << " USE(" << generated_name << ");\n";
682  expected_types = {TypeOracle::GetJSFunctionType()};
683  } else if (param_name == "dispatchHandle") {
684  if (V8_JS_LINKAGE_INCLUDES_DISPATCH_HANDLE_BOOL) {
685  csa_ccfile() << " TNode<JSDispatchHandleT> " << generated_name
686  << " = "
687  "UncheckedParameter<JSDispatchHandleT>(Descriptor::"
688  "kJSDispatchHandle);\n";
689  } else if (V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING_BOOL) {
690  csa_ccfile() << " TNode<JSDispatchHandleT> " << generated_name
691  << " = "
692  "ReinterpretCast<JSDispatchHandleT>("
693  "LoadJSFunctionDispatchHandle("
694  "UncheckedParameter<JSFunction>("
695  << "Descriptor::kJSTarget)));\n";
696  } else {
697  csa_ccfile() << " TNode<JSDispatchHandleT> " << generated_name
698  << " = InvalidDispatchHandleConstant();\n";
699  }
700  csa_ccfile() << " USE(" << generated_name << ");\n";
701  expected_types = {TypeOracle::GetDispatchHandleType()};
702  } else {
703  Error(
704  "Unexpected implicit parameter \"", param_name,
705  "\" for JavaScript calling convention, "
706  "expected \"context\", \"receiver\", \"target\", or \"newTarget\"")
707  .Position(param_pos);
708  expected_types = {actual_type};
709  }
710  if (std::find(expected_types.begin(), expected_types.end(),
711  actual_type) == expected_types.end()) {
712  Error("According to JavaScript calling convention, expected parameter ",
713  param_name, " to have type ", PrintList(expected_types, " or "),
714  " but found type ", *actual_type)
715  .Position(param_pos);
716  }
717  }
718 
719  for (size_t i = signature.implicit_count;
720  i < signature.parameter_names.size(); ++i) {
721  const std::string& parameter_name = signature.parameter_names[i]->value;
722  const Type* type = signature.types()[i];
723  const bool mark_as_used = signature.implicit_count > i;
724  std::string var = AddParameter(i, builtin, &parameters, &parameter_types,
725  &parameter_bindings, mark_as_used);
726  csa_ccfile() << " " << type->GetGeneratedTypeName() << " " << var
727  << " = "
728  << "UncheckedParameter<" << type->GetGeneratedTNodeTypeName()
729  << ">(Descriptor::k" << CamelifyString(parameter_name)
730  << ");\n";
731  csa_ccfile() << " USE(" << var << ");\n";
732  }
733 
734  } else {
735  DCHECK(builtin->IsStub());
736 
737  for (size_t i = 0; i < signature.parameter_names.size(); ++i) {
738  const std::string& parameter_name = signature.parameter_names[i]->value;
739  const Type* type = signature.types()[i];
740  const bool mark_as_used = signature.implicit_count > i;
741  std::string var = AddParameter(i, builtin, &parameters, &parameter_types,
742  &parameter_bindings, mark_as_used);
743  csa_ccfile() << " " << type->GetGeneratedTypeName() << " " << var
744  << " = "
745  << "UncheckedParameter<" << type->GetGeneratedTNodeTypeName()
746  << ">(Descriptor::k" << CamelifyString(parameter_name)
747  << ");\n";
748  csa_ccfile() << " USE(" << var << ");\n";
749  }
750  }
751 
752  if (builtin->use_counter_name()) {
753  DCHECK(!signature.parameter_types.types.empty());
754  DCHECK(signature.parameter_types.types[0] ==
755  TypeOracle::GetNativeContextType() ||
756  signature.parameter_types.types[0] == TypeOracle::GetContextType());
757  csa_ccfile() << " CodeStubAssembler(state_).CallRuntime("
758  << "Runtime::kIncrementUseCounter, parameter0, "
759  << "CodeStubAssembler(state_).SmiConstant("
760  << *builtin->use_counter_name() << "));\n";
761  }
762 
763  assembler_ = CfgAssembler(parameter_types);
764  const Type* body_result = Visit(*builtin->body());
765  if (body_result != TypeOracle::GetNeverType()) {
766  ReportError("control reaches end of builtin, expected return of a value");
767  }
768  CSAGenerator csa_generator{assembler().Result(), csa_ccfile(),
769  builtin->kind()};
770  csa_generator.EmitGraph(parameters);
771  assembler_ = std::nullopt;
772  csa_ccfile() << "}\n\n";
773 }
774 
775 const Type* ImplementationVisitor::Visit(VarDeclarationStatement* stmt) {
776  BlockBindings<LocalValue> block_bindings(&ValueBindingsManager::Get());
777  return Visit(stmt, &block_bindings);
778 }
779 
780 const Type* ImplementationVisitor::Visit(
781  VarDeclarationStatement* stmt, BlockBindings<LocalValue>* block_bindings) {
782  // const qualified variables are required to be initialized properly.
783  if (stmt->const_qualified && !stmt->initializer) {
784  ReportError("local constant \"", stmt->name, "\" is not initialized.");
785  }
786 
787  std::optional<const Type*> type;
788  if (stmt->type) {
789  type = TypeVisitor::ComputeType(*stmt->type);
790  }
791  std::optional<VisitResult> init_result;
792  if (stmt->initializer) {
793  StackScope scope(this);
794  init_result = Visit(*stmt->initializer);
795  if (type) {
796  init_result = GenerateImplicitConvert(*type, *init_result);
797  }
798  type = init_result->type();
799  if ((*type)->IsConstexpr() && !stmt->const_qualified) {
800  Error("Use 'const' instead of 'let' for variable '", stmt->name->value,
801  "' of constexpr type '", (*type)->ToString(), "'.")
802  .Position(stmt->name->pos)
803  .Throw();
804  }
805  init_result = scope.Yield(*init_result);
806  } else {
807  DCHECK(type.has_value());
808  if ((*type)->IsConstexpr()) {
809  ReportError("constexpr variables need an initializer");
810  }
811  TypeVector lowered_types = LowerType(*type);
812  for (const Type* t : lowered_types) {
813  assembler().Emit(PushUninitializedInstruction{TypeOracle::GetTopType(
814  "uninitialized variable '" + stmt->name->value + "' of type " +
815  t->ToString() + " originally defined at " +
816  PositionAsString(stmt->pos),
817  t)});
818  }
819  init_result =
820  VisitResult(*type, assembler().TopRange(lowered_types.size()));
821  }
822  LocationReference ref = stmt->const_qualified
823  ? LocationReference::Temporary(
824  *init_result, "const " + stmt->name->value)
825  : LocationReference::VariableAccess(*init_result);
826  block_bindings->Add(stmt->name, LocalValue{std::move(ref)});
827  return TypeOracle::GetVoidType();
828 }
829 
830 const Type* ImplementationVisitor::Visit(TailCallStatement* stmt) {
831  return Visit(stmt->call, true).type();
832 }
833 
834 VisitResult ImplementationVisitor::Visit(ConditionalExpression* expr) {
835  Block* true_block = assembler().NewBlock(assembler().CurrentStack());
836  Block* false_block = assembler().NewBlock(assembler().CurrentStack());
837  Block* done_block = assembler().NewBlock();
838  Block* true_conversion_block = assembler().NewBlock();
839  GenerateExpressionBranch(expr->condition, true_block, false_block);
840 
841  VisitResult left;
842  VisitResult right;
843 
844  {
845  // The code for both paths of the conditional need to be generated first
846  // before evaluating the conditional expression because the common type of
847  // the result of both the true and false of the condition needs to be known
848  // to convert both branches to a common type.
849  assembler().Bind(true_block);
850  StackScope left_scope(this);
851  left = Visit(expr->if_true);
852  assembler().Goto(true_conversion_block);
853 
854  const Type* common_type;
855  {
856  assembler().Bind(false_block);
857  StackScope right_scope(this);
858  right = Visit(expr->if_false);
859  common_type = GetCommonType(left.type(), right.type());
860  right = right_scope.Yield(GenerateImplicitConvert(common_type, right));
861  assembler().Goto(done_block);
862  }
863 
864  assembler().Bind(true_conversion_block);
865  left = left_scope.Yield(GenerateImplicitConvert(common_type, left));
866  assembler().Goto(done_block);
867  }
868 
869  assembler().Bind(done_block);
870  CHECK_EQ(left, right);
871  return left;
872 }
873 
874 VisitResult ImplementationVisitor::Visit(LogicalOrExpression* expr) {
875  StackScope outer_scope(this);
876  VisitResult left_result = Visit(expr->left);
877 
878  if (left_result.type()->IsConstexprBool()) {
879  VisitResult right_result = Visit(expr->right);
880  if (!right_result.type()->IsConstexprBool()) {
881  ReportError(
882  "expected type constexpr bool on right-hand side of operator "
883  "||");
884  }
885  return VisitResult(TypeOracle::GetConstexprBoolType(),
886  std::string("(") + left_result.constexpr_value() +
887  " || " + right_result.constexpr_value() + ")");
888  }
889 
890  Block* true_block = assembler().NewBlock();
891  Block* false_block = assembler().NewBlock();
892  Block* done_block = assembler().NewBlock();
893 
894  left_result = GenerateImplicitConvert(TypeOracle::GetBoolType(), left_result);
895  GenerateBranch(left_result, true_block, false_block);
896 
897  assembler().Bind(true_block);
898  VisitResult true_result = GenerateBoolConstant(true);
899  assembler().Goto(done_block);
900 
901  assembler().Bind(false_block);
902  VisitResult false_result;
903  {
904  StackScope false_block_scope(this);
905  false_result = false_block_scope.Yield(
906  GenerateImplicitConvert(TypeOracle::GetBoolType(), Visit(expr->right)));
907  }
908  assembler().Goto(done_block);
909 
910  assembler().Bind(done_block);
911  DCHECK_EQ(true_result, false_result);
912  return outer_scope.Yield(true_result);
913 }
914 
915 VisitResult ImplementationVisitor::Visit(LogicalAndExpression* expr) {
916  StackScope outer_scope(this);
917  VisitResult left_result = Visit(expr->left);
918 
919  if (left_result.type()->IsConstexprBool()) {
920  VisitResult right_result = Visit(expr->right);
921  if (!right_result.type()->IsConstexprBool()) {
922  ReportError(
923  "expected type constexpr bool on right-hand side of operator "
924  "&&");
925  }
926  return VisitResult(TypeOracle::GetConstexprBoolType(),
927  std::string("(") + left_result.constexpr_value() +
928  " && " + right_result.constexpr_value() + ")");
929  }
930 
931  Block* true_block = assembler().NewBlock();
932  Block* false_block = assembler().NewBlock();
933  Block* done_block = assembler().NewBlock();
934 
935  left_result = GenerateImplicitConvert(TypeOracle::GetBoolType(), left_result);
936  GenerateBranch(left_result, true_block, false_block);
937 
938  assembler().Bind(true_block);
939  VisitResult true_result;
940  {
941  StackScope true_block_scope(this);
942  VisitResult right_result = Visit(expr->right);
943  if (TryGetSourceForBitfieldExpression(expr->left) != nullptr &&
944  TryGetSourceForBitfieldExpression(expr->right) != nullptr &&
945  TryGetSourceForBitfieldExpression(expr->left)->value ==
946  TryGetSourceForBitfieldExpression(expr->right)->value) {
947  Lint(
948  "Please use & rather than && when checking multiple bitfield "
949  "values, to avoid complexity in generated code.");
950  }
951  true_result = true_block_scope.Yield(
952  GenerateImplicitConvert(TypeOracle::GetBoolType(), right_result));
953  }
954  assembler().Goto(done_block);
955 
956  assembler().Bind(false_block);
957  VisitResult false_result = GenerateBoolConstant(false);
958  assembler().Goto(done_block);
959 
960  assembler().Bind(done_block);
961  DCHECK_EQ(true_result, false_result);
962  return outer_scope.Yield(true_result);
963 }
964 
965 VisitResult ImplementationVisitor::Visit(IncrementDecrementExpression* expr) {
966  StackScope scope(this);
967  LocationReference location_ref = GetLocationReference(expr->location);
968  VisitResult current_value = GenerateFetchFromLocation(location_ref);
969  VisitResult one = {TypeOracle::GetConstInt31Type(), "1"};
970  Arguments args;
971  args.parameters = {current_value, one};
972  VisitResult assignment_value = GenerateCall(
973  expr->op == IncrementDecrementOperator::kIncrement ? "+" : "-", args);
974  GenerateAssignToLocation(location_ref, assignment_value);
975  return scope.Yield(expr->postfix ? current_value : assignment_value);
976 }
977 
978 VisitResult ImplementationVisitor::Visit(AssignmentExpression* expr) {
979  StackScope scope(this);
980  LocationReference location_ref = GetLocationReference(expr->location);
981  VisitResult assignment_value;
982  if (expr->op) {
983  VisitResult location_value = GenerateFetchFromLocation(location_ref);
984  assignment_value = Visit(expr->value);
985  Arguments args;
986  args.parameters = {location_value, assignment_value};
987  assignment_value = GenerateCall(*expr->op, args);
988  GenerateAssignToLocation(location_ref, assignment_value);
989  } else {
990  assignment_value = Visit(expr->value);
991  GenerateAssignToLocation(location_ref, assignment_value);
992  }
993  return scope.Yield(assignment_value);
994 }
995 
996 VisitResult ImplementationVisitor::Visit(FloatingPointLiteralExpression* expr) {
997  const Type* result_type = TypeOracle::GetConstFloat64Type();
998  std::stringstream str;
999  str << std::setprecision(std::numeric_limits<double>::digits10 + 1)
1000  << expr->value;
1001  return VisitResult{result_type, str.str()};
1002 }
1003 
1004 VisitResult ImplementationVisitor::Visit(IntegerLiteralExpression* expr) {
1005  const Type* result_type = TypeOracle::GetIntegerLiteralType();
1006  std::stringstream str;
1007  str << "IntegerLiteral("
1008  << (expr->value.is_negative() ? "true, 0x" : "false, 0x") << std::hex
1009  << expr->value.absolute_value() << std::dec << "ull)";
1010  return VisitResult{result_type, str.str()};
1011 }

1013 VisitResult ImplementationVisitor::Visit(AssumeTypeImpossibleExpression* expr) {
1014  VisitResult result = Visit(expr->expression);
1015  const Type* result_type = SubtractType(
1016  result.type(), TypeVisitor::ComputeType(expr->excluded_type));
1017  if (result_type->IsNever()) {
1018  ReportError("unreachable code");
1019  }
1020  CHECK_EQ(LowerType(result_type), TypeVector{result_type});
1021  assembler().Emit(UnsafeCastInstruction{result_type});
1022  result.SetType(result_type);
1023  return result;
1024 }

1026 VisitResult ImplementationVisitor::Visit(StringLiteralExpression* expr) {
1027  return VisitResult{
1028  TypeOracle::GetConstStringType(),
1029  "\"" + expr->literal.substr(1, expr->literal.size() - 2) + "\""};
1030 }

1032 VisitResult ImplementationVisitor::GetBuiltinCode(Builtin* builtin) {
1033  if (builtin->IsExternal() || builtin->kind() != Builtin::kStub) {
1034  ReportError(
1035  "creating function pointers is only allowed for internal builtins with "
1036  "stub linkage");
1037  }
1038  const Type* type = TypeOracle::GetBuiltinPointerType(
1039  builtin->signature().parameter_types.types,
1040  builtin->signature().return_type);
1041  assembler().Emit(
1042  PushBuiltinPointerInstruction{builtin->ExternalName(), type});
1043  return VisitResult(type, assembler().TopRange(1));
1044 }

1046 VisitResult ImplementationVisitor::Visit(LocationExpression* expr) {
1047  StackScope scope(this);
1048  return scope.Yield(GenerateFetchFromLocation(GetLocationReference(expr)));
1049 }
1050 
1051 VisitResult ImplementationVisitor::Visit(FieldAccessExpression* expr) {
1052  StackScope scope(this);
1053  LocationReference location = GetLocationReference(expr);
1054  if (location.IsBitFieldAccess()) {
1055  if (auto* identifier = IdentifierExpression::DynamicCast(expr->object)) {
1056  bitfield_expressions_[expr] = identifier->name;
1057  }
1058  }
1059  return scope.Yield(GenerateFetchFromLocation(location));
1060 }

1062 const Type* ImplementationVisitor::Visit(GotoStatement* stmt) {
1063  Binding<LocalLabel>* label = LookupLabel(stmt->label->value);
1064  size_t parameter_count = label->parameter_types.size();
1065  if (stmt->arguments.size() != parameter_count) {
1066  ReportError("goto to label has incorrect number of parameters (expected ",
1067  parameter_count, " found ", stmt->arguments.size(), ")");
1068  }
1069 
1070  if (GlobalContext::collect_language_server_data()) {
1071  LanguageServerData::AddDefinition(stmt->label->pos,
1072  label->declaration_position());
1073  }
1074  if (GlobalContext::collect_kythe_data()) {
1075  KytheData::AddBindingUse(stmt->label->pos, label);
1076  }
1077 
1078  size_t i = 0;
1079  StackRange arguments = assembler().TopRange(0);
1080  for (Expression* e : stmt->arguments) {
1081  StackScope scope(this);
1082  VisitResult result = Visit(e);
1083  const Type* parameter_type = label->parameter_types[i++];
1084  result = GenerateImplicitConvert(parameter_type, result);
1085  arguments.Extend(scope.Yield(result).stack_range());
1086  }
1087 
1088  assembler().Goto(label->block, arguments.Size());
1089  return TypeOracle::GetNeverType();
1090 }
1091 
1092 const Type* ImplementationVisitor::Visit(IfStatement* stmt) {
1093  bool has_else = stmt->if_false.has_value();
1094 
1095  if (stmt->is_constexpr) {
1096  VisitResult expression_result = Visit(stmt->condition);
1097 
1098  if (!(expression_result.type() == TypeOracle::GetConstexprBoolType())) {
1099  std::stringstream stream;
1100  stream << "expression should return type constexpr bool "
1101  << "but returns type " << *expression_result.type();
1102  ReportError(stream.str());
1103  }
1104 
1105  Block* true_block = assembler().NewBlock();
1106  Block* false_block = assembler().NewBlock();
1107  Block* done_block = assembler().NewBlock();
1108 
1109  assembler().Emit(ConstexprBranchInstruction{
1110  expression_result.constexpr_value(), true_block, false_block});
1111 
1112  assembler().Bind(true_block);
1113  const Type* left_result = Visit(stmt->if_true);
1114  if (left_result == TypeOracle::GetVoidType()) {
1115  assembler().Goto(done_block);
1116  }
1117 
1118  assembler().Bind(false_block);
1119  const Type* right_result = TypeOracle::GetVoidType();
1120  if (has_else) {
1121  right_result = Visit(*stmt->if_false);
1122  }
1123  if (right_result == TypeOracle::GetVoidType()) {
1124  assembler().Goto(done_block);
1125  }
1126 
1127  if (left_result->IsNever() != right_result->IsNever()) {
1128  std::stringstream stream;
1129  stream << "either both or neither branches in a constexpr if statement "
1130  "must reach their end at"
1131  << PositionAsString(stmt->pos);
1132  ReportError(stream.str());
1133  }
1134 
1135  if (left_result != TypeOracle::GetNeverType()) {
1136  assembler().Bind(done_block);
1137  }
1138  return left_result;
1139  } else {
1140  Block* true_block = assembler().NewBlock(assembler().CurrentStack(),
1141  IsDeferred(stmt->if_true));
1142  Block* false_block =
1143  assembler().NewBlock(assembler().CurrentStack(),
1144  stmt->if_false && IsDeferred(*stmt->if_false));
1145  GenerateExpressionBranch(stmt->condition, true_block, false_block);
1146 
1147  Block* done_block;
1148  bool live = false;
1149  if (has_else) {
1150  done_block = assembler().NewBlock();
1151  } else {
1152  done_block = false_block;
1153  live = true;
1154  }
1155 
1156  assembler().Bind(true_block);
1157  {
1158  const Type* result = Visit(stmt->if_true);
1159  if (result == TypeOracle::GetVoidType()) {
1160  live = true;
1161  assembler().Goto(done_block);
1162  }
1163  }
1164 
1165  if (has_else) {
1166  assembler().Bind(false_block);
1167  const Type* result = Visit(*stmt->if_false);
1168  if (result == TypeOracle::GetVoidType()) {
1169  live = true;
1170  assembler().Goto(done_block);
1171  }
1172  }
1173 
1174  if (live) {
1175  assembler().Bind(done_block);
1176  }
1177  return live ? TypeOracle::GetVoidType() : TypeOracle::GetNeverType();
1178  }
1179 }
1180 
1181 const Type* ImplementationVisitor::Visit(WhileStatement* stmt) {
1182  Block* body_block = assembler().NewBlock(assembler().CurrentStack());
1183  Block* exit_block = assembler().NewBlock(assembler().CurrentStack());
1184 
1185  Block* header_block = assembler().NewBlock();
1186  assembler().Goto(header_block);
1187 
1188  assembler().Bind(header_block);
1189  GenerateExpressionBranch(stmt->condition, body_block, exit_block);
1190 
1191  assembler().Bind(body_block);
1192  {
1193  BreakContinueActivator activator{exit_block, header_block};
1194  const Type* body_result = Visit(stmt->body);
1195  if (body_result != TypeOracle::GetNeverType()) {
1196  assembler().Goto(header_block);
1197  }
1198  }
1199 
1200  assembler().Bind(exit_block);
1201  return TypeOracle::GetVoidType();
1202 }
1203 
1204 const Type* ImplementationVisitor::Visit(BlockStatement* block) {
1205  BlockBindings<LocalValue> block_bindings(&ValueBindingsManager::Get());
1206  const Type* type = TypeOracle::GetVoidType();
1207  for (Statement* s : block->statements) {
1208  CurrentSourcePosition::Scope source_position(s->pos);
1209  if (type->IsNever()) {
1210  ReportError("statement after non-returning statement");
1211  }
1212  if (auto* var_declaration = VarDeclarationStatement::DynamicCast(s)) {
1213  type = Visit(var_declaration, &block_bindings);
1214  } else {
1215  type = Visit(s);
1216  }
1217  }
1218  return type;
1219 }
1220 
1221 const Type* ImplementationVisitor::Visit(DebugStatement* stmt) {
1222  std::string reason;
1223  const Type* return_type;
1224  AbortInstruction::Kind kind;
1225  switch (stmt->kind) {
1226  case DebugStatement::Kind::kUnreachable:
1227  // Use the same string as in C++ to simplify fuzzer pattern-matching.
1228  reason = base::kUnreachableCodeMessage;
1229  return_type = TypeOracle::GetNeverType();
1230  kind = AbortInstruction::Kind::kUnreachable;
1231  break;
1232  case DebugStatement::Kind::kDebug:
1233  reason = "debug break";
1234  return_type = TypeOracle::GetVoidType();
1235  kind = AbortInstruction::Kind::kDebugBreak;
1236  break;
1237  }
1238 #if defined(DEBUG)
1239  assembler().Emit(PrintErrorInstruction{"halting because of " + reason +
1240  " at " + PositionAsString(stmt->pos)});
1241 #endif
1242  assembler().Emit(AbortInstruction{kind});
1243  return return_type;
1244 }
1245 
1246 namespace {
1247 
1248 std::string FormatAssertSource(const std::string& str) {
1249  // Replace all whitespace characters with a space character.
1250  std::string str_no_newlines = str;
1251  std::replace_if(
1252  str_no_newlines.begin(), str_no_newlines.end(),
1253  [](unsigned char c) { return isspace(c); }, ' ');
1254 
1255  // str might include indentation, squash multiple space characters into one.
1256  std::string result;
1257  std::unique_copy(str_no_newlines.begin(), str_no_newlines.end(),
1258  std::back_inserter(result),
1259  [](char a, char b) { return a == ' ' && b == ' '; });
1260  return result;
1261 }
1262 
1263 } // namespace
1264 
1265 const Type* ImplementationVisitor::Visit(AssertStatement* stmt) {
1266  if (stmt->kind == AssertStatement::AssertKind::kStaticAssert) {
1267  std::string message =
1268  "static_assert(" + stmt->source + ") at " + ToString(stmt->pos);
1269  GenerateCall(QualifiedName({"", TORQUE_INTERNAL_NAMESPACE_STRING},
1270  STATIC_ASSERT_MACRO_STRING),
1271  Arguments{{Visit(stmt->expression),
1272  VisitResult(TypeOracle::GetConstexprStringType(),
1273  StringLiteralQuote(message))},
1274  {}});
1275  return TypeOracle::GetVoidType();
1276  }
1277  // When the sandbox is off, sbxchecks become dchecks.
1278  DCHECK_IMPLIES(stmt->kind == AssertStatement::AssertKind::kSbxCheck,
1279  V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX_BOOL);
1280  bool do_check = stmt->kind != AssertStatement::AssertKind::kDcheck ||
1281  GlobalContext::force_assert_statements();
1282 #if defined(DEBUG)
1283  do_check = true;
1284 #endif
1285  Block* resume_block;
1286 
1287  if (!do_check) {
1288  Block* unreachable_block = assembler().NewBlock(assembler().CurrentStack());
1289  resume_block = assembler().NewBlock(assembler().CurrentStack());
1290  assembler().Goto(resume_block);
1291  assembler().Bind(unreachable_block);
1292  }
1293 
1294  // CSA_DCHECK & co. are not used here on purpose for two reasons. First,
1295  // Torque allows and handles two types of expressions in the if protocol
1296  // automagically, ones that return TNode<BoolT> and those that use the
1297  // BranchIf(..., Label* true, Label* false) idiom. Because the machinery to
1298  // handle this is embedded in the expression handling and to it's not
1299  // possible to make the decision to use CSA_DCHECK or CSA_DCHECK_BRANCH
1300  // isn't trivial up-front. Secondly, on failure, the assert text should be
1301  // the corresponding Torque code, not the -gen.cc code, which would be the
1302  // case when using CSA_DCHECK_XXX.
1303  Block* true_block = assembler().NewBlock(assembler().CurrentStack());
1304  Block* false_block = assembler().NewBlock(assembler().CurrentStack(), true);
1305  GenerateExpressionBranch(stmt->expression, true_block, false_block);
1306 
1307  assembler().Bind(false_block);
1308 
1309  assembler().Emit(AbortInstruction{
1310  AbortInstruction::Kind::kAssertionFailure,
1311  "Torque assert '" + FormatAssertSource(stmt->source) + "' failed"});
1312 
1313  assembler().Bind(true_block);
1314 
1315  if (!do_check) {
1316  assembler().Bind(resume_block);
1317  }
1318 
1319  return TypeOracle::GetVoidType();
1320 }
1321 
1322 const Type* ImplementationVisitor::Visit(ExpressionStatement* stmt) {
1323  const Type* type = Visit(stmt->expression).type();
1324  return type->IsNever() ? type : TypeOracle::GetVoidType();
1325 }
1326 
1327 const Type* ImplementationVisitor::Visit(ReturnStatement* stmt) {
1328  Callable* current_callable = CurrentCallable::Get();
1329  if (current_callable->signature().return_type->IsNever()) {
1330  std::stringstream s;
1331  s << "cannot return from a function with return type never";
1332  ReportError(s.str());
1333  }
1334  LocalLabel* end =
1335  current_callable->IsMacro() ? LookupLabel(kMacroEndLabelName) : nullptr;
1336  if (current_callable->HasReturnValue()) {
1337  if (!stmt->value) {
1338  std::stringstream s;
1339  s << "return expression needs to be specified for a return type of "
1340  << *current_callable->signature().return_type;
1341  ReportError(s.str());
1342  }
1343  VisitResult expression_result = Visit(*stmt->value);
1344  VisitResult return_result = GenerateImplicitConvert(
1345  current_callable->signature().return_type, expression_result);
1346  if (current_callable->IsMacro()) {
1347  if (return_result.IsOnStack()) {
1348  StackRange return_value_range =
1349  GenerateLabelGoto(end, return_result.stack_range());
1350  SetReturnValue(VisitResult(return_result.type(), return_value_range));
1351  } else {
1352  GenerateLabelGoto(end);
1353  SetReturnValue(return_result);
1354  }
1355  } else if (current_callable->IsBuiltin()) {
1356  assembler().Emit(ReturnInstruction{
1357  LoweredSlotCount(current_callable->signature().return_type)});
1358  } else {
1359  UNREACHABLE();
1360  }
1361  } else {
1362  if (stmt->value) {
1363  std::stringstream s;
1364  s << "return expression can't be specified for a void or never return "
1365  "type";
1366  ReportError(s.str());
1367  }
1368  GenerateLabelGoto(end);
1369  }
1370  current_callable->IncrementReturns();
1371  return TypeOracle::GetNeverType();
1372 }
1373 
1374 VisitResult ImplementationVisitor::Visit(TryLabelExpression* expr) {
1375  size_t parameter_count = expr->label_block->parameters.names.size();
1376  std::vector<VisitResult> parameters;
1377 
1378  Block* label_block = nullptr;
1379  Block* done_block = assembler().NewBlock();
1380  VisitResult try_result;
1381 
1382  {
1383  CurrentSourcePosition::Scope source_position(expr->label_block->pos);
1384  if (expr->label_block->parameters.has_varargs) {
1385  ReportError("cannot use ... for label parameters");
1386  }
1387  Stack<const Type*> label_input_stack = assembler().CurrentStack();
1388  TypeVector parameter_types;
1389  for (size_t i = 0; i < parameter_count; ++i) {
1390  const Type* type =
1391  TypeVisitor::ComputeType(expr->label_block->parameters.types[i]);
1392  parameter_types.push_back(type);
1393  if (type->IsConstexpr()) {
1394  ReportError("no constexpr type allowed for label arguments");
1395  }
1396  StackRange range = label_input_stack.PushMany(LowerType(type));
1397  parameters.push_back(VisitResult(type, range));
1398  }
1399  label_block = assembler().NewBlock(label_input_stack,
1400  IsDeferred(expr->label_block->body));
1401 
1402  Binding<LocalLabel> label_binding{
1403  &LabelBindingsManager::Get(), expr->label_block->label,
1404  LocalLabel{label_block, std::move(parameter_types)}};
1405 
1406  // Visit try
1407  StackScope stack_scope(this);
1408  try_result = Visit(expr->try_expression);
1409  if (try_result.type() != TypeOracle::GetNeverType()) {
1410  try_result = stack_scope.Yield(try_result);
1411  assembler().Goto(done_block);
1412  }
1413  }
1414 
1415  // Visit and output the code for the label block. If the label block falls
1416  // through, then the try must not return a value. Also, if the try doesn't
1417  // fall through, but the label does, then overall the try-label block
1418  // returns type void.
1419  assembler().Bind(label_block);
1420  const Type* label_result;
1421  {
1422  BlockBindings<LocalValue> parameter_bindings(&ValueBindingsManager::Get());
1423  for (size_t i = 0; i < parameter_count; ++i) {
1424  Identifier* name = expr->label_block->parameters.names[i];
1425  parameter_bindings.Add(name,
1426  LocalValue{LocationReference::Temporary(
1427  parameters[i], "parameter " + name->value)});
1428  }
1429 
1430  label_result = Visit(expr->label_block->body);
1431  }
1432  if (!try_result.type()->IsVoidOrNever() && label_result->IsVoid()) {
1433  ReportError(
1434  "otherwise clauses cannot fall through in a non-void expression");
1435  }
1436  if (label_result != TypeOracle::GetNeverType()) {
1437  assembler().Goto(done_block);
1438  }
1439  if (label_result->IsVoid() && try_result.type()->IsNever()) {
1440  try_result =
1441  VisitResult(TypeOracle::GetVoidType(), try_result.stack_range());
1442  }
1443 
1444  if (!try_result.type()->IsNever()) {
1445  assembler().Bind(done_block);
1446  }
1447  return try_result;
1448 }
1449 
1450 VisitResult ImplementationVisitor::Visit(StatementExpression* expr) {
1451  return VisitResult{Visit(expr->statement), assembler().TopRange(0)};
1452 }
1453 
1454 InitializerResults ImplementationVisitor::VisitInitializerResults(
1455  const ClassType* class_type,
1456  const std::vector<NameAndExpression>& initializers) {
1457  InitializerResults result;
1458  for (const NameAndExpression& initializer : initializers) {
1459  result.names.push_back(initializer.name);
1460  Expression* e = initializer.expression;
1461  const Field& field = class_type->LookupField(initializer.name->value);
1462  bool has_index = field.index.has_value();
1463  if (SpreadExpression* s = SpreadExpression::DynamicCast(e)) {
1464  if (!has_index) {
1465  ReportError(
1466  "spread expressions can only be used to initialize indexed class "
1467  "fields ('",
1468  initializer.name->value, "' is not)");
1469  }
1470  e = s->spreadee;
1471  } else if (has_index) {
1472  ReportError("the indexed class field '", initializer.name->value,
1473  "' must be initialized with a spread operator");
1474  }
1475  result.field_value_map[field.name_and_type.name] = Visit(e);
1476  }
1477  return result;
1478 }
1479 
1480 LocationReference ImplementationVisitor::GenerateFieldReference(
1481  VisitResult object, const Field& field, const ClassType* class_type,
1482  bool treat_optional_as_indexed) {
1483  if (field.index.has_value()) {
1484  LocationReference slice = LocationReference::HeapSlice(
1485  GenerateCall(class_type->GetSliceMacroName(field), {{object}, {}}));
1486  if (field.index->optional && !treat_optional_as_indexed) {
1487  // This field was declared using optional syntax, so any reference to it
1488  // is implicitly a reference to the first item.
1489  return GenerateReferenceToItemInHeapSlice(
1490  slice, {TypeOracle::GetConstInt31Type(), "0"});
1491  } else {
1492  return slice;
1493  }
1494  }
1495  DCHECK(field.offset.has_value());
1496  StackRange result_range = assembler().TopRange(0);
1497  result_range.Extend(GenerateCopy(object).stack_range());
1498  VisitResult offset =
1499  VisitResult(TypeOracle::GetConstInt31Type(), ToString(*field.offset));
1500  offset = GenerateImplicitConvert(TypeOracle::GetIntPtrType(), offset);
1501  result_range.Extend(offset.stack_range());
1502  const Type* type = TypeOracle::GetReferenceType(field.name_and_type.type,
1503  field.const_qualified);
1504  return LocationReference::HeapReference(VisitResult(type, result_range),
1505  field.synchronization);
1506 }
1507 
1508 // This is used to generate field references during initialization, where we can
1509 // reuse the offsets used for computing the allocation size.
1510 LocationReference ImplementationVisitor::GenerateFieldReferenceForInit(
1511  VisitResult object, const Field& field,
1512  const LayoutForInitialization& layout) {
1513  StackRange result_range = assembler().TopRange(0);
1514  result_range.Extend(GenerateCopy(object).stack_range());
1515  VisitResult offset = GenerateImplicitConvert(
1516  TypeOracle::GetIntPtrType(), layout.offsets.at(field.name_and_type.name));
1517  result_range.Extend(offset.stack_range());
1518  if (field.index) {
1519  VisitResult length =
1520  GenerateCopy(layout.array_lengths.at(field.name_and_type.name));
1521  result_range.Extend(length.stack_range());
1522  const Type* slice_type =
1523  TypeOracle::GetMutableSliceType(field.name_and_type.type);
1524  return LocationReference::HeapSlice(VisitResult(slice_type, result_range));
1525  } else {
1526  // Const fields are writable during initialization.
1527  VisitResult heap_reference(
1528  TypeOracle::GetMutableReferenceType(field.name_and_type.type),
1529  result_range);
1530  return LocationReference::HeapReference(heap_reference);
1531  }
1532 }
1533 
1534 void ImplementationVisitor::InitializeClass(
1535  const ClassType* class_type, VisitResult allocate_result,
1536  const InitializerResults& initializer_results,
1537  const LayoutForInitialization& layout) {
1538  if (const ClassType* super = class_type->GetSuperClass()) {
1539  InitializeClass(super, allocate_result, initializer_results, layout);
1540  }
1541 
1542  for (const Field& f : class_type->fields()) {
1543  // Support optional padding fields.
1544  if (f.name_and_type.type->IsVoid()) continue;
1545  VisitResult initializer_value =
1546  initializer_results.field_value_map.at(f.name_and_type.name);
1547  LocationReference field =
1548  GenerateFieldReferenceForInit(allocate_result, f, layout);
1549  if (f.index) {
1550  DCHECK(field.IsHeapSlice());
1551  VisitResult slice = field.GetVisitResult();
1552  GenerateCall(QualifiedName({TORQUE_INTERNAL_NAMESPACE_STRING},
1553  "InitializeFieldsFromIterator"),
1554  {{slice, initializer_value}, {}});
1555  } else {
1556  GenerateAssignToLocation(field, initializer_value);
1557  }
1558  }
1559 }
1560 
1561 VisitResult ImplementationVisitor::GenerateArrayLength(
1562  Expression* array_length, Namespace* nspace,
1563  const std::map<std::string, LocalValue>& bindings) {
1564  StackScope stack_scope(this);
1565  CurrentSourcePosition::Scope pos_scope(array_length->pos);
1566  // Switch to the namespace where the class was declared.
1567  CurrentScope::Scope current_scope_scope(nspace);
1568  // Reset local bindings and install local binding for the preceding fields.
1569  BindingsManagersScope bindings_managers_scope;
1570  BlockBindings<LocalValue> field_bindings(&ValueBindingsManager::Get());
1571  for (auto& p : bindings) {
1572  field_bindings.Add(p.first, LocalValue{p.second}, true);
1573  }
1574  VisitResult length = Visit(array_length);
1575  VisitResult converted_length =
1576  GenerateCall("Convert", Arguments{{length}, {}},
1577  {TypeOracle::GetIntPtrType(), length.type()}, false);
1578  return stack_scope.Yield(converted_length);
1579 }
1580 
1581 VisitResult ImplementationVisitor::GenerateArrayLength(VisitResult object,
1582  const Field& field) {
1583  DCHECK(field.index);
1584 
1585  StackScope stack_scope(this);
1586  const ClassType* class_type = *object.type()->ClassSupertype();
1587  std::map<std::string, LocalValue> bindings;
1588  bool before_current = true;
1589  for (const Field& f : class_type->ComputeAllFields()) {
1590  if (field.name_and_type.name == f.name_and_type.name) {
1591  before_current = false;
1592  }
1593  // We can't generate field references eagerly here, because some preceding
1594  // fields might be optional, and attempting to get a reference to an
1595  // optional field can crash the program if the field isn't present.
1596  // Instead, we use the lazy form of LocalValue to only generate field
1597  // references if they are used in the length expression.
1598  bindings.insert(
1599  {f.name_and_type.name,
1600  f.const_qualified
1601  ? (before_current
1602  ? LocalValue{[this, object, f, class_type]() {
1603  return GenerateFieldReference(object, f, class_type);
1604  }}
1605  : LocalValue("Array lengths may only refer to fields "
1606  "defined earlier"))
1607  : LocalValue(
1608  "Non-const fields cannot be used for array lengths.")});
1609  }
1610  return stack_scope.Yield(
1611  GenerateArrayLength(field.index->expr, class_type->nspace(), bindings));
1612 }
1613 
1614 VisitResult ImplementationVisitor::GenerateArrayLength(
1615  const ClassType* class_type, const InitializerResults& initializer_results,
1616  const Field& field) {
1617  DCHECK(field.index);
1618 
1619  StackScope stack_scope(this);
1620  std::map<std::string, LocalValue> bindings;
1621  for (const Field& f : class_type->ComputeAllFields()) {
1622  if (f.index) break;
1623  const std::string& fieldname = f.name_and_type.name;
1624  VisitResult value = initializer_results.field_value_map.at(fieldname);
1625  bindings.insert(
1626  {fieldname,
1627  f.const_qualified
1628  ? LocalValue{LocationReference::Temporary(
1629  value, "initial field " + fieldname)}
1630  : LocalValue(
1631  "Non-const fields cannot be used for array lengths.")});
1632  }
1633  return stack_scope.Yield(
1634  GenerateArrayLength(field.index->expr, class_type->nspace(), bindings));
1635 }
1636 
1637 LayoutForInitialization ImplementationVisitor::GenerateLayoutForInitialization(
1638  const ClassType* class_type,
1639  const InitializerResults& initializer_results) {
1640  LayoutForInitialization layout;
1641  VisitResult offset;
1642  for (Field f : class_type->ComputeAllFields()) {
1643  if (f.offset.has_value()) {
1644  offset =
1645  VisitResult(TypeOracle::GetConstInt31Type(), ToString(*f.offset));
1646  }
1647  layout.offsets[f.name_and_type.name] = offset;
1648  if (f.index) {
1649  size_t element_size;
1650  std::string element_size_string;
1651  std::tie(element_size, element_size_string) =
1652  *SizeOf(f.name_and_type.type);
1653  VisitResult array_element_size =
1654  VisitResult(TypeOracle::GetConstInt31Type(), element_size_string);
1655  VisitResult array_length =
1656  GenerateArrayLength(class_type, initializer_results, f);
1657  layout.array_lengths[f.name_and_type.name] = array_length;
1658  Arguments arguments;
1659  arguments.parameters = {offset, array_length, array_element_size};
1660  offset = GenerateCall(QualifiedName({TORQUE_INTERNAL_NAMESPACE_STRING},
1661  "AddIndexedFieldSizeToObjectSize"),
1662  arguments);
1663  } else {
1664  DCHECK(f.offset.has_value());
1665  }
1666  }
1667  if (class_type->size().SingleValue()) {
1668  layout.size = VisitResult(TypeOracle::GetConstInt31Type(),
1669  ToString(*class_type->size().SingleValue()));
1670  } else {
1671  layout.size = offset;
1672  }
1673  if ((size_t{1} << class_type->size().AlignmentLog2()) <
1674  TargetArchitecture::TaggedSize()) {
1675  Arguments arguments;
1676  arguments.parameters = {layout.size};
1677  layout.size = GenerateCall(
1678  QualifiedName({TORQUE_INTERNAL_NAMESPACE_STRING}, "AlignTagged"),
1679  arguments);
1680  }
1681  return layout;
1682 }
1683 
1684 VisitResult ImplementationVisitor::Visit(NewExpression* expr) {
1685  StackScope stack_scope(this);
1686  const Type* type = TypeVisitor::ComputeType(expr->type);
1687  const ClassType* class_type = ClassType::DynamicCast(type);
1688  if (class_type == nullptr) {
1689  ReportError("type for new expression must be a class, \"", *type,
1690  "\" is not");
1691  }
1692 
1693  if (!class_type->AllowInstantiation()) {
1694  // Classes that are only used for testing should never be instantiated.
1695  ReportError(*class_type,
1696  " cannot be allocated with new (it's used for testing)");
1697  }
1698 
1699  InitializerResults initializer_results =
1700  VisitInitializerResults(class_type, expr->initializers);
1701 
1702  const Field& map_field = class_type->LookupField("map");
1703  if (*map_field.offset != 0) {
1704  ReportError("class initializers must have a map as first parameter");
1705  }
1706  const std::map<std::string, VisitResult>& initializer_fields =
1707  initializer_results.field_value_map;
1708  auto it_object_map = initializer_fields.find(map_field.name_and_type.name);
1709  VisitResult object_map;
1710  if (class_type->IsExtern()) {
1711  if (it_object_map == initializer_fields.end()) {
1712  ReportError("Constructor for ", class_type->name(),
1713  " needs Map argument!");
1714  }
1715  object_map = it_object_map->second;
1716  } else {
1717  if (it_object_map != initializer_fields.end()) {
1718  ReportError(
1719  "Constructor for ", class_type->name(),
1720  " must not specify Map argument; it is automatically inserted.");
1721  }
1722  Arguments get_struct_map_arguments;
1723  get_struct_map_arguments.parameters.push_back(
1724  VisitResult(TypeOracle::GetConstexprInstanceTypeType(),
1725  CapifyStringWithUnderscores(class_type->name()) + "_TYPE"));
1726  object_map = GenerateCall(
1727  QualifiedName({TORQUE_INTERNAL_NAMESPACE_STRING}, "GetInstanceTypeMap"),
1728  get_struct_map_arguments, {}, false);
1729  CurrentSourcePosition::Scope current_pos(expr->pos);
1730  initializer_results.names.insert(initializer_results.names.begin(),
1731  MakeNode<Identifier>("map"));
1732  initializer_results.field_value_map[map_field.name_and_type.name] =
1733  object_map;
1734  }
1735 
1736  CheckInitializersWellformed(class_type->name(),
1737  class_type->ComputeAllFields(),
1738  expr->initializers, !class_type->IsExtern());
1739 
1740  LayoutForInitialization layout =
1741  GenerateLayoutForInitialization(class_type, initializer_results);
1742 
1743  Arguments allocate_arguments;
1744  allocate_arguments.parameters.push_back(layout.size);
1745  allocate_arguments.parameters.push_back(object_map);
1746  allocate_arguments.parameters.push_back(
1747  GenerateBoolConstant(expr->pretenured));
1748  allocate_arguments.parameters.push_back(
1749  GenerateBoolConstant(expr->clear_padding));
1750  VisitResult allocate_result = GenerateCall(
1751  QualifiedName({TORQUE_INTERNAL_NAMESPACE_STRING}, "AllocateFromNew"),
1752  allocate_arguments, {class_type}, false);
1753  DCHECK(allocate_result.IsOnStack());
1754 
1755  InitializeClass(class_type, allocate_result, initializer_results, layout);
1756 
1757  return stack_scope.Yield(GenerateCall(
1758  "%RawDownCast", Arguments{{allocate_result}, {}}, {class_type}));
1759 }
1760 
1761 const Type* ImplementationVisitor::Visit(BreakStatement* stmt) {
1762  std::optional<Binding<LocalLabel>*> break_label =
1763  TryLookupLabel(kBreakLabelName);
1764  if (!break_label) {
1765  ReportError("break used outside of loop");
1766  }
1767  assembler().Goto((*break_label)->block);
1768  return TypeOracle::GetNeverType();
1769 }
1770 
1771 const Type* ImplementationVisitor::Visit(ContinueStatement* stmt) {
1772  std::optional<Binding<LocalLabel>*> continue_label =
1773  TryLookupLabel(kContinueLabelName);
1774  if (!continue_label) {
1775  ReportError("continue used outside of loop");
1776  }
1777  assembler().Goto((*continue_label)->block);
1778  return TypeOracle::GetNeverType();
1779 }
1780 
1781 const Type* ImplementationVisitor::Visit(ForLoopStatement* stmt) {
1782  BlockBindings<LocalValue> loop_bindings(&ValueBindingsManager::Get());
1783 
1784  if (stmt->var_declaration) Visit(*stmt->var_declaration, &loop_bindings);
1785 
1786  Block* body_block = assembler().NewBlock(assembler().CurrentStack());
1787  Block* exit_block = assembler().NewBlock(assembler().CurrentStack());
1788 
1789  Block* header_block = assembler().NewBlock();
1790  assembler().Goto(header_block);
1791  assembler().Bind(header_block);
1792 
1793  // The continue label is where "continue" statements jump to. If no action
1794  // expression is provided, we jump directly to the header.
1795  Block* continue_block = header_block;
1796 
1797  // The action label is only needed when an action expression was provided.
1798  Block* action_block = nullptr;
1799  if (stmt->action) {
1800  action_block = assembler().NewBlock();
1801 
1802  // The action expression needs to be executed on a continue.
1803  continue_block = action_block;
1804  }
1805 
1806  if (stmt->test) {
1807  GenerateExpressionBranch(*stmt->test, body_block, exit_block);
1808  } else {
1809  assembler().Goto(body_block);
1810  }
1811 
1812  assembler().Bind(body_block);
1813  {
1814  BreakContinueActivator activator(exit_block, continue_block);
1815  const Type* body_result = Visit(stmt->body);
1816  if (body_result != TypeOracle::GetNeverType()) {
1817  assembler().Goto(continue_block);
1818  }
1819  }
1820 
1821  if (stmt->action) {
1822  assembler().Bind(action_block);
1823  const Type* action_result = Visit(*stmt->action);
1824  if (action_result != TypeOracle::GetNeverType()) {
1825  assembler().Goto(header_block);
1826  }
1827  }
1828 
1829  assembler().Bind(exit_block);
1830  return TypeOracle::GetVoidType();
1831 }
1832 
1833 VisitResult ImplementationVisitor::Visit(SpreadExpression* expr) {
1834  ReportError(
1835  "spread operators are only currently supported in indexed class field "
1836  "initialization expressions");
1837 }
1838 
1839 void ImplementationVisitor::GenerateImplementation(const std::string& dir) {
1840  for (SourceId file : SourceFileMap::AllSources()) {
1841  std::string base_filename =
1842  dir + "/" + SourceFileMap::PathFromV8RootWithoutExtension(file);
1843  GlobalContext::PerFileStreams& streams =
1844  GlobalContext::GeneratedPerFile(file);
1845 
1846  std::string csa_cc = streams.csa_ccfile.str();
1847  // Insert missing builtin includes where the marker is.
1848  {
1849  auto pos = csa_cc.find(BuiltinIncludesMarker);
1850  CHECK_NE(pos, std::string::npos);
1851  std::string includes;
1852  for (const SourceId& include : streams.required_builtin_includes) {
1853  std::string include_file =
1854  SourceFileMap::PathFromV8RootWithoutExtension(include);
1855  includes += "#include \"torque-generated/";
1856  includes += include_file;
1857  includes += "-tq-csa.h\"\n";
1858  }
1859  csa_cc.replace(pos, strlen(BuiltinIncludesMarker), std::move(includes));
1860  }
1861 
1862  // TODO(torque-builder): Pass file directly.
1863  WriteFile(base_filename + "-tq-csa.cc", std::move(csa_cc));
1864  WriteFile(base_filename + "-tq-csa.h", streams.csa_headerfile.str());
1865  WriteFile(base_filename + "-tq.inc",
1866  streams.class_definition_headerfile.str());
1867  WriteFile(
1868  base_filename + "-tq-inl.inc",
1869  streams.class_definition_inline_headerfile_macro_declarations.str() +
1870  streams.class_definition_inline_headerfile_macro_definitions.str() +
1871  streams.class_definition_inline_headerfile.str());
1872  WriteFile(base_filename + "-tq.cc", streams.class_definition_ccfile.str());
1873  }
1874 
1875  WriteFile(dir + "/debug-macros.h", debug_macros_h_.str());
1876  WriteFile(dir + "/debug-macros.cc", debug_macros_cc_.str());
1877 }

1879 cpp::Function ImplementationVisitor::GenerateMacroFunctionDeclaration(
1880  Macro* macro) {
1881  return GenerateFunction(nullptr,
1882  output_type_ == OutputType::kCC
1883  ? macro->CCName()
1884  : output_type_ == OutputType::kCCDebug
1885  ? macro->CCDebugName()
1886  : macro->ExternalName(),
1887  macro->signature(), macro->parameter_names());
1888 }
1889 
1890 cpp::Function ImplementationVisitor::GenerateFunction(
1891  cpp::Class* owner, const std::string& name, const Signature& signature,
1892  const NameVector& parameter_names, bool pass_code_assembler_state,
1893  std::vector<std::string>* generated_parameter_names) {
1894  cpp::Function f(owner, name);
1895  f.SetInline(output_type_ == OutputType::kCC);
1896 
1897  // Set return type.
1898  // TODO(torque-builder): Consider an overload of SetReturnType that handles
1899  // this.
1900  if (signature.return_type->IsVoidOrNever()) {
1901  f.SetReturnType("void");
1902  } else if (output_type_ == OutputType::kCCDebug) {
1903  f.SetReturnType(std::string("Value<") +
1904  signature.return_type->GetDebugType() + ">");
1905  } else if (output_type_ == OutputType::kCC) {
1906  f.SetReturnType(signature.return_type->GetRuntimeType());
1907  } else {
1908  DCHECK_EQ(output_type_, OutputType::kCSA);
1909  f.SetReturnType(signature.return_type->IsConstexpr()
1910  ? signature.return_type->TagglifiedCppTypeName()
1911  : signature.return_type->GetGeneratedTypeName());
1912  }
1913 
1914  bool ignore_first_parameter = true;
1915  if (output_type_ == OutputType::kCCDebug) {
1916  f.AddParameter("d::MemoryAccessor", "accessor");
1917  } else if (output_type_ == OutputType::kCSA && pass_code_assembler_state) {
1918  f.AddParameter("compiler::CodeAssemblerState*", "state_");
1919  } else {
1920  ignore_first_parameter = false;
1921  }
1922 
1923  // TODO(torque-builder): Consider an overload for AddParameter that handles
1924  // this.
1925  DCHECK_GE(signature.types().size(), parameter_names.size());
1926  for (std::size_t i = 0; i < signature.types().size(); ++i) {
1927  const Type* parameter_type = signature.types()[i];
1928  std::string type;
1929  if (output_type_ == OutputType::kCC) {
1930  type = parameter_type->GetRuntimeType();
1931  } else if (output_type_ == OutputType::kCCDebug) {
1932  type = parameter_type->GetDebugType();
1933  } else {
1934  DCHECK_EQ(output_type_, OutputType::kCSA);
1935  if (parameter_type->IsConstexpr()) {
1936  type = parameter_type->TagglifiedCppTypeName();
1937  } else {
1938  type = parameter_type->GetGeneratedTypeName();
1939  }
1940  }
1941  f.AddParameter(std::move(type),
1942  ExternalParameterName(i < parameter_names.size()
1943  ? parameter_names[i]->value
1944  : std::to_string(i)));
1945  }
1946 
1947  for (const LabelDeclaration& label_info : signature.labels) {
1948  if (output_type_ == OutputType::kCC ||
1949  output_type_ == OutputType::kCCDebug) {
1950  ReportError("Macros that generate runtime code can't have label exits");
1951  }
1952  f.AddParameter("compiler::CodeAssemblerLabel*",
1953  ExternalLabelName(label_info.name->value));
1954  size_t i = 0;
1955  for (const Type* type : label_info.types) {
1956  std::string generated_type_name;
1957  if (type->StructSupertype()) {
1958  generated_type_name = "\n#error no structs allowed in labels\n";
1959  } else {
1960  generated_type_name = "compiler::TypedCodeAssemblerVariable<";
1961  generated_type_name += type->GetGeneratedTNodeTypeName();
1962  generated_type_name += ">*";
1963  }
1964  f.AddParameter(generated_type_name,
1965  ExternalLabelParameterName(label_info.name->value, i));
1966  ++i;
1967  }
1968  }
1969 
1970  if (generated_parameter_names) {
1971  *generated_parameter_names = f.GetParameterNames();
1972  if (ignore_first_parameter) {
1973  DCHECK(!generated_parameter_names->empty());
1974  generated_parameter_names->erase(generated_parameter_names->begin());
1975  }
1976  }
1977  return f;
1978 }

1980 namespace {
1981 
1982 void FailCallableLookup(
1983  const std::string& reason, const QualifiedName& name,
1984  const TypeVector& parameter_types,
1985  const std::vector<Binding<LocalLabel>*>& labels,
1986  const std::vector<Signature>& candidates,
1987  const std::vector<std::pair<GenericCallable*, std::string>>
1988  inapplicable_generics) {
1989  std::stringstream stream;
1990  stream << "\n" << reason << ": \n " << name << "(" << parameter_types << ")";
1991  if (!labels.empty()) {
1992  stream << " labels ";
1993  for (size_t i = 0; i < labels.size(); ++i) {
1994  stream << labels[i]->name() << "(" << labels[i]->parameter_types << ")";
1995  }
1996  }
1997  stream << "\ncandidates are:";
1998  for (const Signature& signature : candidates) {
1999  stream << "\n " << name;
2000  PrintSignature(stream, signature, false);
2001  }
2002  if (!inapplicable_generics.empty()) {
2003  stream << "\nfailed to instantiate all of these generic declarations:";
2004  for (auto& failure : inapplicable_generics) {
2005  GenericCallable* generic = failure.first;
2006  const std::string& fail_reason = failure.second;
2007  stream << "\n " << generic->name() << " defined at "
2008  << PositionAsString(generic->Position()) << ":\n "
2009  << fail_reason << "\n";
2010  }
2011  }
2012  ReportError(stream.str());
2013 }
2014 
2015 Callable* GetOrCreateSpecialization(
2016  const SpecializationKey<GenericCallable>& key) {
2017  if (std::optional<Callable*> specialization =
2018  key.generic->GetSpecialization(key.specialized_types)) {
2019  return *specialization;
2020  }
2021  return DeclarationVisitor::SpecializeImplicit(key);
2022 }
