2053 // Try to lookup a callable with the provided argument types. Do not report
2054 // an error if no matching callable was found, but return false instead.
2055 // This is used to test the presence of overloaded field accessors.
2056 bool ImplementationVisitor::TestLookupCallable(
2057  const QualifiedName& name, const TypeVector& parameter_types) {
2058  return LookupCallable(name, Declarations::TryLookup(name), parameter_types,
2059  {}, {}, true) != nullptr;
2060 }
2061 
2062 TypeArgumentInference ImplementationVisitor::InferSpecializationTypes(
2063  GenericCallable* generic, const TypeVector& explicit_specialization_types,
2064  const TypeVector& explicit_arguments) {
2065  std::vector<std::optional<const Type*>> all_arguments;
2066  const ParameterList& parameters = generic->declaration()->parameters;
2067  for (size_t i = 0; i < parameters.implicit_count; ++i) {
2068  std::optional<Binding<LocalValue>*> val =
2069  TryLookupLocalValue(parameters.names[i]->value);
2070  all_arguments.push_back(
2071  val ? (*val)->GetLocationReference(*val).ReferencedType()
2072  : std::nullopt);
2073  }
2074  for (const Type* explicit_argument : explicit_arguments) {
2075  all_arguments.push_back(explicit_argument);
2076  }
2077  return generic->InferSpecializationTypes(explicit_specialization_types,
2078  all_arguments);
2079 }
2080 
2081 template <class Container>
2082 Callable* ImplementationVisitor::LookupCallable(
2083  const QualifiedName& name, const Container& declaration_container,
2084  const TypeVector& parameter_types,
2085  const std::vector<Binding<LocalLabel>*>& labels,
2086  const TypeVector& specialization_types, bool silence_errors) {
2087  Callable* result = nullptr;
2088 
2089  std::vector<Declarable*> overloads;
2090  std::vector<Signature> overload_signatures;
2091  std::vector<std::pair<GenericCallable*, std::string>> inapplicable_generics;
2092  for (auto* declarable : declaration_container) {
2093  if (GenericCallable* generic = GenericCallable::DynamicCast(declarable)) {
2094  TypeArgumentInference inference = InferSpecializationTypes(
2095  generic, specialization_types, parameter_types);
2096  if (inference.HasFailed()) {
2097  inapplicable_generics.push_back(
2098  std::make_pair(generic, inference.GetFailureReason()));
2099  continue;
2100  }
2101  overloads.push_back(generic);
2102  overload_signatures.push_back(
2103  DeclarationVisitor::MakeSpecializedSignature(
2104  SpecializationKey<GenericCallable>{generic,
2105  inference.GetResult()}));
2106  } else if (Callable* callable = Callable::DynamicCast(declarable)) {
2107  overloads.push_back(callable);
2108  overload_signatures.push_back(callable->signature());
2109  }
2110  }
2111  // Indices of candidates in overloads/overload_signatures.
2112  std::vector<size_t> candidates;
2113  for (size_t i = 0; i < overloads.size(); ++i) {
2114  const Signature& signature = overload_signatures[i];
2115  if (IsCompatibleSignature(signature, parameter_types, labels.size())) {
2116  candidates.push_back(i);
2117  }
2118  }
2119 
2120  if (overloads.empty() && inapplicable_generics.empty()) {
2121  if (silence_errors) return nullptr;
2122  std::stringstream stream;
2123  stream << "no matching declaration found for " << name;
2124  ReportError(stream.str());
2125  } else if (candidates.empty()) {
2126  if (silence_errors) return nullptr;
2127  FailCallableLookup("cannot find suitable callable with name", name,
2128  parameter_types, labels, overload_signatures,
2129  inapplicable_generics);
2130  }
2131 
2132  auto is_better_candidate = [&](size_t a, size_t b) {
2133  return ParameterDifference(overload_signatures[a].GetExplicitTypes(),
2134  parameter_types)
2135  .StrictlyBetterThan(ParameterDifference(
2136  overload_signatures[b].GetExplicitTypes(), parameter_types));
2137  };
2138 
2139  size_t best = *std::min_element(candidates.begin(), candidates.end(),
2140  is_better_candidate);
2141  // This check is contained in libstdc++'s std::min_element.
2142  DCHECK(!is_better_candidate(best, best));
2143  for (size_t candidate : candidates) {
2144  if (candidate != best && !is_better_candidate(best, candidate)) {
2145  std::vector<Signature> candidate_signatures;
2146  candidate_signatures.reserve(candidates.size());
2147  for (size_t i : candidates) {
2148  candidate_signatures.push_back(overload_signatures[i]);
2149  }
2150  FailCallableLookup("ambiguous callable ", name, parameter_types, labels,
2151  candidate_signatures, inapplicable_generics);
2152  }
2153  }
2154 
2155  if (GenericCallable* generic =
2156  GenericCallable::DynamicCast(overloads[best])) {
2157  TypeArgumentInference inference = InferSpecializationTypes(
2158  generic, specialization_types, parameter_types);
2159  result = GetOrCreateSpecialization(
2160  SpecializationKey<GenericCallable>{generic, inference.GetResult()});
2161  } else {
2162  result = Callable::cast(overloads[best]);
2163  }
2164 
2165  size_t caller_size = parameter_types.size();
2166  size_t callee_size =
2167  result->signature().types().size() - result->signature().implicit_count;
2168  if (caller_size != callee_size &&
2169  !result->signature().parameter_types.var_args) {
2170  std::stringstream stream;
2171  stream << "parameter count mismatch calling " << *result << " - expected "
2172  << std::to_string(callee_size) << ", found "
2173  << std::to_string(caller_size);
2174  ReportError(stream.str());
2175  }
2176 
2177  return result;
2178 }
2179 
2180 template <class Container>
2181 Callable* ImplementationVisitor::LookupCallable(
2182  const QualifiedName& name, const Container& declaration_container,
2183  const Arguments& arguments, const TypeVector& specialization_types) {
2184  return LookupCallable(name, declaration_container,
2185  arguments.parameters.ComputeTypeVector(),
2186  arguments.labels, specialization_types);

2189 Method* ImplementationVisitor::LookupMethod(
2190  const std::string& name, const AggregateType* receiver_type,
2191  const Arguments& arguments, const TypeVector& specialization_types) {
2192  TypeVector types(arguments.parameters.ComputeTypeVector());
2193  types.insert(types.begin(), receiver_type);
2194  return Method::cast(LookupCallable({{}, name}, receiver_type->Methods(name),
2195  types, arguments.labels,
2196  specialization_types));

2198 
2199 const Type* ImplementationVisitor::GetCommonType(const Type* left,
2200  const Type* right) {
2201  const Type* common_type;
2202  if (IsAssignableFrom(left, right)) {
2203  common_type = left;
2204  } else if (IsAssignableFrom(right, left)) {
2205  common_type = right;
2206  } else {
2207  common_type = TypeOracle::GetUnionType(left, right);
2208  }
2209  common_type = common_type->NonConstexprVersion();
2210  return common_type;
2211 }
2212 
2213 VisitResult ImplementationVisitor::GenerateCopy(const VisitResult& to_copy) {
2214  if (to_copy.IsOnStack()) {
2215  return VisitResult(to_copy.type(),
2216  assembler().Peek(to_copy.stack_range(), to_copy.type()));
2217  }
2218  return to_copy;
2219 }
2220 
2221 VisitResult ImplementationVisitor::Visit(StructExpression* expr) {
2222  StackScope stack_scope(this);
2223 
2224  auto& initializers = expr->initializers;
2225  std::vector<VisitResult> values;
2226  std::vector<const Type*> term_argument_types;
2227  values.reserve(initializers.size());
2228  term_argument_types.reserve(initializers.size());
2229 
2230  // Compute values and types of all initializer arguments
2231  for (const NameAndExpression& initializer : initializers) {
2232  VisitResult value = Visit(initializer.expression);
2233  values.push_back(value);
2234  term_argument_types.push_back(value.type());
2235  }
2236 
2237  // Compute and check struct type from given struct name and argument types
2238  const Type* type = TypeVisitor::ComputeTypeForStructExpression(
2239  expr->type, term_argument_types);
2240  if (const auto* struct_type = StructType::DynamicCast(type)) {
2241  CheckInitializersWellformed(struct_type->name(), struct_type->fields(),
2242  initializers);
2243 
2244  // Implicitly convert values and thereby build the struct on the stack
2245  StackRange struct_range = assembler().TopRange(0);
2246  auto& fields = struct_type->fields();
2247  for (size_t i = 0; i < values.size(); i++) {
2248  values[i] =
2249  GenerateImplicitConvert(fields[i].name_and_type.type, values[i]);
2250  struct_range.Extend(values[i].stack_range());
2251  }
2252 
2253  return stack_scope.Yield(VisitResult(struct_type, struct_range));
2254  } else {
2255  const auto* bitfield_struct_type = BitFieldStructType::cast(type);
2256  CheckInitializersWellformed(bitfield_struct_type->name(),
2257  bitfield_struct_type->fields(), initializers);
2258 
2259  // Create a zero and cast it to the desired bitfield struct type.
2260  VisitResult result{TypeOracle::GetConstInt32Type(), "0"};
2261  result = GenerateImplicitConvert(TypeOracle::GetInt32Type(), result);
2262  result = GenerateCall("Unsigned", Arguments{{result}, {}}, {});
2263  result = GenerateCall("%RawDownCast", Arguments{{result}, {}},
2264  {bitfield_struct_type});
2265 
2266  // Set each field in the result. If these fields are constexpr, then all of
2267  // this initialization will end up reduced to a single value during TurboFan
2268  // optimization.
2269  auto& fields = bitfield_struct_type->fields();
2270  for (size_t i = 0; i < values.size(); i++) {
2271  values[i] =
2272  GenerateImplicitConvert(fields[i].name_and_type.type, values[i]);
2273  result = GenerateSetBitField(bitfield_struct_type, fields[i], result,
2274  values[i], /*starts_as_zero=*/true);
2275  }
2276 
2277  return stack_scope.Yield(result);
2278  }
2279 }
2280 
2281 VisitResult ImplementationVisitor::GenerateSetBitField(
2282  const Type* bitfield_struct_type, const BitField& bitfield,
2283  VisitResult bitfield_struct, VisitResult value, bool starts_as_zero) {
2284  GenerateCopy(bitfield_struct);
2285  GenerateCopy(value);
2286  assembler().Emit(
2287  StoreBitFieldInstruction{bitfield_struct_type, bitfield, starts_as_zero});
2288  return VisitResult(bitfield_struct_type, assembler().TopRange(1));
2289 }
2290 
2291 LocationReference ImplementationVisitor::GetLocationReference(
2292  Expression* location) {
2293  switch (location->kind) {
2294  case AstNode::Kind::kIdentifierExpression:
2295  return GetLocationReference(static_cast<IdentifierExpression*>(location));
2296  case AstNode::Kind::kFieldAccessExpression:
2297  return GetLocationReference(
2298  static_cast<FieldAccessExpression*>(location));
2299  case AstNode::Kind::kElementAccessExpression:
2300  return GetLocationReference(
2301  static_cast<ElementAccessExpression*>(location));
2302  case AstNode::Kind::kDereferenceExpression:
2303  return GetLocationReference(
2304  static_cast<DereferenceExpression*>(location));
2305  default:
2306  return LocationReference::Temporary(Visit(location), "expression");
2307  }
2308 }
2309 
2310 LocationReference ImplementationVisitor::GetLocationReference(
2311  FieldAccessExpression* expr) {
2312  return GenerateFieldAccess(GetLocationReference(expr->object),
2313  expr->field->value, false, expr->field->pos);
2314 }
2315 
2316 LocationReference ImplementationVisitor::GenerateFieldAccess(
2317  LocationReference reference, const std::string& fieldname,
2318  bool ignore_stuct_field_constness, std::optional<SourcePosition> pos) {
2319  if (reference.IsVariableAccess() &&
2320  reference.variable().type()->StructSupertype()) {
2321  const StructType* type = *reference.variable().type()->StructSupertype();
2322  const Field& field = type->LookupField(fieldname);
2323  if (GlobalContext::collect_language_server_data() && pos.has_value()) {
2324  LanguageServerData::AddDefinition(*pos, field.pos);
2325  }
2326  if (GlobalContext::collect_kythe_data() && pos.has_value()) {
2327  KytheData::AddClassFieldUse(*pos, &field);
2328  }
2329  if (field.const_qualified) {
2330  VisitResult t_value = ProjectStructField(reference.variable(), fieldname);
2331  return LocationReference::Temporary(
2332  t_value, "for constant field '" + field.name_and_type.name + "'");
2333  } else {
2334  return LocationReference::VariableAccess(
2335  ProjectStructField(reference.variable(), fieldname));
2336  }
2337  }
2338  if (reference.IsTemporary() &&
2339  reference.temporary().type()->StructSupertype()) {
2340  if (GlobalContext::collect_language_server_data() && pos.has_value()) {
2341  const StructType* type = *reference.temporary().type()->StructSupertype();
2342  const Field& field = type->LookupField(fieldname);
2343  LanguageServerData::AddDefinition(*pos, field.pos);
2344  }
2345  return LocationReference::Temporary(
2346  ProjectStructField(reference.temporary(), fieldname),
2347  reference.temporary_description());
2348  }
2349  if (std::optional<const Type*> referenced_type = reference.ReferencedType()) {
2350  if ((*referenced_type)->IsBitFieldStructType()) {
2351  const BitFieldStructType* bitfield_struct =
2352  BitFieldStructType::cast(*referenced_type);
2353  const BitField& field = bitfield_struct->LookupField(fieldname);
2354  return LocationReference::BitFieldAccess(reference, field);
2355  }
2356  if (const auto type_wrapped_in_smi = Type::MatchUnaryGeneric(
2357  (*referenced_type), TypeOracle::GetSmiTaggedGeneric())) {
2358  const BitFieldStructType* bitfield_struct =
2359  BitFieldStructType::DynamicCast(*type_wrapped_in_smi);
2360  if (bitfield_struct == nullptr) {
2361  ReportError(
2362  "When a value of type SmiTagged<T> is used in a field access "
2363  "expression, T is expected to be a bitfield struct type. Instead, "
2364  "T "
2365  "is ",
2366  **type_wrapped_in_smi);
2367  }
2368  const BitField& field = bitfield_struct->LookupField(fieldname);
2369  return LocationReference::BitFieldAccess(reference, field);
2370  }
2371  }
2372  if (reference.IsHeapReference()) {
2373  VisitResult ref = reference.heap_reference();
2374  bool is_const;
2375  auto generic_type =
2376  TypeOracle::MatchReferenceGeneric(ref.type(), &is_const);
2377  if (!generic_type) {
2378  ReportError(
2379  "Left-hand side of field access expression is marked as a reference "
2380  "but is not of type Reference<...>. Found type: ",
2381  ref.type()->ToString());
2382  }
2383  if (auto struct_type = (*generic_type)->StructSupertype()) {
2384  const Field& field = (*struct_type)->LookupField(fieldname);
2385  // Update the Reference's type to refer to the field type within the
2386  // struct.
2387  ref.SetType(TypeOracle::GetReferenceType(
2388  field.name_and_type.type,
2389  is_const ||
2390  (field.const_qualified && !ignore_stuct_field_constness)));
2391  if (!field.offset.has_value()) {
2392  Error("accessing field with unknown offset").Throw();
2393  }
2394  if (*field.offset != 0) {
2395  // Copy the Reference struct up the stack and update the new copy's
2396  // |offset| value to point to the struct field.
2397  StackScope scope(this);
2398  ref = GenerateCopy(ref);
2399  VisitResult ref_offset = ProjectStructField(ref, "offset");
2400  VisitResult struct_offset{
2401  TypeOracle::GetIntPtrType()->ConstexprVersion(),
2402  std::to_string(*field.offset)};
2403  VisitResult updated_offset =
2404  GenerateCall("+", Arguments{{ref_offset, struct_offset}, {}});
2405  assembler().Poke(ref_offset.stack_range(), updated_offset.stack_range(),
2406  ref_offset.type());
2407  ref = scope.Yield(ref);
2408  }
2409  return LocationReference::HeapReference(ref);
2410  }
2411  }
2412  VisitResult object_result = GenerateFetchFromLocation(reference);
2413  if (std::optional<const ClassType*> class_type =
2414  object_result.type()->ClassSupertype()) {
2415  // This is a hack to distinguish the situation where we want to use
2416  // overloaded field accessors from when we want to create a reference.
2417  bool has_explicit_overloads = TestLookupCallable(
2418  QualifiedName{"." + fieldname}, {object_result.type()});
2419  if ((*class_type)->HasField(fieldname) && !has_explicit_overloads) {
2420  const Field& field = (*class_type)->LookupField(fieldname);
2421  if (GlobalContext::collect_language_server_data() && pos.has_value()) {
2422  LanguageServerData::AddDefinition(*pos, field.pos);
2423  }
2424  if (GlobalContext::collect_kythe_data()) {
2425  KytheData::AddClassFieldUse(*pos, &field);
2426  }
2427  return GenerateFieldReference(object_result, field, *class_type);
2428  }
2429  }
2430  return LocationReference::FieldAccess(object_result, fieldname);
2431 }
2432 
2433 LocationReference ImplementationVisitor::GetLocationReference(
2434  ElementAccessExpression* expr) {
2435  LocationReference reference = GetLocationReference(expr->array);
2436  VisitResult index = Visit(expr->index);
2437  if (reference.IsHeapSlice()) {
2438  return GenerateReferenceToItemInHeapSlice(reference, index);
2439  } else {
2440  return LocationReference::ArrayAccess(GenerateFetchFromLocation(reference),
2441  index);
2442  }
2443 }
2444 
2445 LocationReference ImplementationVisitor::GenerateReferenceToItemInHeapSlice(
2446  LocationReference slice, VisitResult index) {
2447  DCHECK(slice.IsHeapSlice());
2448  Arguments arguments{{index}, {}};
2449  const StructType* slice_type = *slice.heap_slice().type()->StructSupertype();
2450  Method* method = LookupMethod("AtIndex", slice_type, arguments, {});
2451  // The reference has to be treated like a normal value when calling methods
2452  // on the underlying slice implementation.
2453  LocationReference slice_value =
2454  LocationReference::Temporary(slice.GetVisitResult(), "slice as value");
2455  return LocationReference::HeapReference(
2456  GenerateCall(method, std::move(slice_value), arguments, {}, false));
2457 }
2458 
2459 LocationReference ImplementationVisitor::GetLocationReference(
2460  IdentifierExpression* expr) {
2461  if (expr->namespace_qualification.empty()) {
2462  if (std::optional<Binding<LocalValue>*> value =
2463  TryLookupLocalValue(expr->name->value)) {
2464  if (GlobalContext::collect_language_server_data()) {
2465  LanguageServerData::AddDefinition(expr->name->pos,
2466  (*value)->declaration_position());
2467  }
2468  if (GlobalContext::collect_kythe_data()) {
2469  if (!expr->IsThis()) {
2470  DCHECK_EQ(expr->name->pos.end.column - expr->name->pos.start.column,
2471  expr->name->value.length());
2472  KytheData::AddBindingUse(expr->name->pos, *value);
2473  }
2474  }
2475  if (!expr->generic_arguments.empty()) {
2476  ReportError("cannot have generic parameters on local name ",
2477  expr->name);
2478  }
2479  return (*value)->GetLocationReference(*value);
2480  }
2481  }
2482 
2483  if (expr->IsThis()) {
2484  ReportError("\"this\" cannot be qualified");
2485  }
2486  QualifiedName name =
2487  QualifiedName(expr->namespace_qualification, expr->name->value);
2488  if (std::optional<Builtin*> builtin = Declarations::TryLookupBuiltin(name)) {
2489  if (GlobalContext::collect_language_server_data()) {
2490  LanguageServerData::AddDefinition(expr->name->pos,
2491  (*builtin)->Position());
2492  }
2493  // TODO(v8:12261): Consider collecting KytheData here.
2494  return LocationReference::Temporary(GetBuiltinCode(*builtin),
2495  "builtin " + expr->name->value);
2496  }
2497  if (!expr->generic_arguments.empty()) {
2498  GenericCallable* generic = Declarations::LookupUniqueGeneric(name);
2499  Callable* specialization =
2500  GetOrCreateSpecialization(SpecializationKey<GenericCallable>{
2501  generic, TypeVisitor::ComputeTypeVector(expr->generic_arguments)});
2502  if (Builtin* builtin = Builtin::DynamicCast(specialization)) {
2503  DCHECK(!builtin->IsExternal());
2504  return LocationReference::Temporary(GetBuiltinCode(builtin),
2505  "builtin " + expr->name->value);
2506  } else {
2507  ReportError("cannot create function pointer for non-builtin ",
2508  generic->name());
2509  }
2510  }
2511  Value* value = Declarations::LookupValue(name);
2512  CHECK(value->Position().source.IsValid());
2513  if (auto stream = CurrentFileStreams::Get()) {
2514  stream->required_builtin_includes.insert(value->Position().source);
2515  }
2516  if (GlobalContext::collect_language_server_data()) {
2517  LanguageServerData::AddDefinition(expr->name->pos, value->name()->pos);
2518  }
2519  if (auto* constant = NamespaceConstant::DynamicCast(value)) {
2520  if (GlobalContext::collect_kythe_data()) {
2521  KytheData::AddConstantUse(expr->name->pos, constant);
2522  }
2523  if (constant->type()->IsConstexpr()) {
2524  return LocationReference::Temporary(
2525  VisitResult(constant->type(), constant->external_name() + "(state_)"),
2526  "namespace constant " + expr->name->value);
2527  }
2528  assembler().Emit(NamespaceConstantInstruction{constant});
2529  StackRange stack_range =
2530  assembler().TopRange(LoweredSlotCount(constant->type()));
2531  return LocationReference::Temporary(
2532  VisitResult(constant->type(), stack_range),
2533  "namespace constant " + expr->name->value);
2534  }
2535  ExternConstant* constant = ExternConstant::cast(value);
2536  if (GlobalContext::collect_kythe_data()) {
2537  KytheData::AddConstantUse(expr->name->pos, constant);
2538  }
2539  return LocationReference::Temporary(constant->value(),
2540  "extern value " + expr->name->value);
2541 }
2542 
2543 LocationReference ImplementationVisitor::GetLocationReference(
2544  DereferenceExpression* expr) {
2545  VisitResult ref = Visit(expr->reference);
2546  if (!TypeOracle::MatchReferenceGeneric(ref.type())) {
2547  Error("Operator * expects a reference type but found a value of type ",
2548  *ref.type())
2549  .Throw();
2550  }
2551  return LocationReference::HeapReference(ref);
2552 }
2553 
2554 VisitResult ImplementationVisitor::GenerateFetchFromLocation(
2555  const LocationReference& reference) {
2556  if (reference.IsTemporary()) {
2557  return GenerateCopy(reference.temporary());
2558  } else if (reference.IsVariableAccess()) {
2559  return GenerateCopy(reference.variable());
2560  } else if (reference.IsHeapReference()) {
2561  const Type* referenced_type = *reference.ReferencedType();
2562  if (referenced_type == TypeOracle::GetFloat64OrUndefinedOrHoleType()) {
2563  return GenerateCall(QualifiedName({TORQUE_INTERNAL_NAMESPACE_STRING},
2564 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_EXPERIMENTAL_UNDEFINED_DOUBLE
2565  "LoadFloat64OrUndefinedOrHole"
2566 #else
2567  "LoadFloat64OrHole"
2568 #endif // V8_ENABLE_EXPERIMENTAL_UNDEFINED_DOUBLE
2569  ),
2570  Arguments{{reference.heap_reference()}, {}});
2571  } else if (auto struct_type = referenced_type->StructSupertype()) {
2572  StackRange result_range = assembler().TopRange(0);
2573  for (const Field& field : (*struct_type)->fields()) {
2574  StackScope scope(this);
2575  const std::string& fieldname = field.name_and_type.name;
2576  VisitResult field_value = scope.Yield(GenerateFetchFromLocation(
2577  GenerateFieldAccess(reference, fieldname)));
2578  result_range.Extend(field_value.stack_range());
2579  }
2580  return VisitResult(referenced_type, result_range);
2581  } else {
2582  GenerateCopy(reference.heap_reference());
2583  FieldSynchronization sync = reference.heap_reference_synchronization();
2584  assembler().Emit(LoadReferenceInstruction{referenced_type, sync});
2585  DCHECK_EQ(1, LoweredSlotCount(referenced_type));
2586  return VisitResult(referenced_type, assembler().TopRange(1));
2587  }
2588  } else if (reference.IsBitFieldAccess()) {
2589  // First fetch the bitfield struct, then get the bits out of it.
2590  VisitResult bit_field_struct =
2591  GenerateFetchFromLocation(reference.bit_field_struct_location());
2592  assembler().Emit(LoadBitFieldInstruction{bit_field_struct.type(),
2593  reference.bit_field()});
2594  return VisitResult(*reference.ReferencedType(), assembler().TopRange(1));
2595  } else {
2596  if (reference.IsHeapSlice()) {
2597  ReportError(
2598  "fetching a value directly from an indexed field isn't allowed");
2599  }
2600  DCHECK(reference.IsCallAccess());
2601  return GenerateCall(reference.eval_function(),
2602  Arguments{reference.call_arguments(), {}});
2603  }
2604 }
2605 
2606 void ImplementationVisitor::GenerateAssignToLocation(
2607  const LocationReference& reference, const VisitResult& assignment_value) {
2608  if (reference.IsCallAccess()) {
2609  Arguments arguments{reference.call_arguments(), {}};
2610  arguments.parameters.push_back(assignment_value);
2611  GenerateCall(reference.assign_function(), arguments);
2612  } else if (reference.IsVariableAccess()) {
2613  VisitResult variable = reference.variable();
2614  VisitResult converted_value =
2615  GenerateImplicitConvert(variable.type(), assignment_value);
2616  assembler().Poke(variable.stack_range(), converted_value.stack_range(),
2617  variable.type());
2618 
2619  // Local variables are detected by the existence of a binding. Assignment
2620  // to local variables is recorded to support lint errors.
2621  if (reference.binding()) {
2622  (*reference.binding())->SetWritten();
2623  }
2624  } else if (reference.IsHeapSlice()) {
2625  ReportError("assigning a value directly to an indexed field isn't allowed");
2626  } else if (reference.IsHeapReference()) {
2627  const Type* referenced_type = *reference.ReferencedType();
2628  if (reference.IsConst()) {
2629  Error("cannot assign to const value of type ", *referenced_type).Throw();
2630  }
2631  if (referenced_type == TypeOracle::GetFloat64OrUndefinedOrHoleType()) {
2632  GenerateCall(
2633  QualifiedName({TORQUE_INTERNAL_NAMESPACE_STRING},
2634 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_EXPERIMENTAL_UNDEFINED_DOUBLE
2635  "StoreFloat64OrUndefinedOrHole"
2636 #else
2637  "StoreFloat64OrHole"
2638 #endif // V8_ENABLE_EXPERIMENTAL_UNDEFINED_DOUBLE
2639  ),
2640  Arguments{{reference.heap_reference(), assignment_value}, {}});
2641  } else if (auto struct_type = referenced_type->StructSupertype()) {
2642  if (!assignment_value.type()->IsSubtypeOf(referenced_type)) {
2643  ReportError("Cannot assign to ", *referenced_type,
2644  " with value of type ", *assignment_value.type());
2645  }
2646  for (const Field& field : (*struct_type)->fields()) {
2647  const std::string& fieldname = field.name_and_type.name;
2648  // Allow assignment of structs even if they contain const fields.
2649  // Const on struct fields just disallows direct writes to them.
2650  bool ignore_stuct_field_constness = true;
2651  GenerateAssignToLocation(
2652  GenerateFieldAccess(reference, fieldname,
2653  ignore_stuct_field_constness),
2654  ProjectStructField(assignment_value, fieldname));
2655  }
2656  } else {
2657  GenerateCopy(reference.heap_reference());
2658  VisitResult converted_assignment_value =
2659  GenerateImplicitConvert(referenced_type, assignment_value);
2660  if (referenced_type == TypeOracle::GetFloat64Type()) {
2661  VisitResult silenced_float_value = GenerateCall(
2662  "Float64SilenceNaN", Arguments{{assignment_value}, {}});
2663  assembler().Poke(converted_assignment_value.stack_range(),
2664  silenced_float_value.stack_range(), referenced_type);
2665  }
2666  assembler().Emit(StoreReferenceInstruction{referenced_type});
2667  }
2668  } else if (reference.IsBitFieldAccess()) {
2669  // First fetch the bitfield struct, then set the updated bits, then store
2670  // it back to where we found it.
2671  VisitResult bit_field_struct =
2672  GenerateFetchFromLocation(reference.bit_field_struct_location());
2673  VisitResult converted_value =
2674  GenerateImplicitConvert(*reference.ReferencedType(), assignment_value);
2675  VisitResult updated_bit_field_struct =
2676  GenerateSetBitField(bit_field_struct.type(), reference.bit_field(),
2677  bit_field_struct, converted_value);
2678  GenerateAssignToLocation(reference.bit_field_struct_location(),
2679  updated_bit_field_struct);
2680  } else {
2681  DCHECK(reference.IsTemporary());
2682  ReportError("cannot assign to const-bound or temporary ",
2683  reference.temporary_description());
2684  }
2685 }
2686 
2687 VisitResult ImplementationVisitor::GeneratePointerCall(
2688  Expression* callee, const Arguments& arguments, bool is_tailcall) {
2689  StackScope scope(this);
2690  TypeVector parameter_types(arguments.parameters.ComputeTypeVector());
2691  VisitResult callee_result = Visit(callee);
2692  if (!callee_result.type()->IsBuiltinPointerType()) {
2693  std::stringstream stream;
2694  stream << "Expected a function pointer type but found "
2695  << *callee_result.type();
2696  ReportError(stream.str());
2697  }
2698  const BuiltinPointerType* type =
2699  BuiltinPointerType::cast(callee_result.type());
2700 
2701  if (type->parameter_types().size() != parameter_types.size()) {
2702  std::stringstream stream;
2703  stream << "parameter count mismatch calling function pointer with Type: "
2704  << *type << " - expected "
2705  << std::to_string(type->parameter_types().size()) << ", found "
2706  << std::to_string(parameter_types.size());
2707  ReportError(stream.str());
2708  }
2709 
2710  ParameterTypes types{type->parameter_types(), false};
2711  Signature sig;
2712  sig.parameter_types = types;
2713  if (!IsCompatibleSignature(sig, parameter_types, 0)) {
2714  std::stringstream stream;
2715  stream << "parameters do not match function pointer signature. Expected: ("
2716  << type->parameter_types() << ") but got: (" << parameter_types
2717  << ")";
2718  ReportError(stream.str());
2719  }
2720 
2721  callee_result = GenerateCopy(callee_result);
2722  StackRange arg_range = assembler().TopRange(0);
2723  for (size_t current = 0; current < arguments.parameters.size(); ++current) {
2724  const Type* to_type = type->parameter_types()[current];
2725  arg_range.Extend(
2726  GenerateImplicitConvert(to_type, arguments.parameters[current])
2727  .stack_range());
2728  }
2729 
2730  assembler().Emit(
2731  CallBuiltinPointerInstruction{is_tailcall, type, arg_range.Size()});
2732 
2733  if (is_tailcall) {
2734  return VisitResult::NeverResult();
2735  }
2736  DCHECK_EQ(1, LoweredSlotCount(type->return_type()));
2737  return scope.Yield(VisitResult(type->return_type(), assembler().TopRange(1)));
2738 }
2739 
2740 void ImplementationVisitor::AddCallParameter(
2741  Callable* callable, VisitResult parameter, const Type* parameter_type,
2742  std::vector<VisitResult>* converted_arguments, StackRange* argument_range,
2743  std::vector<std::string>* constexpr_arguments, bool inline_macro) {
2744  VisitResult converted;
2745  if ((converted_arguments->size() < callable->signature().implicit_count) &&
2746  parameter.type()->IsTopType()) {
2747  converted = GenerateCopy(parameter);
2748  } else {
2749  converted = GenerateImplicitConvert(parameter_type, parameter);
2750  }
2751  converted_arguments->push_back(converted);
2752  if (!inline_macro) {
2753  if (converted.IsOnStack()) {
2754  argument_range->Extend(converted.stack_range());
2755  } else {
2756  constexpr_arguments->push_back(converted.constexpr_value());
2757  }
2758  }
2759 }
2760 
2761 namespace {
2762 std::pair<std::string, std::string> GetClassInstanceTypeRange(
2763  const ClassType* class_type) {
2764  std::pair<std::string, std::string> result;
2765  if (class_type->InstanceTypeRange()) {
2766  auto instance_type_range = *class_type->InstanceTypeRange();
2767  std::string instance_type_string_first =
2768  "static_cast<InstanceType>(" +
2769  std::to_string(instance_type_range.first) + ")";
2770  std::string instance_type_string_second =
2771  "static_cast<InstanceType>(" +
2772  std::to_string(instance_type_range.second) + ")";
2773  result =
2774  std::make_pair(instance_type_string_first, instance_type_string_second);
2775  } else {
2776  ReportError(
2777  "%Min/MaxInstanceType must take a class type that is either a string "
2778  "or has a generated instance type range");
2779  }
2780  return result;
2781 }
2782 } // namespace
2783 
2784 VisitResult ImplementationVisitor::GenerateCall(
2785  Callable* callable, std::optional<LocationReference> this_reference,
2786  Arguments arguments, const TypeVector& specialization_types,
2787  bool is_tailcall) {
2788  CHECK(callable->Position().source.IsValid());
2789  if (auto stream = CurrentFileStreams::Get()) {
2790  stream->required_builtin_includes.insert(callable->Position().source);
2791  }
2792 
2793  const Type* return_type = callable->signature().return_type;
2794 
2795  if (is_tailcall) {
2796  if (Builtin* builtin = Builtin::DynamicCast(CurrentCallable::Get())) {
2797  const Type* outer_return_type = builtin->signature().return_type;
2798  if (!return_type->IsSubtypeOf(outer_return_type)) {
2799  Error("Cannot tailcall, type of result is ", *return_type,
2800  " but should be a subtype of ", *outer_return_type, ".");
2801  }
2802  } else {
2803  Error("Tail calls are only allowed from builtins");
2804  }
2805  }
2806 
2807  bool inline_macro = callable->ShouldBeInlined(output_type_);
2808  std::vector<VisitResult> implicit_arguments;
2809  for (size_t i = 0; i < callable->signature().implicit_count; ++i) {
2810  std::string implicit_name = callable->signature().parameter_names[i]->value;
2811  std::optional<Binding<LocalValue>*> val =
2812  TryLookupLocalValue(implicit_name);
2813  if (val) {
2814  implicit_arguments.push_back(
2815  GenerateFetchFromLocation((*val)->GetLocationReference(*val)));
2816  } else {
2817  VisitResult unititialized = VisitResult::TopTypeResult(
2818  "implicit parameter '" + implicit_name +
2819  "' is not defined when invoking " + callable->ReadableName() +
2820  " at " + PositionAsString(CurrentSourcePosition::Get()),
2821  callable->signature().parameter_types.types[i]);
2822  implicit_arguments.push_back(unititialized);
2823  }
2824  const Type* type = implicit_arguments.back().type();
2825  if (const TopType* top_type = TopType::DynamicCast(type)) {
2826  if (!callable->IsMacro() || callable->IsExternal()) {
2827  ReportError(
2828  "unititialized implicit parameters can only be passed to "
2829  "Torque-defined macros: the ",
2830  top_type->reason());
2831  }
2832  inline_macro = true;
2833  }
2834  }
2835 
2836  std::vector<VisitResult> converted_arguments;
2837  StackRange argument_range = assembler().TopRange(0);
2838  std::vector<std::string> constexpr_arguments;
2839 
2840  size_t current = 0;
2841  for (; current < callable->signature().implicit_count; ++current) {
2842  AddCallParameter(callable, implicit_arguments[current],
2843  callable->signature().parameter_types.types[current],
2844  &converted_arguments, &argument_range,
2845  &constexpr_arguments, inline_macro);
2846  }
2847 
2848  if (this_reference) {
2849  DCHECK(callable->IsMethod());
2850  Method* method = Method::cast(callable);
2851  // By now, the this reference should either be a variable, a temporary or
2852  // a Slice. In either case the fetch of the VisitResult should succeed.
2853  VisitResult this_value = this_reference->GetVisitResult();
2854  if (inline_macro) {
2855  if (!this_value.type()->IsSubtypeOf(method->aggregate_type())) {
2856  ReportError("this parameter must be a subtype of ",
2857  *method->aggregate_type(), " but it is of type ",
2858  *this_value.type());
2859  }
2860  } else {
2861  AddCallParameter(callable, this_value, method->aggregate_type(),
2862  &converted_arguments, &argument_range,
2863  &constexpr_arguments, inline_macro);
2864  }
2865  ++current;
2866  }
2867 
2868  for (const auto& arg : arguments.parameters) {
2869  const Type* to_type = (current >= callable->signature().types().size())
2870  ? TypeOracle::GetObjectType()
2871  : callable->signature().types()[current++];
2872  AddCallParameter(callable, arg, to_type, &converted_arguments,
2873  &argument_range, &constexpr_arguments, inline_macro);
2874  }
2875 
2876  size_t label_count = callable->signature().labels.size();
2877  if (label_count != arguments.labels.size()) {
2878  std::stringstream s;
2879  s << "unexpected number of otherwise labels for "
2880  << callable->ReadableName() << " (expected "
2881  << std::to_string(label_count) << " found "
2882  << std::to_string(arguments.labels.size()) << ")";
2883  ReportError(s.str());
2884  }
2885 
2886  if (callable->IsTransitioning()) {
2887  if (!CurrentCallable::Get()->IsTransitioning()) {
2888  std::stringstream s;
2889  s << *CurrentCallable::Get()
2890  << " isn't marked transitioning but calls the transitioning "
2891  << *callable;
2892  ReportError(s.str());
2893  }
2894  }
2895 
2896  if (auto* builtin = Builtin::DynamicCast(callable)) {
2897  std::optional<Block*> catch_block = GetCatchBlock();
2898  assembler().Emit(CallBuiltinInstruction{
2899  is_tailcall, builtin, argument_range.Size(), catch_block});
2900  GenerateCatchBlock(catch_block);
2901  if (is_tailcall) {
2902  return VisitResult::NeverResult();
2903  } else if (return_type->IsNever()) {
2904  assembler().Emit(AbortInstruction{AbortInstruction::Kind::kUnreachable});
2905  return VisitResult::NeverResult();
2906  } else {
2907  size_t slot_count = LoweredSlotCount(return_type);
2908  if (builtin->IsStub()) {
2909  if (slot_count < 1 || slot_count > 2) {
2910  ReportError(
2911  "Builtin with stub linkage is expected to return one or two "
2912  "values but returns ",
2913  slot_count);
2914  }
2915  } else {
2916  if (slot_count != 1) {
2917  ReportError(
2918  "Builtin with JS linkage is expected to return one value but "
2919  "returns ",
2920  slot_count);
2921  }
2922  }
2923  return VisitResult(return_type, assembler().TopRange(slot_count));
2924  }
2925  } else if (auto* macro = Macro::DynamicCast(callable)) {
2926  if (is_tailcall) {
2927  ReportError("can't tail call a macro");
2928  }
2929 
2930  macro->SetUsed();
2931 
2932  // If we're currently generating a C++ macro and it's calling another macro,
2933  // then we need to make sure that we also generate C++ code for the called
2934  // macro within the same -inl.inc file.
2935  if ((output_type_ == OutputType::kCC ||
2936  output_type_ == OutputType::kCCDebug) &&
2937  !inline_macro) {
2938  if (auto* torque_macro = TorqueMacro::DynamicCast(macro)) {
2939  auto* streams = CurrentFileStreams::Get();
2940  SourceId file = streams ? streams->file : SourceId::Invalid();
2941  GlobalContext::EnsureInCCOutputList(torque_macro, file);
2942  }
2943  }
2944 
2945  // TODO(torque-builder): Consider a function builder here.
2946  if (return_type->IsConstexpr()) {
2947  DCHECK_EQ(0, arguments.labels.size());
2948  std::stringstream result;
2949  result << "(";
2950  bool first = true;
2951  switch (output_type_) {
2952  case OutputType::kCSA: {
2953  if (auto* extern_macro = ExternMacro::DynamicCast(macro)) {
2954  result << extern_macro->external_assembler_name() << "(state_)."
2955  << extern_macro->ExternalName() << "(";
2956  } else {
2957  result << macro->ExternalName() << "(state_";
2958  first = false;
2959  }
2960  break;
2961  }
2962  case OutputType::kCC: {
2963  auto* extern_macro = ExternMacro::DynamicCast(macro);
2964  CHECK_NOT_NULL(extern_macro);
2965  result << extern_macro->CCName() << "(";
2966  break;
2967  }
2968  case OutputType::kCCDebug: {
2969  auto* extern_macro = ExternMacro::DynamicCast(macro);
2970  CHECK_NOT_NULL(extern_macro);
2971  result << extern_macro->CCDebugName() << "(accessor";
2972  first = false;
2973  break;
2974  }
2975  }
2976  for (const VisitResult& arg : converted_arguments) {
2977  DCHECK(!arg.IsOnStack());
2978  if (!first) {
2979  result << ", ";
2980  }
2981  first = false;
2982  result << arg.constexpr_value();
2983  }
2984  result << "))";
2985  return VisitResult(return_type, result.str());
2986  } else if (inline_macro) {
2987  std::vector<Block*> label_blocks;
2988  label_blocks.reserve(arguments.labels.size());
2989  for (Binding<LocalLabel>* label : arguments.labels) {
2990  label_blocks.push_back(label->block);
2991  }
2992  return InlineMacro(macro, this_reference, converted_arguments,
2993  std::move(label_blocks));
2994  } else if (arguments.labels.empty() &&
2995  return_type != TypeOracle::GetNeverType()) {
2996  std::optional<Block*> catch_block = GetCatchBlock();
2997  assembler().Emit(CallCsaMacroInstruction{
2998  macro, std::move(constexpr_arguments), catch_block});
2999  GenerateCatchBlock(catch_block);
3000  size_t return_slot_count = LoweredSlotCount(return_type);
3001  return VisitResult(return_type, assembler().TopRange(return_slot_count));
3002  } else {
3003  std::optional<Block*> return_continuation;
3004  if (return_type != TypeOracle::GetNeverType()) {
3005  return_continuation = assembler().NewBlock();
3006  }
3007 
3008  std::vector<Block*> label_blocks;
3009 
3010  for (size_t i = 0; i < label_count; ++i) {
3011  label_blocks.push_back(assembler().NewBlock());
3012  }
3013  std::optional<Block*> catch_block = GetCatchBlock();
3014  assembler().Emit(CallCsaMacroAndBranchInstruction{
3015  macro, constexpr_arguments, return_continuation, label_blocks,
3016  catch_block});
3017  GenerateCatchBlock(catch_block);
3018 
3019  for (size_t i = 0; i < label_count; ++i) {
3020  Binding<LocalLabel>* label = arguments.labels[i];
3021  size_t callee_label_parameters =
3022  callable->signature().labels[i].types.size();
3023  if (label->parameter_types.size() != callee_label_parameters) {
3024  std::stringstream s;
3025  s << "label " << label->name()
3026  << " doesn't have the right number of parameters (found "
3027  << std::to_string(label->parameter_types.size()) << " expected "
3028  << std::to_string(callee_label_parameters) << ")";
3029  ReportError(s.str());
3030  }
3031  assembler().Bind(label_blocks[i]);
3032  assembler().Goto(
3033  label->block,
3034  LowerParameterTypes(callable->signature().labels[i].types).size());
3035 
3036  size_t j = 0;
3037  for (auto t : callable->signature().labels[i].types) {
3038  const Type* parameter_type = label->parameter_types[j];
3039  if (!t->IsSubtypeOf(parameter_type)) {
3040  ReportError("mismatch of label parameters (label expects ",
3041  *parameter_type, " but macro produces ", *t,
3042  " for parameter ", i + 1, ")");
3043  }
3044  j++;
3045  }
3046  }
3047 
3048  if (return_continuation) {
3049  assembler().Bind(*return_continuation);
3050  size_t return_slot_count = LoweredSlotCount(return_type);
3051  return VisitResult(return_type,
3052  assembler().TopRange(return_slot_count));
3053  } else {
3054  return VisitResult::NeverResult();
3055  }
3056  }
3057  } else if (auto* runtime_function = RuntimeFunction::DynamicCast(callable)) {
3058  std::optional<Block*> catch_block = GetCatchBlock();
3059  assembler().Emit(CallRuntimeInstruction{
3060  is_tailcall, runtime_function, argument_range.Size(), catch_block});
3061  GenerateCatchBlock(catch_block);
3062  if (is_tailcall || return_type == TypeOracle::GetNeverType()) {
3063  return VisitResult::NeverResult();
3064  } else {
3065  size_t slot_count = LoweredSlotCount(return_type);
3066  DCHECK_LE(slot_count, 1);
3067  // TODO(turbofan): Actually, runtime functions have to return a value, so
3068  // we should assert slot_count == 1 here.
3069  return VisitResult(return_type, assembler().TopRange(slot_count));
3070  }
3071  } else if (auto* intrinsic = Intrinsic::DynamicCast(callable)) {
3072  if (intrinsic->ExternalName() == "%SizeOf") {
3073  if (specialization_types.size() != 1) {
3074  ReportError("%SizeOf must take a single type parameter");
3075  }
3076  const Type* type = specialization_types[0];
3077  std::string size_string;
3078  if (std::optional<std::tuple<size_t, std::string>> size = SizeOf(type)) {
3079  size_string = std::get<1>(*size);
3080  } else {
3081  Error("size of ", *type, " is not known.");
3082  }
3083  return VisitResult(return_type, size_string);
3084  } else if (intrinsic->ExternalName() == "%ClassHasMapConstant") {
3085  const Type* type = specialization_types[0];
3086  const ClassType* class_type = ClassType::DynamicCast(type);
3087  if (!class_type) {
3088  ReportError("%ClassHasMapConstant must take a class type parameter");
3089  }
3090  // If the class isn't actually used as the parameter to a TNode,
3091  // then we can't rely on the class existing in C++ or being of the same
3092  // type (e.g. it could be a template), so don't use the template CSA
3093  // machinery for accessing the class' map.
3094  if (class_type->name() != class_type->GetGeneratedTNodeTypeName()) {
3095  return VisitResult(return_type, std::string("false"));
3096  } else {
3097  return VisitResult(
3098  return_type,
3099  std::string("CodeStubAssembler(state_).ClassHasMapConstant<") +
3100  class_type->name() + ">()");
3101  }
3102  } else if (intrinsic->ExternalName() == "%MinInstanceType") {
3103  if (specialization_types.size() != 1) {
3104  ReportError("%MinInstanceType must take a single type parameter");
3105  }
3106  const Type* type = specialization_types[0];
3107  const ClassType* class_type = ClassType::DynamicCast(type);
3108  if (!class_type) {
3109  ReportError("%MinInstanceType must take a class type parameter");
3110  }
3111  std::pair<std::string, std::string> instance_types =
3112  GetClassInstanceTypeRange(class_type);
3113  return VisitResult(return_type, instance_types.first);
3114  } else if (intrinsic->ExternalName() == "%MaxInstanceType") {
3115  if (specialization_types.size() != 1) {
3116  ReportError("%MaxInstanceType must take a single type parameter");
3117  }
3118  const Type* type = specialization_types[0];
3119  const ClassType* class_type = ClassType::DynamicCast(type);
3120  if (!class_type) {
3121  ReportError("%MaxInstanceType must take a class type parameter");
3122  }
3123  std::pair<std::string, std::string> instance_types =
3124  GetClassInstanceTypeRange(class_type);
3125  return VisitResult(return_type, instance_types.second);
3126  } else if (intrinsic->ExternalName() == "%RawConstexprCast") {
3127  if (intrinsic->signature().parameter_types.types.size() != 1 ||
3128  constexpr_arguments.size() != 1) {
3129  ReportError(
3130  "%RawConstexprCast must take a single parameter with constexpr "
3131  "type");
3132  }
3133  if (!return_type->IsConstexpr()) {
3134  std::stringstream s;
3135  s << *return_type
3136  << " return type for %RawConstexprCast is not constexpr";
3137  ReportError(s.str());
3138  }
3139  std::stringstream result;
3140  result << "static_cast<" << return_type->GetGeneratedTypeName() << ">(";
3141  result << constexpr_arguments[0];
3142  result << ")";
3143  return VisitResult(return_type, result.str());
3144  } else if (intrinsic->ExternalName() == "%IndexedFieldLength") {
3145  const Type* type = specialization_types[0];
3146  const ClassType* class_type = ClassType::DynamicCast(type);
3147  if (!class_type) {
3148  ReportError("%IndexedFieldLength must take a class type parameter");
3149  }
3150  const Field& field =
3151  class_type->LookupField(StringLiteralUnquote(constexpr_arguments[0]));
3152  return GenerateArrayLength(VisitResult(type, argument_range), field);
3153  } else if (intrinsic->ExternalName() == "%MakeLazy") {
3154  if (specialization_types[0]->IsStructType()) {
3155  ReportError("%MakeLazy can't use macros that return structs");
3156  }
3157  std::string getter_name = StringLiteralUnquote(constexpr_arguments[0]);
3158 
3159  // Normally the parser would split namespace names for us, but we
3160  // sidestepped it by putting the macro name in a string literal.
3161  QualifiedName qualified_getter_name = QualifiedName::Parse(getter_name);
3162 
3163  // converted_arguments contains all of the arguments to %MakeLazy. We're
3164  // looking for a function that takes all but the first.
3165  Arguments arguments_to_getter;
3166  arguments_to_getter.parameters.insert(
3167  arguments_to_getter.parameters.begin(),
3168  converted_arguments.begin() + 1, converted_arguments.end());
3169 
3170  Callable* callable_macro = LookupCallable(
3171  qualified_getter_name, Declarations::Lookup(qualified_getter_name),
3172  arguments_to_getter, {});
3173  Macro* getter = Macro::DynamicCast(callable_macro);
3174  if (!getter || getter->IsMethod()) {
3175  ReportError(
3176  "%MakeLazy expects a macro, not builtin or other type of callable");
3177  }
3178  if (!getter->signature().labels.empty()) {
3179  ReportError("%MakeLazy requires a macro with no labels");
3180  }
3181  if (!getter->signature().return_type->IsSubtypeOf(
3182  specialization_types[0])) {
3183  ReportError("%MakeLazy expected return type ", *specialization_types[0],
3184  " but found ", *getter->signature().return_type);
3185  }
3186  if (getter->signature().implicit_count > 0) {
3187  ReportError("Implicit parameters are not yet supported in %MakeLazy");
3188  }
3189 
3190  getter->SetUsed(); // Prevent warnings about unused macros.
3191 
3192  // Now that we've looked up the getter macro, we have to convert the
3193  // arguments again, so that, for example, constexpr arguments can be
3194  // coerced to non-constexpr types and put on the stack.
3195 
3196  std::vector<VisitResult> converted_arguments_for_getter;
3197  StackRange argument_range_for_getter = assembler().TopRange(0);
3198  std::vector<std::string> constexpr_arguments_for_getter;
3199 
3200  size_t arg_count = 0;
3201  for (const auto& arg : arguments_to_getter.parameters) {
3202  DCHECK_LT(arg_count, getter->signature().types().size());
3203  const Type* to_type = getter->signature().types()[arg_count++];
3204  AddCallParameter(getter, arg, to_type, &converted_arguments_for_getter,
3205  &argument_range_for_getter,
3206  &constexpr_arguments_for_getter,
3207  /*inline_macro=*/false);
3208  }
3209 
3210  // Now that the arguments are prepared, emit the instruction that consumes
3211  // them.
3212  assembler().Emit(MakeLazyNodeInstruction{
3213  getter, return_type, std::move(constexpr_arguments_for_getter)});
3214  return VisitResult(return_type, assembler().TopRange(1));
3215  } else if (intrinsic->ExternalName() == "%FieldSlice") {
3216  const Type* type = specialization_types[0];
3217  const ClassType* class_type = ClassType::DynamicCast(type);
3218  if (!class_type) {
3219  ReportError("The first type parameter to %FieldSlice must be a class");
3220  }
3221  const Field& field =
3222  class_type->LookupField(StringLiteralUnquote(constexpr_arguments[0]));
3223  const Type* expected_slice_type =
3224  field.const_qualified
3225  ? TypeOracle::GetConstSliceType(field.name_and_type.type)
3226  : TypeOracle::GetMutableSliceType(field.name_and_type.type);
3227  const Type* declared_slice_type = specialization_types[1];
3228  if (expected_slice_type != declared_slice_type) {
3229  Error(
3230  "The second type parameter to %FieldSlice must be the precise "
3231  "slice type for the named field");
3232  }
3233  LocationReference ref = GenerateFieldReference(
3234  VisitResult(type, argument_range), field, class_type,
3235  /*treat_optional_as_indexed=*/true);
3236  if (!ref.IsHeapSlice()) {
3237  ReportError("%FieldSlice expected an indexed or optional field");
3238  }
3239  return ref.heap_slice();
3240  } else {
3241  assembler().Emit(CallIntrinsicInstruction{intrinsic, specialization_types,
3242  constexpr_arguments});
3243  size_t return_slot_count =
3244  LoweredSlotCount(intrinsic->signature().return_type);
3245  return VisitResult(return_type, assembler().TopRange(return_slot_count));
3246  }
3247  } else {
3248  UNREACHABLE();
3249  }
3250 }
3251 
3252 VisitResult ImplementationVisitor::GenerateCall(
3253  const QualifiedName& callable_name, Arguments arguments,
3254  const TypeVector& specialization_types, bool is_tailcall) {
3255  Callable* callable =
3256  LookupCallable(callable_name, Declarations::Lookup(callable_name),
3257  arguments, specialization_types);
3258  return GenerateCall(callable, std::nullopt, arguments, specialization_types,
3259  is_tailcall);
3260 }
3261 
3262 VisitResult ImplementationVisitor::Visit(CallExpression* expr,
3263  bool is_tailcall) {
3264  StackScope scope(this);
3265 
3266  if (expr->callee->name->value == "&" && expr->arguments.size() == 1) {
3267  if (auto* loc_expr = LocationExpression::DynamicCast(expr->arguments[0])) {
3268  LocationReference ref = GetLocationReference(loc_expr);
3269  if (ref.IsHeapReference()) return scope.Yield(ref.heap_reference());
3270  if (ref.IsHeapSlice()) return scope.Yield(ref.heap_slice());
3271  }
3272  ReportError("Unable to create a heap reference.");
3273  }
3274 
3275  Arguments arguments;
3276  QualifiedName name = QualifiedName(expr->callee->namespace_qualification,
3277  expr->callee->name->value);
3278  TypeVector specialization_types =
3279  TypeVisitor::ComputeTypeVector(expr->callee->generic_arguments);
3280  bool has_template_arguments = !specialization_types.empty();
3281  for (Expression* arg : expr->arguments)
3282  arguments.parameters.push_back(Visit(arg));
3283  arguments.labels = LabelsFromIdentifiers(expr->labels);
3284  if (!has_template_arguments && name.namespace_qualification.empty() &&
3285  TryLookupLocalValue(name.name)) {
3286  return scope.Yield(
3287  GeneratePointerCall(expr->callee, arguments, is_tailcall));
3288  } else {
3289  if (GlobalContext::collect_language_server_data()) {
3290  Callable* callable = LookupCallable(name, Declarations::Lookup(name),
3291  arguments, specialization_types);
3292  LanguageServerData::AddDefinition(expr->callee->name->pos,
3293  callable->IdentifierPosition());
3294  }
3295  if (GlobalContext::collect_kythe_data()) {
3296  Callable* callable = LookupCallable(name, Declarations::Lookup(name),
3297  arguments, specialization_types);
3298  Callable* caller = CurrentCallable::Get();
3299  KytheData::AddCall(caller, expr->callee->name->pos, callable);
3300  }
3301  if (expr->callee->name->value == "!" && arguments.parameters.size() == 1) {
3302  PropagateBitfieldMark(expr->arguments[0], expr);
3303  }
3304  if (expr->callee->name->value == "==" && arguments.parameters.size() == 2) {
3305  if (arguments.parameters[0].type()->IsConstexpr()) {
3306  PropagateBitfieldMark(expr->arguments[1], expr);
3307  } else if (arguments.parameters[1].type()->IsConstexpr()) {
3308  PropagateBitfieldMark(expr->arguments[0], expr);
3309  }
3310  }
3311  return scope.Yield(
3312  GenerateCall(name, arguments, specialization_types, is_tailcall));
3313  }
3314 }
3315 
3316 VisitResult ImplementationVisitor::Visit(CallMethodExpression* expr) {
3317  StackScope scope(this);
3318  Arguments arguments;
3319  std::string method_name = expr->method->name->value;
3320  TypeVector specialization_types =
3321  TypeVisitor::ComputeTypeVector(expr->method->generic_arguments);
3322  LocationReference target = GetLocationReference(expr->target);
3323  if (!target.IsVariableAccess()) {
3324  VisitResult result = GenerateFetchFromLocation(target);
3325  target = LocationReference::Temporary(result, "this parameter");
3326  }
3327  const AggregateType* target_type =
3328  (*target.ReferencedType())->AggregateSupertype().value_or(nullptr);
3329  if (!target_type) {
3330  ReportError("target of method call not a struct or class type");
3331  }
3332  for (Expression* arg : expr->arguments) {
3333  arguments.parameters.push_back(Visit(arg));
3334  }
3335  arguments.labels = LabelsFromIdentifiers(expr->labels);
3336  TypeVector argument_types = arguments.parameters.ComputeTypeVector();
3337  DCHECK_EQ(expr->method->namespace_qualification.size(), 0);
3338  QualifiedName qualified_name = QualifiedName(method_name);
3339  Callable* callable = LookupMethod(method_name, target_type, arguments, {});
3340  if (GlobalContext::collect_language_server_data()) {
3341  LanguageServerData::AddDefinition(expr->method->name->pos,
3342  callable->IdentifierPosition());
3343  }
3344  if (GlobalContext::collect_kythe_data()) {
3345  Callable* caller = CurrentCallable::Get();
3346  KytheData::AddCall(caller, expr->method->name->pos, callable);
3347  }
3348  return scope.Yield(GenerateCall(callable, target, arguments, {}, false));
3349 }
3350 
3351 VisitResult ImplementationVisitor::Visit(IntrinsicCallExpression* expr) {
3352  StackScope scope(this);
3353  Arguments arguments;
3354  TypeVector specialization_types =
3355  TypeVisitor::ComputeTypeVector(expr->generic_arguments);
3356  for (Expression* arg : expr->arguments)
3357  arguments.parameters.push_back(Visit(arg));
3358  return scope.Yield(
3359  GenerateCall(expr->name->value, arguments, specialization_types, false));
3360 }
3361 
3362 void ImplementationVisitor::GenerateBranch(const VisitResult& condition,
3363  Block* true_block,
3364  Block* false_block) {
3365  DCHECK_EQ(condition,
3366  VisitResult(TypeOracle::GetBoolType(), assembler().TopRange(1)));
3367  assembler().Branch(true_block, false_block);
3368 }
3369 
3370 VisitResult ImplementationVisitor::GenerateBoolConstant(bool constant) {
3371  return GenerateImplicitConvert(TypeOracle::GetBoolType(),
3372  VisitResult(TypeOracle::GetConstexprBoolType(),
3373  constant ? "true" : "false"));
3374 }
3375 
3376 void ImplementationVisitor::GenerateExpressionBranch(Expression* expression,
3377  Block* true_block,
3378  Block* false_block) {
3379  StackScope stack_scope(this);
3380  VisitResult expression_result = this->Visit(expression);
3381  expression_result = stack_scope.Yield(
3382  GenerateImplicitConvert(TypeOracle::GetBoolType(), expression_result));
3383  GenerateBranch(expression_result, true_block, false_block);
3384 }
3385 
3386 VisitResult ImplementationVisitor::GenerateImplicitConvert(
3387  const Type* destination_type, VisitResult source) {
3388  StackScope scope(this);
3389  if (source.type() == TypeOracle::GetNeverType()) {
3390  ReportError("it is not allowed to use a value of type never");
3391  }
3392 
3393  if (destination_type == source.type()) {
3394  return scope.Yield(GenerateCopy(source));
3395  }
3396 
3397  if (auto from = TypeOracle::ImplicitlyConvertableFrom(destination_type,
3398  source.type())) {
3399  return scope.Yield(GenerateCall(kFromConstexprMacroName,
3400  Arguments{{source}, {}},
3401  {destination_type, *from}, false));
3402  } else if (IsAssignableFrom(destination_type, source.type())) {
3403  source.SetType(destination_type);
3404  return scope.Yield(GenerateCopy(source));
3405  } else {
3406  std::stringstream s;
3407  if (const TopType* top_type = TopType::DynamicCast(source.type())) {
3408  s << "undefined expression of type " << *destination_type << ": the "
3409  << top_type->reason();
3410  } else {
3411  s << "cannot use expression of type " << *source.type()
3412  << " as a value of type " << *destination_type;
3413  }
3414  ReportError(s.str());
3415  }
3416 }
3417 
3418 StackRange ImplementationVisitor::GenerateLabelGoto(
3419  LocalLabel* label, std::optional<StackRange> arguments) {
3420  return assembler().Goto(label->block, arguments ? arguments->Size() : 0);
3421 }
3422 
3423 std::vector<Binding<LocalLabel>*> ImplementationVisitor::LabelsFromIdentifiers(
3424  const std::vector<Identifier*>& names) {
3425  std::vector<Binding<LocalLabel>*> result;
3426  result.reserve(names.size());
3427  for (const auto& name : names) {
3428  Binding<LocalLabel>* label = LookupLabel(name->value);
3429  result.push_back(label);
3430 
3431  // Link up labels in "otherwise" part of the call expression with
3432  // either the label in the signature of the calling macro or the label
3433  // block ofa surrounding "try".
3434  if (GlobalContext::collect_language_server_data()) {
3435  LanguageServerData::AddDefinition(name->pos,
3436  label->declaration_position());
3437  }
3438  // TODO(v8:12261): Might have to track KytheData here.
3439  }
3440  return result;
3441 }
3442 
3443 StackRange ImplementationVisitor::LowerParameter(
3444  const Type* type, const std::string& parameter_name,
3445  Stack<std::string>* lowered_parameters) {
3446  if (std::optional<const StructType*> struct_type = type->StructSupertype()) {
3447  StackRange range = lowered_parameters->TopRange(0);
3448  for (auto& field : (*struct_type)->fields()) {
3449  StackRange parameter_range = LowerParameter(
3450  field.name_and_type.type,
3451  parameter_name + "." + field.name_and_type.name, lowered_parameters);
3452  range.Extend(parameter_range);
3453  }
3454  return range;
3455  } else {
3456  lowered_parameters->Push(parameter_name);
3457  return lowered_parameters->TopRange(1);
3458  }
3459 }
3460 
3461 void ImplementationVisitor::LowerLabelParameter(
3462  const Type* type, const std::string& parameter_name,
3463  std::vector<std::string>* lowered_parameters) {
3464  if (std::optional<const StructType*> struct_type = type->StructSupertype()) {
3465  for (auto& field : (*struct_type)->fields()) {
3466  LowerLabelParameter(
3467  field.name_and_type.type,
3468  "&((*" + parameter_name + ")." + field.name_and_type.name + ")",
3469  lowered_parameters);
3470  }
3471  } else {
3472  lowered_parameters->push_back(parameter_name);
3473  }
3474 }

3490 
3491 bool IsCompatibleSignature(const Signature& sig, const TypeVector& types,
3492  size_t label_count) {
3493  auto i = sig.parameter_types.types.begin() + sig.implicit_count;
3494  if ((sig.parameter_types.types.size() - sig.implicit_count) > types.size())
3495  return false;
3496  if (sig.labels.size() != label_count) return false;
3497  for (auto current : types) {
3498  if (i == sig.parameter_types.types.end()) {
3499  if (!sig.parameter_types.var_args) return false;
3500  if (!IsAssignableFrom(TypeOracle::GetObjectType(), current)) return false;
3501  } else {
3502  if (!IsAssignableFrom(*i++, current)) return false;
3503  }
3504  }
3505  return true;
3506 }
3507 
3508 std::optional<Block*> ImplementationVisitor::GetCatchBlock() {
3509  std::optional<Block*> catch_block;
3510  if (TryLookupLabel(kCatchLabelName)) {
3511  catch_block = assembler().NewBlock(std::nullopt, true);
3512  }
3513  return catch_block;
3514 }
3515 
3516 void ImplementationVisitor::GenerateCatchBlock(
3517  std::optional<Block*> catch_block) {
3518  if (catch_block) {
3519  std::optional<Binding<LocalLabel>*> catch_handler =
3520  TryLookupLabel(kCatchLabelName);
3521  // Reset the local scopes to prevent the macro calls below from using the
3522  // current catch handler.
3523  BindingsManagersScope bindings_managers_scope;
3524  if (assembler().CurrentBlockIsComplete()) {
3525  assembler().Bind(*catch_block);
3526  GenerateCall(QualifiedName({TORQUE_INTERNAL_NAMESPACE_STRING},
3527  "GetAndResetPendingMessage"),
3528  Arguments{{}, {}}, {}, false);
3529  assembler().Goto((*catch_handler)->block, 2);
3530  } else {
3531  CfgAssemblerScopedTemporaryBlock temp(&assembler(), *catch_block);
3532  GenerateCall(QualifiedName({TORQUE_INTERNAL_NAMESPACE_STRING},
3533  "GetAndResetPendingMessage"),
3534  Arguments{{}, {}}, {}, false);
3535  assembler().Goto((*catch_handler)->block, 2);
3536  }
3537  }
3538 }
3539 void ImplementationVisitor::VisitAllDeclarables() {
3540  CurrentCallable::Scope current_callable(nullptr);
3541  const std::vector<std::unique_ptr<Declarable>>& all_declarables =
3542  GlobalContext::AllDeclarables();
3543 
3544  // This has to be an index-based loop because all_declarables can be extended
3545  // during the loop.
3546  for (size_t i = 0; i < all_declarables.size(); ++i) {
3547  try {
3548  Visit(all_declarables[i].get());
3549  } catch (TorqueAbortCompilation&) {
3550  // Recover from compile errors here. The error is recorded already.
3551  }
3552  }
3553 
3554  // Do the same for macros which generate C++ code.
3555  output_type_ = OutputType::kCC;
3556  const std::vector<std::pair<TorqueMacro*, SourceId>>& cc_macros =
3557  GlobalContext::AllMacrosForCCOutput();
3558  for (size_t i = 0; i < cc_macros.size(); ++i) {
3559  try {
3560  Visit(static_cast<Declarable*>(cc_macros[i].first), cc_macros[i].second);
3561  } catch (TorqueAbortCompilation&) {
3562  // Recover from compile errors here. The error is recorded already.
3563  }
3564  }
3565 
3566  // Do the same for macros which generate C++ debug code.
3567  // The set of macros is the same as C++ macros.
3568  output_type_ = OutputType::kCCDebug;
3569  const std::vector<std::pair<TorqueMacro*, SourceId>>& cc_debug_macros =
3570  GlobalContext::AllMacrosForCCDebugOutput();
3571  for (size_t i = 0; i < cc_debug_macros.size(); ++i) {
3572  try {
3573  Visit(static_cast<Declarable*>(cc_debug_macros[i].first),
3574  cc_debug_macros[i].second);
3575  } catch (TorqueAbortCompilation&) {
3576  // Recover from compile errors here. The error is recorded already.
3577  }
3578  }
3579 
3580  output_type_ = OutputType::kCSA;
3581 }
3582 
3583 void ImplementationVisitor::Visit(Declarable* declarable,
3584  std::optional<SourceId> file) {
3585  CurrentScope::Scope current_scope(declarable->ParentScope());
3586  CurrentSourcePosition::Scope current_source_position(declarable->Position());
3587  CurrentFileStreams::Scope current_file_streams(
3588  &GlobalContext::GeneratedPerFile(file ? *file
3589  : declarable->Position().source));
3590  if (Callable* callable = Callable::DynamicCast(declarable)) {
3591  if (!callable->ShouldGenerateExternalCode(output_type_))
3592  CurrentFileStreams::Get() = nullptr;
3593  }
3594  switch (declarable->kind()) {
3595  case Declarable::kExternMacro:
3596  return Visit(ExternMacro::cast(declarable));
3597  case Declarable::kTorqueMacro:
3598  return Visit(TorqueMacro::cast(declarable));
3599  case Declarable::kMethod:
3600  return Visit(Method::cast(declarable));
3601  case Declarable::kBuiltin:
3602  return Visit(Builtin::cast(declarable));
3603  case Declarable::kTypeAlias:
3604  return Visit(TypeAlias::cast(declarable));
3605  case Declarable::kNamespaceConstant:
3606  return Visit(NamespaceConstant::cast(declarable));
3607  case Declarable::kRuntimeFunction:
3608  case Declarable::kIntrinsic:
3609  case Declarable::kExternConstant:
3610  case Declarable::kNamespace:
3611  case Declarable::kGenericCallable:
3612  case Declarable::kGenericType:
3613  return;
3614  }
3615 }
3616 
3617 std::string MachineTypeString(const Type* type) {
3618  if (type->IsSubtypeOf(TypeOracle::GetSmiType())) {
3619  return "MachineType::TaggedSigned()";
3620  }
3621  if (type->IsSubtypeOf(TypeOracle::GetHeapObjectType())) {
3622  return "MachineType::TaggedPointer()";
3623  }
3624  if (type->IsSubtypeOf(TypeOracle::GetTaggedType())) {
3625  return "MachineType::AnyTagged()";
3626  }
3627  return "MachineTypeOf<" + type->GetGeneratedTNodeTypeName() + ">::value";
3628 }
3629 
3630 void ImplementationVisitor::GenerateBuiltinDefinitionsAndInterfaceDescriptors(
3631  const std::string& output_directory) {
3632  std::stringstream builtin_definitions;
3633  std::string builtin_definitions_file_name = "builtin-definitions.h";
3634 
3635  // This file contains plain interface descriptor definitions and has to be
3636  // included in the middle of interface-descriptors.h. Thus it is not a normal
3637  // header file and uses the .inc suffix instead of the .h suffix.
3638  std::stringstream interface_descriptors;
3639  std::string interface_descriptors_file_name = "interface-descriptors.inc";
3640  {
3641  IncludeGuardScope builtin_definitions_include_guard(
3642  builtin_definitions, builtin_definitions_file_name);
3643 
3644  builtin_definitions
3645  << "\n"
3646  "#define BUILTIN_LIST_FROM_TORQUE(CPP, TFJ, TFC, TFS, TFH, "
3647  "ASM) "
3648  "\\\n";
3649  for (auto& declarable : GlobalContext::AllDeclarables()) {
3650  Builtin* builtin = Builtin::DynamicCast(declarable.get());
3651  if (!builtin || builtin->IsExternal()) continue;
3652  if (builtin->IsStub()) {
3653  builtin_definitions << "TFC(" << builtin->ExternalName() << ", "
3654  << builtin->ExternalName();
3655  if (!builtin->HasCustomInterfaceDescriptor()) {
3656  std::string descriptor_name = builtin->ExternalName() + "Descriptor";
3657  bool has_context_parameter =
3658  builtin->signature().HasContextParameter();
3659  size_t kFirstNonContextParameter = has_context_parameter ? 1 : 0;
3660  TypeVector return_types = LowerType(builtin->signature().return_type);
3661 
3662  interface_descriptors << "class " << descriptor_name
3663  << " : public StaticCallInterfaceDescriptor<"
3664  << descriptor_name << "> {\n";
3665 
3666  interface_descriptors << " public:\n";
3667 
3668  // Currently, no torque-defined builtins are directly exposed to
3669  // objects inside the sandbox via the code pointer table.
3670  interface_descriptors << " INTERNAL_DESCRIPTOR()\n";
3671 
3672  interface_descriptors << " SANDBOXING_MODE(kSandboxed)\n";
3673 
3674  if (has_context_parameter) {
3675  interface_descriptors << " DEFINE_RESULT_AND_PARAMETERS(";
3676  } else {
3677  interface_descriptors
3678  << " DEFINE_RESULT_AND_PARAMETERS_NO_CONTEXT(";
3679  }
3680  interface_descriptors << return_types.size();
3681  for (size_t i = kFirstNonContextParameter;
3682  i < builtin->parameter_names().size(); ++i) {
3683  Identifier* parameter = builtin->parameter_names()[i];
3684  interface_descriptors << ", k" << CamelifyString(parameter->value);
3685  }
3686  interface_descriptors << ")\n";
3687 
3688  interface_descriptors << " DEFINE_RESULT_AND_PARAMETER_TYPES(";
3689  PrintCommaSeparatedList(interface_descriptors, return_types,
3690  MachineTypeString);
3691  bool is_first = return_types.empty();
3692  for (size_t i = kFirstNonContextParameter;
3693  i < builtin->parameter_names().size(); ++i) {
3694  const Type* type = builtin->signature().parameter_types.types[i];
3695  interface_descriptors << (is_first ? "" : ", ")
3696  << MachineTypeString(type);
3697  is_first = false;
3698  }
3699  interface_descriptors << ")\n";
3700 
3701  interface_descriptors << " DECLARE_DEFAULT_DESCRIPTOR("
3702  << descriptor_name << ")\n";
3703  interface_descriptors << "};\n\n";
3704  }
3705  } else {
3706  builtin_definitions << "TFJ(" << builtin->ExternalName();
3707  if (builtin->IsVarArgsJavaScript()) {
3708  builtin_definitions << ", kDontAdaptArgumentsSentinel";
3709  } else {
3710  DCHECK(builtin->IsFixedArgsJavaScript());
3711  // FixedArg javascript builtins need to offer the parameter
3712  // count.
3713  int parameter_count =
3714  static_cast<int>(builtin->signature().ExplicitCount());
3715  builtin_definitions << ", JSParameterCount(" << parameter_count
3716  << ")";
3717  // And the receiver is explicitly declared.
3718  builtin_definitions << ", kReceiver";
3719  for (size_t i = builtin->signature().implicit_count;
3720  i < builtin->parameter_names().size(); ++i) {
3721  Identifier* parameter = builtin->parameter_names()[i];
3722  builtin_definitions << ", k" << CamelifyString(parameter->value);
3723  }
3724  }
3725  }
3726  builtin_definitions << ") \\\n";
3727  }
3728  builtin_definitions << "\n";
3729 
3730  builtin_definitions
3731  << "#define TORQUE_FUNCTION_POINTER_TYPE_TO_BUILTIN_MAP(V) \\\n";
3732  for (const BuiltinPointerType* type :
3733  TypeOracle::AllBuiltinPointerTypes()) {
3734  Builtin* example_builtin =
3735  Declarations::FindSomeInternalBuiltinWithType(type);
3736  if (!example_builtin) {
3737  CurrentSourcePosition::Scope current_source_position(
3738  SourcePosition{CurrentSourceFile::Get(), LineAndColumn::Invalid(),
3739  LineAndColumn::Invalid()});
3740  ReportError("unable to find any builtin with type \"", *type, "\"");
3741  }
3742  builtin_definitions << " V(" << type->function_pointer_type_id() << ","
3743  << example_builtin->ExternalName() << ")\\\n";
3744  }
3745  builtin_definitions << "\n";
3746  }
3747  WriteFile(output_directory + "/" + builtin_definitions_file_name,
3748  builtin_definitions.str());
3749  WriteFile(output_directory + "/" + interface_descriptors_file_name,
3750  interface_descriptors.str());
3751 }
3752 
3753 namespace {
3754 
3755 enum class FieldSectionType : uint32_t {
3756  kNoSection = 0,
3757  kWeakSection = 1 << 0,
3758  kStrongSection = 2 << 0,
3759  kScalarSection = 3 << 0
3760 };
3761 
3762 bool IsPointerSection(FieldSectionType type) {
3763  return type == FieldSectionType::kWeakSection ||
3764  type == FieldSectionType::kStrongSection;
3765 }
3766 
3767 using FieldSections = base::Flags<FieldSectionType>;
3768 
3769 std::string ToString(FieldSectionType type) {
3770  switch (type) {
3771  case FieldSectionType::kNoSection:
3772  return "NoSection";
3773  case FieldSectionType::kWeakSection:
3774  return "WeakFields";
3775  case FieldSectionType::kStrongSection:
3776  return "StrongFields";
3777  case FieldSectionType::kScalarSection:
3778  return "ScalarFields";
3779  }
3780  UNREACHABLE();
3781 }
3782 
3783 class FieldOffsetsGenerator {
3784  public:
3785  explicit FieldOffsetsGenerator(const ClassType* type) : type_(type) {}
3786 
3787  virtual void WriteField(const Field& f, const std::string& size_string) = 0;
3788  virtual void WriteFieldOffsetGetter(const Field& f) = 0;
3789  virtual void WriteMarker(const std::string& marker) = 0;
3790 
3791  virtual ~FieldOffsetsGenerator() { CHECK(is_finished_); }
3792 
3793  void RecordOffsetFor(const Field& f) {
3794  CHECK(!is_finished_);
3795  UpdateSection(f);
3796 
3797  // Emit kHeaderSize before any indexed field.
3798  if (f.index.has_value() && !header_size_emitted_) {
3799  WriteMarker("kHeaderSize");
3800  header_size_emitted_ = true;
3801  }
3802 
3803  // We don't know statically how much space an indexed field takes, so report
3804  // it as zero.
3805  std::string size_string = "0";
3806  if (!f.index.has_value()) {
3807  size_t field_size;
3808  std::tie(field_size, size_string) = f.GetFieldSizeInformation();
3809  }
3810  if (f.offset.has_value()) {
3811  WriteField(f, size_string);
3812  } else {
3813  WriteFieldOffsetGetter(f);
3814  }
3815  }
3816 
3817  void Finish() {
3818  End(current_section_);
3819  if (!(completed_sections_ & FieldSectionType::kWeakSection)) {
3820  Begin(FieldSectionType::kWeakSection);
3821  End(FieldSectionType::kWeakSection);
3822  }
3823  if (!(completed_sections_ & FieldSectionType::kStrongSection)) {
3824  Begin(FieldSectionType::kStrongSection);
3825  End(FieldSectionType::kStrongSection);
3826  }
3827  is_finished_ = true;
3828 
3829  // In the presence of indexed fields, we already emitted kHeaderSize before
3830  // the indexed field.
3831  if (!type_->IsShape() && !header_size_emitted_) {
3832  WriteMarker("kHeaderSize");
3833  }
3834  if (!type_->IsAbstract() && type_->HasStaticSize()) {
3835  WriteMarker("kSize");
3836  }
3837  }
3838 
3839  protected:
3840  const ClassType* type_;
3841 
3842  private:
3843  FieldSectionType GetSectionFor(const Field& f) {
3844  const Type* field_type = f.name_and_type.type;
3845  if (field_type == TypeOracle::GetVoidType()) {
3846  // Allow void type for marker constants of size zero.
3847  return current_section_;
3848  }
3849  StructType::Classification struct_contents =
3850  StructType::ClassificationFlag::kEmpty;
3851  if (auto field_as_struct = field_type->StructSupertype()) {
3852  struct_contents = (*field_as_struct)->ClassifyContents();
3853  }
3854  if ((struct_contents & StructType::ClassificationFlag::kStrongTagged) &&
3855  (struct_contents & StructType::ClassificationFlag::kWeakTagged)) {
3856  // It's okay for a struct to contain both strong and weak data. We'll just
3857  // treat the whole thing as weak. This is required for DescriptorEntry.
3858  struct_contents &= ~StructType::Classification(
3859  StructType::ClassificationFlag::kStrongTagged);
3860  }
3861  bool struct_contains_tagged_fields =
3862  (struct_contents & StructType::ClassificationFlag::kStrongTagged) ||
3863  (struct_contents & StructType::ClassificationFlag::kWeakTagged);
3864  if (struct_contains_tagged_fields &&
3865  (struct_contents & StructType::ClassificationFlag::kUntagged)) {
3866  // We can't declare what section a struct goes in if it has multiple
3867  // categories of data within.
3868  Error(
3869  "Classes do not support fields which are structs containing both "
3870  "tagged and untagged data.")
3871  .Position(f.pos);
3872  }
3873  if ((field_type->IsSubtypeOf(TypeOracle::GetStrongTaggedType()) ||
3874  struct_contents == StructType::ClassificationFlag::kStrongTagged) &&
3875  !f.custom_weak_marking) {
3876  return FieldSectionType::kStrongSection;
3877  } else if (field_type->IsSubtypeOf(TypeOracle::GetTaggedType()) ||
3878  struct_contains_tagged_fields) {
3879  return FieldSectionType::kWeakSection;
3880  } else {
3881  return FieldSectionType::kScalarSection;
3882  }
3883  }
3884  void UpdateSection(const Field& f) {
3885  FieldSectionType type = GetSectionFor(f);
3886  if (current_section_ == type) return;
3887  if (IsPointerSection(type)) {
3888  if (completed_sections_ & type) {
3889  std::stringstream s;
3890  s << "cannot declare field " << f.name_and_type.name << " in class "
3891  << type_->name() << ", because section " << ToString(type)
3892  << " to which it belongs has already been finished.";
3893  Error(s.str()).Position(f.pos);
3894  }
3895  }
3896  End(current_section_);
3897  current_section_ = type;
3898  Begin(current_section_);
3899  }
3900  void Begin(FieldSectionType type) {
3901  DCHECK(type != FieldSectionType::kNoSection);
3902  if (!IsPointerSection(type)) return;
3903  WriteMarker("kStartOf" + ToString(type) + "Offset");
3904  }
3905  void End(FieldSectionType type) {
3906  if (!IsPointerSection(type)) return;
3907  completed_sections_ |= type;
3908  WriteMarker("kEndOf" + ToString(type) + "Offset");
3909  }
3910 
3911  FieldSectionType current_section_ = FieldSectionType::kNoSection;
3912  FieldSections completed_sections_ = FieldSectionType::kNoSection;
3913  bool is_finished_ = false;
3914  bool header_size_emitted_ = false;
3915 };
3916 
3917 void GenerateClassExport(const ClassType* type, std::ostream& header,
3918  std::ostream& inl_header) {
3919  const ClassType* super = type->GetSuperClass();
3920  std::string parent = "TorqueGenerated" + type->name() + "<" + type->name() +
3921  ", " + super->name() + ">";
3922  header << "class " << type->name() << " : public " << parent << " {\n";
3923  header << " public:\n";
3924  if (type->ShouldGenerateBodyDescriptor()) {
3925  header << " class BodyDescriptor;\n";
3926  }
3927  header << " TQ_OBJECT_CONSTRUCTORS(" << type->name() << ")\n";
3928  header << "};\n\n";
3929  inl_header << "TQ_OBJECT_CONSTRUCTORS_IMPL(" << type->name() << ")\n";
3930 }

3934 void ImplementationVisitor::GenerateVisitorLists(
