3972 
3973 void ImplementationVisitor::GenerateBitFields(
3974  const std::string& output_directory) {
3975  std::stringstream header;
3976  std::string file_name = "bit-fields.h";
3977  {
3978  IncludeGuardScope include_guard(header, file_name);
3979  header << "#include \"src/base/bit-field.h\"\n\n";
3980  NamespaceScope namespaces(header, {"v8", "internal"});
3981 
3982  for (const auto& type : TypeOracle::GetBitFieldStructTypes()) {
3983  bool all_single_bits = true; // Track whether every field is one bit.
3984  header << "// " << type->GetPosition() << "\n";
3985  header << "#define DEFINE_TORQUE_GENERATED_"
3986  << CapifyStringWithUnderscores(type->name()) << "() \\\n";
3987  std::string type_name = type->GetConstexprGeneratedTypeName();
3988  for (const auto& field : type->fields()) {
3989  const char* suffix = field.num_bits == 1 ? "Bit" : "Bits";
3990  all_single_bits = all_single_bits && field.num_bits == 1;
3991  std::string field_type_name =
3992  field.name_and_type.type->GetConstexprGeneratedTypeName();
3993  header << " using " << CamelifyString(field.name_and_type.name)
3994  << suffix << " = base::BitField<" << field_type_name << ", "
3995  << field.offset << ", " << field.num_bits << ", " << type_name
3996  << ">; \\\n";
3997  }
3998 
3999  // If every field is one bit, we can also generate a convenient enum.
4000  if (all_single_bits) {
4001  header << " enum Flag: " << type_name << " { \\\n";
4002  header << " kNone = 0, \\\n";
4003  for (const auto& field : type->fields()) {
4004  header << " k" << CamelifyString(field.name_and_type.name) << " = "
4005  << type_name << "{1} << " << field.offset << ", \\\n";
4006  }
4007  header << " }; \\\n";
4008  header << " using Flags = base::Flags<Flag>; \\\n";
4009  header << " static constexpr int kFlagCount = "
4010  << type->fields().size() << "; \\\n";
4011  }
4012 
4013  header << "\n";
4014  }
4015  }
4016  const std::string output_header_path = output_directory + "/" + file_name;
4017  WriteFile(output_header_path, header.str());
4018 }

4020 namespace {
4021 
4022 class ClassFieldOffsetGenerator : public FieldOffsetsGenerator {
4023  public:
4024  ClassFieldOffsetGenerator(std::ostream& header, std::ostream& inline_header,
4025  const ClassType* type, std::string gen_name,
4026  const ClassType* parent, bool use_templates = true)
4027  : FieldOffsetsGenerator(type),
4028  hdr_(header),
4029  inl_(inline_header),
4030  previous_field_end_(FirstFieldStart(type, parent, use_templates)),
4031  gen_name_(gen_name) {}
4032 
4033  void WriteField(const Field& f, const std::string& size_string) override {
4034  hdr_ << " // " << f.pos << "\n";
4035  std::string field = "k" + CamelifyString(f.name_and_type.name) + "Offset";
4036  std::string field_end = field + "End";
4037  hdr_ << " static constexpr int " << field << " = " << previous_field_end_
4038  << ";\n";
4039  hdr_ << " static constexpr int " << field_end << " = " << field << " + "
4040  << size_string << " - 1;\n";
4041  previous_field_end_ = field_end + " + 1";
4042  }
4043 
4044  void WriteFieldOffsetGetter(const Field& f) override {
4045  // A static constexpr int is more convenient than a getter if the offset is
4046  // known.
4047  DCHECK(!f.offset.has_value());
4048 
4049  std::string function_name = CamelifyString(f.name_and_type.name) + "Offset";
4050 
4051  std::vector<cpp::TemplateParameter> params = {cpp::TemplateParameter("D"),
4052  cpp::TemplateParameter("P")};
4053  cpp::Class owner(std::move(params), gen_name_);
4054 
4055  auto getter = cpp::Function::DefaultGetter("int", &owner, function_name);
4056  getter.PrintDeclaration(hdr_);
4057  getter.PrintDefinition(inl_, [&](std::ostream& stream) {
4058  // Item 1 in a flattened slice is the offset.
4059  stream << " return static_cast<int>(std::get<1>("
4060  << Callable::PrefixNameForCCOutput(type_->GetSliceMacroName(f))
4061  << "(*static_cast<const D*>(this))));\n";
4062  });
4063  }
4064  void WriteMarker(const std::string& marker) override {
4065  hdr_ << " static constexpr int " << marker << " = " << previous_field_end_
4066  << ";\n";
4067  }
4068 
4069  private:
4070  static std::string FirstFieldStart(const ClassType* type,
4071  const ClassType* parent,
4072  bool use_templates = true) {
4073  std::string parent_name = use_templates ? "P" : parent->name();
4074 
4075  if (type->IsLayoutDefinedInCpp()) {
4076  // TODO(leszeks): Hacked in support for some classes (e.g.
4077  // HeapObject) being mirrored by a *Layout class. Remove once
4078  // everything is ported to layout classes.
4079  if (parent_name == "HeapObject" || parent_name == "TrustedObject" ||
4080  parent_name == "Struct") {
4081  parent_name += "Layout";
4082  }
4083 
4084  return "sizeof(" + parent_name + ")";
4085  }
4086 
4087  if (parent && parent->IsShape()) {
4088  return parent_name + "::kSize";
4089  }
4090  return parent_name + "::kHeaderSize";
4091  }
4092 
4093  std::ostream& hdr_;
4094  std::ostream& inl_;
4095  std::string previous_field_end_;
4096  std::string gen_name_;
4097 };

4099 class CppClassGenerator {
4100  public:
4101  CppClassGenerator(const ClassType* type, std::ostream& header,
4102  std::ostream& inl_header, std::ostream& impl)
4103  : type_(type),
4104  super_(type->GetSuperClass()),
4105  name_(type->name()),
4106  gen_name_("TorqueGenerated" + name_),
4107  gen_name_T_(gen_name_ + "<D, P>"),
4108  gen_name_I_(gen_name_ + "<" + name_ + ", " + super_->name() + ">"),
4109  hdr_(header),
4110  inl_(inl_header),
4111  impl_(impl) {}
4112  const std::string template_decl() const {
4113  return "template <class D, class P>";
4114  }
4115 
4116  void GenerateClass();
4117  void GenerateCppObjectDefinitionAsserts();
4118  void GenerateCppObjectLayoutDefinitionAsserts();
4119 
4120  private:
4121  SourcePosition Position();
4122 
4123  void GenerateClassConstructors();
4124 
4125  // Generates getter and setter runtime member functions for the given class
4126  // field. Traverses depth-first through any nested struct fields to generate
4127  // accessors for them also; struct_fields represents the stack of currently
4128  // active struct fields.
4129  void GenerateFieldAccessors(const Field& class_field,
4130  std::vector<const Field*>& struct_fields);
4131  void EmitLoadFieldStatement(std::ostream& stream, const Field& class_field,
4132  std::vector<const Field*>& struct_fields);
4133  void EmitStoreFieldStatement(std::ostream& stream, const Field& class_field,
4134  std::vector<const Field*>& struct_fields);

4136  std::string GetFieldOffsetForAccessor(const Field& f);
4137 
4138  // Gets the C++ type name that should be used in accessors for referring to
4139  // the value of a class field.
4140  std::string GetTypeNameForAccessor(const Field& f);
4141 
4142  bool CanContainHeapObjects(const Type* t);
4143 
4144  const ClassType* type_;
4145  const ClassType* super_;
4146  const std::string name_;
4147  const std::string gen_name_;
4148  const std::string gen_name_T_;
4149  const std::string gen_name_I_;

4151  std::ostream& inl_;
4152  std::ostream& impl_;

4154 
4155 std::optional<std::vector<Field>> GetOrderedUniqueIndexFields(
4156  const ClassType& type) {
4157  std::vector<Field> result;
4158  std::set<std::string> index_names;
4159  for (const Field& field : type.ComputeAllFields()) {
4160  if (field.index) {
4161  auto name_and_type = ExtractSimpleFieldArraySize(type, field.index->expr);
4162  if (!name_and_type) {
4163  return std::nullopt;
4164  }
4165  index_names.insert(name_and_type->name);
4166  }
4167  }
4168 
4169  for (const Field& field : type.ComputeAllFields()) {
4170  if (index_names.count(field.name_and_type.name) != 0) {
4171  result.push_back(field);
4172  }
4173  }
4174 
4175  return result;
4176 }
4177 
4178 void CppClassGenerator::GenerateClass() {
4179  // Is<name>_NonInline(Tagged<HeapObject>)
4180  if (!type_->IsShape()) {
4181  cpp::Function f("Is"s + name_ + "_NonInline");
4182  f.SetDescription("Alias for Is"s + name_ + "() that avoids inlining.");
4183  f.SetExport(true);
4184  f.SetReturnType("bool");
4185  f.AddParameter("Tagged<HeapObject>", "o");
4186 
4187  f.PrintDeclaration(hdr_);
4188  hdr_ << "\n";
4189  f.PrintDefinition(impl_, [&](std::ostream& stream) {
4190  stream << " return Is" << name_ << "(o);\n";
4191  });
4192  }
4193  hdr_ << "// Definition " << Position() << "\n";
4194  hdr_ << template_decl() << "\n";
4195  hdr_ << "class " << gen_name_ << " : public P {\n";
4196  hdr_ << " static_assert(\n"
4197  << " std::is_same_v<" << name_ << ", D>,\n"
4198  << " \"Use this class as direct base for " << name_ << ".\");\n";
4199  hdr_ << " static_assert(\n"
4200  << " std::is_same_v<" << super_->name() << ", P>,\n"
4201  << " \"Pass in " << super_->name()
4202  << " as second template parameter for " << gen_name_ << ".\");\n\n";
4203  hdr_ << " public: \n";
4204  hdr_ << " using Super = P;\n";
4205  hdr_ << " using TorqueGeneratedClass = " << gen_name_ << "<D,P>;\n\n";
4206  if (!type_->ShouldExport() && !type_->IsExtern()) {
4207  hdr_ << " protected: // not extern or @export\n";
4208  }
4209  for (const Field& f : type_->fields()) {
4210  CurrentSourcePosition::Scope scope(f.pos);
4211  std::vector<const Field*> struct_fields;
4212  GenerateFieldAccessors(f, struct_fields);
4213  }
4214  if (!type_->ShouldExport() && !type_->IsExtern()) {
4215  hdr_ << " public:\n";
4216  }
4217 
4218  std::vector<cpp::TemplateParameter> templateArgs = {
4219  cpp::TemplateParameter("D"), cpp::TemplateParameter("P")};
4220  cpp::Class c(std::move(templateArgs), gen_name_);
4221 
4222  if (type_->ShouldGeneratePrint()) {
4223  hdr_ << " DECL_PRINTER(" << name_ << ")\n\n";
4224  }
4225 
4226  if (type_->ShouldGenerateVerify()) {
4227  IfDefScope hdr_scope(hdr_, "VERIFY_HEAP");
4228  // V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE void Verify(Isolate*);
4229  cpp::Function f(&c, name_ + "Verify");
4230  f.SetExport();
4231  f.SetReturnType("void");
4232  f.AddParameter("Isolate*", "isolate");
4233  f.PrintDeclaration(hdr_);
4234 
4235  IfDefScope impl_scope(impl_, "VERIFY_HEAP");
4236  impl_ << "\ntemplate <>\n";
4237  impl_ << "void " << gen_name_I_ << "::" << name_
4238  << "Verify(Isolate* isolate) {\n";
4239  impl_ << " TorqueGeneratedClassVerifiers::" << name_ << "Verify(Cast<"
4240  << name_
4241  << ">(*this), "
4242  "isolate);\n";
4243  impl_ << "}\n\n";
4244  impl_ << "\n";
4245  }
4246 
4247  hdr_ << "\n";
4248  ClassFieldOffsetGenerator g(hdr_, inl_, type_, gen_name_,
4249  type_->GetSuperClass());
4250  for (const auto& f : type_->fields()) {
4251  CurrentSourcePosition::Scope scope(f.pos);
4252  g.RecordOffsetFor(f);
4253  }
4254  g.Finish();
4255  hdr_ << "\n";
4256 
4257  auto index_fields = GetOrderedUniqueIndexFields(*type_);
4258 
4259  if (!index_fields.has_value()) {
4260  hdr_ << " // SizeFor implementations not generated due to complex array "
4261  "lengths\n\n";
4262 
4263  const Field& last_field = type_->LastField();
4264  std::string last_field_item_size =
4265  std::get<1>(*SizeOf(last_field.name_and_type.type));
4266 
4267  // int AllocatedSize() const
4268  {
4269  cpp::Function f =
4270  cpp::Function::DefaultGetter("int", &c, "AllocatedSize");
4271  f.PrintDeclaration(hdr_);
4272 
4273  f.PrintDefinition(inl_, [&](std::ostream& stream) {
4274  stream << " auto slice = "
4275  << Callable::PrefixNameForCCOutput(
4276  type_->GetSliceMacroName(last_field))
4277  << "(*static_cast<const D*>(this));\n";
4278  stream << " return static_cast<int>(std::get<1>(slice)) + "
4279  << last_field_item_size
4280  << " * static_cast<int>(std::get<2>(slice));\n";
4281  });
4282  }
4283  } else if (type_->ShouldGenerateBodyDescriptor() ||
4284  (!type_->IsAbstract() &&
4285  !type_->IsSubtypeOf(TypeOracle::GetJSObjectType()))) {
4286  cpp::Function f(&c, "SizeFor");
4287  f.SetReturnType("int32_t");
4288  f.SetFlags(cpp::Function::kStatic | cpp::Function::kConstexpr |
4289  cpp::Function::kV8Inline);
4290  for (const Field& field : *index_fields) {
4291  f.AddParameter("int", field.name_and_type.name);
4292  }
4293  f.PrintInlineDefinition(hdr_, [&](std::ostream& stream) {
4294  if (index_fields->empty()) {
4295  stream << " DCHECK(kHeaderSize == kSize && kHeaderSize == "
4296  << *type_->size().SingleValue() << ");\n";
4297  }
4298  stream << " int32_t size = kHeaderSize;\n";
4299  for (const Field& field : type_->ComputeAllFields()) {
4300  if (field.index) {
4301  auto index_name_and_type =
4302  *ExtractSimpleFieldArraySize(*type_, field.index->expr);
4303  stream << " size += " << index_name_and_type.name << " * "
4304  << std::get<0>(field.GetFieldSizeInformation()) << ";\n";
4305  }
4306  }
4307  if (type_->size().Alignment() < TargetArchitecture::TaggedSize()) {
4308  stream << " size = OBJECT_POINTER_ALIGN(size);\n";
4309  }
4310  stream << " return size;\n";
4311  });
4312 
4313  // V8_INLINE int32_t AllocatedSize() const
4314  {
4315  cpp::Function allocated_size_f =
4316  cpp::Function::DefaultGetter("int32_t", &c, "AllocatedSize");
4317  allocated_size_f.SetFlag(cpp::Function::kV8Inline);
4318  allocated_size_f.PrintInlineDefinition(hdr_, [&](std::ostream& stream) {
4319  stream << " return SizeFor(";
4320  bool first = true;
4321  for (const auto& field : *index_fields) {
4322  if (!first) stream << ", ";
4323  stream << "this->" << field.name_and_type.name << "()";
4324  first = false;
4325  }
4326  stream << ");\n";
4327  });
4328  }
4329  }
4330 
4331  hdr_ << " friend class Factory;\n\n";
4332 
4333  GenerateClassConstructors();
4334 
4335  hdr_ << "};\n\n";
4336 
4337  if (type_->ShouldGenerateFullClassDefinition()) {
4338  // If this class extends from another class which is defined in the same tq
4339  // file, and that other class doesn't generate a full class definition, then
4340  // the resulting .inc file would be uncompilable due to ordering
4341  // requirements: the generated file must go before the hand-written
4342  // definition of the base class, but it must also go after that same
4343  // hand-written definition.
4344  std::optional<const ClassType*> parent = type_->parent()->ClassSupertype();
4345  while (parent) {
4346  if ((*parent)->ShouldGenerateCppClassDefinitions() &&
4347  !(*parent)->ShouldGenerateFullClassDefinition() &&
4348  (*parent)->AttributedToFile() == type_->AttributedToFile()) {
4349  Error("Exported ", *type_,
4350  " cannot be in the same file as its parent extern ", **parent);
4351  }
4352  parent = (*parent)->parent()->ClassSupertype();
4353  }
4354 
4355  GenerateClassExport(type_, hdr_, inl_);
4356  }
4357 }
4358 
4359 void CppClassGenerator::GenerateCppObjectDefinitionAsserts() {
4360  impl_ << "// Definition " << Position() << "\n"
4361  << "class " << gen_name_ << "Asserts {\n";
4362 
4363  ClassFieldOffsetGenerator g(impl_, impl_, type_, gen_name_,
4364  type_->GetSuperClass(), false);
4365  for (const auto& f : type_->fields()) {
4366  CurrentSourcePosition::Scope scope(f.pos);
4367  g.RecordOffsetFor(f);
4368  }
4369  g.Finish();
4370  impl_ << "\n";
4371 
4372  for (const auto& f : type_->fields()) {
4373  std::string field_offset =
4374  "k" + CamelifyString(f.name_and_type.name) + "Offset";
4375  impl_ << " static_assert(" << field_offset << " == " << name_
4376  << "::" << field_offset << ",\n"
4377  << " \"Values of " << name_ << "::" << field_offset
4378  << " defined in Torque and C++ do not match\");\n";
4379  }
4380  if (!type_->IsAbstract() && type_->HasStaticSize()) {
4381  impl_ << " static_assert(kSize == " << name_ << "::kSize);\n";
4382  }
4383 
4384  impl_ << "};\n\n";
4385 }
4386 
4387 void CppClassGenerator::GenerateCppObjectLayoutDefinitionAsserts() {
4388  impl_ << "// Definition " << Position() << "\n"
4389  << "class " << gen_name_ << "Asserts {\n";
4390 
4391  ClassFieldOffsetGenerator g(impl_, impl_, type_, gen_name_,
4392  type_->GetSuperClass(), false);
4393  for (const auto& f : type_->fields()) {
4394  CurrentSourcePosition::Scope scope(f.pos);
4395  g.RecordOffsetFor(f);
4396  }
4397  g.Finish();
4398  impl_ << "\n";
4399 
4400  for (const auto& f : type_->fields()) {
4401  std::string field_offset =
4402  "k" + CamelifyString(f.name_and_type.name) + "Offset";
4403  std::string cpp_field_offset =
4404  f.index.has_value()
4405  ? "OFFSET_OF_DATA_START(" + name_ + ")"
4406  : "offsetof(" + name_ + ", " + f.name_and_type.name + "_)";
4407  impl_ << " static_assert(" << field_offset << " == " << cpp_field_offset
4408  << ",\n"
4409  << " \"Value of " << name_ << "::" << field_offset
4410  << " defined in Torque and offset of field " << name_
4411  << "::" << f.name_and_type.name << " in C++ do not match\");\n";
4412  }
4413  if (!type_->IsAbstract() && type_->HasStaticSize()) {
4414  impl_ << " static_assert(kSize == sizeof(" + name_ + "));\n";
4415  }
4416 
4417  impl_ << "};\n\n";
4418 }

4420 SourcePosition CppClassGenerator::Position() { return type_->GetPosition(); }
4421 
4422 void CppClassGenerator::GenerateClassConstructors() {
4423  const ClassType* typecheck_type = type_;
4424  while (typecheck_type->IsShape()) {
4425  typecheck_type = typecheck_type->GetSuperClass();
4426 
4427  // Shapes have already been checked earlier to inherit from JSObject, so we
4428  // should have found an appropriate type.
4429  DCHECK(typecheck_type);
4430  }
4431 
4432  hdr_ << " template <class DAlias = D>\n";
4433  hdr_ << " constexpr " << gen_name_ << "() : P() {\n";
4434  hdr_ << " static_assert(\n";
4435  hdr_ << " std::is_base_of_v<" << gen_name_ << ", DAlias>,\n";
4436  hdr_ << " \"class " << gen_name_
4437  << " should be used as direct base for " << name_ << ".\");\n";
4438  hdr_ << " }\n\n";
4439 
4440  hdr_ << " protected:\n";
4441  hdr_ << " inline explicit constexpr " << gen_name_
4442  << "(Address ptr, typename P::SkipTypeCheckTag\n)";
4443  hdr_ << " : P(ptr, typename P::SkipTypeCheckTag{}) {}\n";
4444  hdr_ << " inline explicit " << gen_name_ << "(Address ptr);\n";
4445 
4446  inl_ << "template<class D, class P>\n";
4447  inl_ << "inline " << gen_name_T_ << "::" << gen_name_ << "(Address ptr)\n";
4448  inl_ << " : P(ptr) {\n";
4449  inl_ << " SLOW_DCHECK(Is" << typecheck_type->name()
4450  << "_NonInline(*this));\n";
4451  inl_ << "}\n";
4452 }
4453 
4454 namespace {
4455 std::string GenerateRuntimeTypeCheck(const Type* type,
4456  const std::string& value) {
4457  bool maybe_object = !type->IsSubtypeOf(TypeOracle::GetStrongTaggedType());
4458  std::stringstream type_check;
4459  bool at_start = true;
4460  // If weak pointers are allowed, then start by checking for a cleared value.
4461  if (maybe_object) {
4462  type_check << value << ".IsCleared()";
4463  at_start = false;
4464  }
4465  for (const TypeChecker& runtime_type : type->GetTypeCheckers()) {
4466  if (!at_start) type_check << " || ";
4467  at_start = false;
4468  if (maybe_object) {
4469  bool strong = runtime_type.weak_ref_to.empty();
4470  if (strong && runtime_type.type == WEAK_HEAP_OBJECT) {
4471  // Rather than a generic Weak<T>, this is the basic type WeakHeapObject.
4472  // We can't validate anything more about the type of the object pointed
4473  // to, so just check that it's weak.
4474  type_check << value << ".IsWeak()";
4475  } else {
4476  type_check << "(" << (strong ? "!" : "") << value << ".IsWeak() && Is"
4477  << (strong ? runtime_type.type : runtime_type.weak_ref_to)
4478  << "(" << value << ".GetHeapObjectOrSmi()))";
4479  }
4480  } else {
4481  type_check << "Is" << runtime_type.type << "(" << value << ")";
4482  }
4483  }
4484  return type_check.str();
4485 }
4486 
4487 void GenerateBoundsDCheck(std::ostream& os, const std::string& index,
4488  const ClassType* type, const Field& f) {
4489  os << " DCHECK_GE(" << index << ", 0);\n";
4490  std::string length_expression;
4491  if (std::optional<NameAndType> array_length =
4492  ExtractSimpleFieldArraySize(*type, f.index->expr)) {
4493  length_expression = "this ->" + array_length->name + "()";
4494  } else {
4495  // The length is element 2 in the flattened field slice.
4496  length_expression =
4497  "static_cast<int>(std::get<2>(" +
4498  Callable::PrefixNameForCCOutput(type->GetSliceMacroName(f)) +
4499  "(*static_cast<const D*>(this))))";
4500  }
4501  os << " DCHECK_LT(" << index << ", " << length_expression << ");\n";
4502 }
4503 
4504 bool CanGenerateFieldAccessors(const Type* field_type) {
4505  // float64_or_undefined_or_hole should be treated like float64. For now, we
4506  // don't need it.
4507  // TODO(v8:10391) Generate accessors for external pointers.
4508  return field_type != TypeOracle::GetVoidType() &&
4509  field_type != TypeOracle::GetFloat64OrUndefinedOrHoleType() &&
4510  !field_type->IsSubtypeOf(TypeOracle::GetExternalPointerType()) &&
4511  !field_type->IsSubtypeOf(TypeOracle::GetTrustedPointerType()) &&
4512  !field_type->IsSubtypeOf(TypeOracle::GetProtectedPointerType());
4513 }
4514 } // namespace
4515 
4516 // TODO(sigurds): Keep in sync with DECL_ACCESSORS and ACCESSORS macro.
4517 void CppClassGenerator::GenerateFieldAccessors(
4518  const Field& class_field, std::vector<const Field*>& struct_fields) {
4519  const Field& innermost_field =
4520  struct_fields.empty() ? class_field : *struct_fields.back();
4521  const Type* field_type = innermost_field.name_and_type.type;
4522  if (!CanGenerateFieldAccessors(field_type)) return;
4523 
4524  if (const StructType* struct_type = StructType::DynamicCast(field_type)) {
4525  struct_fields.resize(struct_fields.size() + 1);
4526  for (const Field& struct_field : struct_type->fields()) {
4527  struct_fields[struct_fields.size() - 1] = &struct_field;
4528  GenerateFieldAccessors(class_field, struct_fields);
4529  }
4530  struct_fields.resize(struct_fields.size() - 1);
4531  return;
4532  }
4533 
4534  bool indexed = class_field.index && !class_field.index->optional;
4535  std::string type_name = GetTypeNameForAccessor(innermost_field);
4536  bool can_contain_heap_objects = CanContainHeapObjects(field_type);
4537 
4538  // Assemble an accessor name by accumulating together all of the nested field
4539  // names.
4540  std::string name = class_field.name_and_type.name;
4541  for (const Field* nested_struct_field : struct_fields) {
4542  name += "_" + nested_struct_field->name_and_type.name;
4543  }
4544 
4545  // Generate declarations in header.
4546  if (can_contain_heap_objects && !field_type->IsClassType() &&
4547  !field_type->IsStructType() &&
4548  field_type != TypeOracle::GetObjectType()) {
4549  hdr_ << " // Torque type: " << field_type->ToString() << "\n";
4550  }
4551 
4552  std::vector<cpp::TemplateParameter> templateParameters = {
4553  cpp::TemplateParameter("D"), cpp::TemplateParameter("P")};
4554  cpp::Class owner(std::move(templateParameters), gen_name_);
4555 
4556  // getter
4557  {
4558  auto getter = cpp::Function::DefaultGetter(type_name, &owner, name);
4559  if (indexed) {
4560  getter.AddParameter("int", "i");
4561  }
4562  const char* tag_argument;
4563  switch (class_field.synchronization) {
4564  case FieldSynchronization::kNone:
4565  tag_argument = "";
4566  break;
4567  case FieldSynchronization::kRelaxed:
4568  getter.AddParameter("RelaxedLoadTag");
4569  tag_argument = ", kRelaxedLoad";
4570  break;
4571  case FieldSynchronization::kAcquireRelease:
4572  getter.AddParameter("AcquireLoadTag");
4573  tag_argument = ", kAcquireLoad";
4574  break;
4575  }
4576 
4577  getter.PrintDeclaration(hdr_);
4578 
4579  // For tagged data, generate the extra getter that derives an
4580  // PtrComprCageBase from the current object's pointer.
4581  if (can_contain_heap_objects) {
4582  getter.PrintDefinition(inl_, [&](auto& stream) {
4583  stream
4584  << " PtrComprCageBase cage_base = GetPtrComprCageBase(*this);\n";
4585  stream << " return " << gen_name_ << "::" << name << "(cage_base"
4586  << (indexed ? ", i" : "") << tag_argument << ");\n";
4587  });
4588 
4589  getter.InsertParameter(0, "PtrComprCageBase", "cage_base");
4590  getter.PrintDeclaration(hdr_);
4591  }
4592 
4593  getter.PrintDefinition(inl_, [&](auto& stream) {
4594  EmitLoadFieldStatement(stream, class_field, struct_fields);
4595  stream << " return value;\n";
4596  });
4597  }
4598 
4599  // setter
4600  {
4601  auto setter = cpp::Function::DefaultSetter(
4602  &owner, std::string("set_") + name, type_name, "value");
4603  if (indexed) {
4604  setter.InsertParameter(0, "int", "i");
4605  }
4606  switch (class_field.synchronization) {
4607  case FieldSynchronization::kNone:
4608  break;
4609  case FieldSynchronization::kRelaxed:
4610  setter.AddParameter("RelaxedStoreTag");
4611  break;
4612  case FieldSynchronization::kAcquireRelease:
4613  setter.AddParameter("ReleaseStoreTag");
4614  break;
4615  }
4616  if (can_contain_heap_objects) {
4617  setter.AddParameter("WriteBarrierMode", "mode", "UPDATE_WRITE_BARRIER");
4618  }
4619  setter.PrintDeclaration(hdr_);
4620 
4621  setter.PrintDefinition(inl_, [&](auto& stream) {
4622  EmitStoreFieldStatement(stream, class_field, struct_fields);
4623  });
4624  }
4625 
4626  hdr_ << "\n";
4627 }
4628 
4629 std::string CppClassGenerator::GetFieldOffsetForAccessor(const Field& f) {
4630  if (f.offset.has_value()) {
4631  return "k" + CamelifyString(f.name_and_type.name) + "Offset";
4632  }
4633  return CamelifyString(f.name_and_type.name) + "Offset()";
4634 }
4635 
4636 std::string CppClassGenerator::GetTypeNameForAccessor(const Field& f) {
4637  const Type* field_type = f.name_and_type.type;
4638  if (!field_type->IsSubtypeOf(TypeOracle::GetTaggedType())) {
4639  const Type* constexpr_version = field_type->ConstexprVersion();
4640  if (!constexpr_version) {
4641  Error("Field accessor for ", type_->name(), ":: ", f.name_and_type.name,
4642  " cannot be generated because its type ", *field_type,
4643  " is neither a subclass of Object nor does the type have a "
4644  "constexpr "
4645  "version.")
4646  .Position(f.pos)
4647  .Throw();
4648  }
4649  return constexpr_version->GetGeneratedTypeName();
4650  }
4651  return field_type->TagglifiedCppTypeName();
4652 }
4653 
4654 bool CppClassGenerator::CanContainHeapObjects(const Type* t) {
4655  return t->IsSubtypeOf(TypeOracle::GetTaggedType()) &&
4656  !t->IsSubtypeOf(TypeOracle::GetSmiType());
4657 }
4658 
4659 void CppClassGenerator::EmitLoadFieldStatement(
4660  std::ostream& stream, const Field& class_field,
4661  std::vector<const Field*>& struct_fields) {
4662  const Field& innermost_field =
4663  struct_fields.empty() ? class_field : *struct_fields.back();
4664  const Type* field_type = innermost_field.name_and_type.type;
4665  std::string type_name = GetTypeNameForAccessor(innermost_field);
4666  const std::string class_field_size =
4667  std::get<1>(class_field.GetFieldSizeInformation());
4668 
4669  // field_offset contains both the offset from the beginning of the object to
4670  // the class field and the combined offsets of any nested struct fields
4671  // within, but not the index adjustment.
4672  std::string field_offset = GetFieldOffsetForAccessor(class_field);
4673  for (const Field* nested_struct_field : struct_fields) {
4674  field_offset += " + " + std::to_string(*nested_struct_field->offset);
4675  }
4676 
4677  std::string offset = field_offset;
4678  if (class_field.index) {
4679  const char* index = class_field.index->optional ? "0" : "i";
4680  GenerateBoundsDCheck(stream, index, type_, class_field);
4681  stream << " int offset = " << field_offset << " + " << index << " * "
4682  << class_field_size << ";\n";
4683  offset = "offset";
4684  }
4685 
4686  stream << " " << type_name << " value = ";
4687 
4688  if (!field_type->IsSubtypeOf(TypeOracle::GetTaggedType())) {
4689  const char* load;
4690  switch (class_field.synchronization) {
4691  case FieldSynchronization::kNone:
4692  load = "ReadField";
4693  break;
4694  case FieldSynchronization::kRelaxed:
4695  load = "Relaxed_ReadField";
4696  break;
4697  case FieldSynchronization::kAcquireRelease:
4698  ReportError("Torque doesn't support @cppAcquireLoad on untagged data");
4699  }
4700  stream << "this->template " << load << "<" << type_name << ">(" << offset
4701  << ");\n";
4702  } else {
4703  const char* load;
4704  switch (class_field.synchronization) {
4705  case FieldSynchronization::kNone:
4706  load = "load";
4707  break;
4708  case FieldSynchronization::kRelaxed:
4709  load = "Relaxed_Load";
4710  break;
4711  case FieldSynchronization::kAcquireRelease:
4712  load = "Acquire_Load";
4713  break;
4714  }
4715  bool is_smi = field_type->IsSubtypeOf(TypeOracle::GetSmiType());
4716  const std::string load_type = is_smi ? "Smi" : type_name;
4717  const char* postfix = is_smi ? ".value()" : "";
4718  const char* optional_cage_base = is_smi ? "" : "cage_base, ";
4719 
4720  stream << "TaggedField<" << load_type << ">::" << load << "("
4721  << optional_cage_base << "*this, " << offset << ")" << postfix
4722  << ";\n";
4723  }
4724 
4725  if (CanContainHeapObjects(field_type)) {
4726  stream << " DCHECK(" << GenerateRuntimeTypeCheck(field_type, "value")
4727  << ");\n";
4728  }
4729 }
4730 
4731 void CppClassGenerator::EmitStoreFieldStatement(
4732  std::ostream& stream, const Field& class_field,
4733  std::vector<const Field*>& struct_fields) {
4734  const Field& innermost_field =
4735  struct_fields.empty() ? class_field : *struct_fields.back();
4736  const Type* field_type = innermost_field.name_and_type.type;
4737  std::string type_name = GetTypeNameForAccessor(innermost_field);
4738  const std::string class_field_size =
4739  std::get<1>(class_field.GetFieldSizeInformation());
4740 
4741  // field_offset contains both the offset from the beginning of the object to
4742  // the class field and the combined offsets of any nested struct fields
4743  // within, but not the index adjustment.
4744  std::string field_offset = GetFieldOffsetForAccessor(class_field);
4745  for (const Field* nested_struct_field : struct_fields) {
4746  field_offset += " + " + std::to_string(*nested_struct_field->offset);
4747  }
4748 
4749  std::string offset = field_offset;
4750  if (class_field.index) {
4751  const char* index = class_field.index->optional ? "0" : "i";
4752  GenerateBoundsDCheck(stream, index, type_, class_field);
4753  stream << " int offset = " << field_offset << " + " << index << " * "
4754  << class_field_size << ";\n";
4755  offset = "offset";
4756  }
4757 
4758  if (!field_type->IsSubtypeOf(TypeOracle::GetTaggedType())) {
4759  const char* store;
4760  switch (class_field.synchronization) {
4761  case FieldSynchronization::kNone:
4762  store = "WriteField";
4763  break;
4764  case FieldSynchronization::kRelaxed:
4765  store = "Relaxed_WriteField";
4766  break;
4767  case FieldSynchronization::kAcquireRelease:
4768  ReportError("Torque doesn't support @cppReleaseStore on untagged data");
4769  }
4770  stream << " this->template " << store << "<" << type_name << ">(" << offset
4771  << ", value);\n";
4772  } else {
4773  bool strong_pointer = field_type->IsSubtypeOf(TypeOracle::GetObjectType());
4774  bool is_smi = field_type->IsSubtypeOf(TypeOracle::GetSmiType());
4775  const char* write_macro;
4776  if (!strong_pointer) {
4777  if (class_field.synchronization ==
4778  FieldSynchronization::kAcquireRelease) {
4779  ReportError("Torque doesn't support @cppReleaseStore on weak fields");
4780  }
4781  write_macro = "RELAXED_WRITE_WEAK_FIELD";
4782  } else {
4783  switch (class_field.synchronization) {
4784  case FieldSynchronization::kNone:
4785  write_macro = "WRITE_FIELD";
4786  break;
4787  case FieldSynchronization::kRelaxed:
4788  write_macro = "RELAXED_WRITE_FIELD";
4789  break;
4790  case FieldSynchronization::kAcquireRelease:
4791  write_macro = "RELEASE_WRITE_FIELD";
4792  break;
4793  }
4794  }
4795  std::string value_to_write;
4796  if (const auto type_wrapped_in_smi = Type::MatchUnaryGeneric(
4797  field_type, TypeOracle::GetSmiTaggedGeneric())) {
4798  DCHECK(is_smi);
4799  stream << " // " << type_wrapped_in_smi.value()->ToString() << "\n";
4800  value_to_write = "Smi::From31BitPattern(value)";
4801  } else {
4802  value_to_write = is_smi ? "Smi::FromInt(value)" : "value";
4803  }
4804 
4805  if (!is_smi) {
4806  // Don't DCHECK types if the roots aren't initialized, so that we don't
4807  // incorrectly fail these checks during initial heap setup.
4808  stream << " "
4809  "SLOW_DCHECK(!IsolateGroup::current()->shared_read_only_heap()-"
4810  ">roots_init_complete() || ("
4811  << GenerateRuntimeTypeCheck(field_type, "value") << "));\n";
4812  }
4813  stream << " " << write_macro << "(*this, " << offset << ", "
4814  << value_to_write << ");\n";
4815  if (!is_smi) {
4816  stream << " CONDITIONAL_WRITE_BARRIER(*this, " << offset
4817  << ", value, mode);\n";
4818  }
4819  }
4820 }
4821 
4822 void GenerateStructLayoutDescription(std::ostream& header,
4823  const StructType* type) {
4824  header << "struct TorqueGenerated" << CamelifyString(type->name())
4825  << "Offsets {\n";
4826  for (const Field& field : type->fields()) {
4827  header << " static constexpr int k"
4828  << CamelifyString(field.name_and_type.name)
4829  << "Offset = " << *field.offset << ";\n";
4830  }
4831  header << " static constexpr int kSize = " << type->PackedSize() << ";\n";
4832  header << "};\n\n";
4833 }
4834 
4835 } // namespace
4836 
4837 void ImplementationVisitor::GenerateClassDefinitions(
4838  const std::string& output_directory) {
4839  std::stringstream factory_header;
4840  std::stringstream factory_impl;
4841  std::string factory_basename = "factory";
4842 
4843  std::stringstream forward_declarations;
4844  std::string forward_declarations_filename = "class-forward-declarations.h";
4845 
4846  {
4847  factory_impl << "#include \"src/heap/factory-base.h\"\n";
4848  factory_impl << "#include \"src/heap/factory-base-inl.h\"\n";
4849  factory_impl << "#include \"src/heap/heap.h\"\n";
4850  factory_impl << "#include \"src/heap/heap-inl.h\"\n";
4851  factory_impl << "#include \"src/execution/isolate.h\"\n";
4852  factory_impl << "#include "
4853  "\"src/objects/all-objects-inl.h\"\n\n";
4854  NamespaceScope factory_impl_namespaces(factory_impl, {"v8", "internal"});
4855  factory_impl << "\n";
4856 
4857  IncludeGuardScope include_guard(forward_declarations,
4858  forward_declarations_filename);
4859  NamespaceScope forward_declarations_namespaces(forward_declarations,
4860  {"v8", "internal"});
4861 
4862  std::set<const StructType*, TypeLess> structs_used_in_classes;
4863 
4864  // Emit forward declarations.
4865  for (const ClassType* type : TypeOracle::GetClasses()) {
4866  CurrentSourcePosition::Scope position_activator(type->GetPosition());
4867  auto& streams = GlobalContext::GeneratedPerFile(type->AttributedToFile());
4868  std::ostream& header = streams.class_definition_headerfile;
4869  std::string name = type->ShouldGenerateCppClassDefinitions()
4870  ? type->name()
4871  : type->GetGeneratedTNodeTypeName();
4872  if (type->ShouldGenerateCppClassDefinitions()) {
4873  header << "class " << name << ";\n";
4874  }
4875  forward_declarations << "class " << name << ";\n";
4876  }
4877 
4878  for (const ClassType* type : TypeOracle::GetClasses()) {
4879  CurrentSourcePosition::Scope position_activator(type->GetPosition());
4880  auto& streams = GlobalContext::GeneratedPerFile(type->AttributedToFile());
4881  std::ostream& header = streams.class_definition_headerfile;
4882  std::ostream& inline_header = streams.class_definition_inline_headerfile;
4883  std::ostream& implementation = streams.class_definition_ccfile;
4884 
4885  if (type->ShouldGenerateCppClassDefinitions()) {
4886  CppClassGenerator g(type, header, inline_header, implementation);
4887  g.GenerateClass();
4888  } else if (type->ShouldGenerateCppObjectDefinitionAsserts()) {
4889  CppClassGenerator g(type, header, inline_header, implementation);
4890  g.GenerateCppObjectDefinitionAsserts();
4891  } else if (type->ShouldGenerateCppObjectLayoutDefinitionAsserts()) {
4892  CppClassGenerator g(type, header, inline_header, implementation);
4893  g.GenerateCppObjectLayoutDefinitionAsserts();
4894  }
4895  for (const Field& f : type->fields()) {
4896  const Type* field_type = f.name_and_type.type;
4897  if (auto field_as_struct = field_type->StructSupertype()) {
4898  structs_used_in_classes.insert(*field_as_struct);
4899  }
4900  }
4901  if (type->ShouldGenerateFactoryFunction()) {
4902  std::string return_type =
4903  type->HandlifiedCppTypeName(Type::HandleKind::kIndirect);
4904  std::string function_name = "New" + type->name();
4905  std::stringstream parameters;
4906  for (const Field& f : type->ComputeAllFields()) {
4907  if (f.name_and_type.name == "map") continue;
4908  if (f.name_and_type.name == "self_indirect_pointer") continue;
4909  if (!f.index) {
4910  std::string type_string =
4911  f.name_and_type.type->HandlifiedCppTypeName(
4912  Type::HandleKind::kDirect);
4913  parameters << type_string << " " << f.name_and_type.name << ", ";
4914  }
4915  }
4916  parameters << "AllocationType allocation_type";
4917 
4918  factory_header << return_type << " " << function_name << "("
4919  << parameters.str() << ");\n";
4920  factory_impl << "template <typename Impl>\n";
4921  factory_impl << return_type
4922  << " TorqueGeneratedFactory<Impl>::" << function_name
4923  << "(" << parameters.str() << ") {\n";
4924 
4925  factory_impl << " int size = ";
4926  const ClassType* super = type->GetSuperClass();
4927  std::string gen_name = "TorqueGenerated" + type->name();
4928  std::string gen_name_T =
4929  gen_name + "<" + type->name() + ", " + super->name() + ">";
4930  factory_impl << gen_name_T << "::SizeFor(";
4931 
4932  bool first = true;
4933  auto index_fields = GetOrderedUniqueIndexFields(*type);
4934  CHECK(index_fields.has_value());
4935  for (const auto& index_field : *index_fields) {
4936  if (!first) {
4937  factory_impl << ", ";
4938  }
4939  factory_impl << index_field.name_and_type.name;
4940  first = false;
4941  }
4942 
4943  factory_impl << ");\n";
4944  factory_impl << " Tagged<Map> map = factory()->read_only_roots()."
4945  << SnakeifyString(type->name()) << "_map();\n";
4946  factory_impl << " Tagged<HeapObject> raw_object =\n";
4947  factory_impl << " factory()->AllocateRawWithImmortalMap(size, "
4948  "allocation_type, map);\n";
4949  factory_impl << " " << type->TagglifiedCppTypeName()
4950  << " result = Cast<"
4951  << type->GetConstexprGeneratedTypeName()
4952  << ">(raw_object);\n";
4953  factory_impl << " DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;\n";
4954  factory_impl << " WriteBarrierMode write_barrier_mode =\n"
4955  << " allocation_type == AllocationType::kYoung\n"
4956  << " ? SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER : UPDATE_WRITE_BARRIER;\n"
4957  << " USE(write_barrier_mode);\n";
4958 
4959  for (const Field& f : type->ComputeAllFields()) {
4960  if (f.name_and_type.name == "map") continue;
4961  if (f.name_and_type.name == "self_indirect_pointer") {
4962  factory_impl << " "
4963  "result->init_self_indirect_pointer(factory()->"
4964  "isolate());\n";
4965  } else if (!f.index) {
4966  factory_impl << " result->TorqueGeneratedClass::set_"
4967  << SnakeifyString(f.name_and_type.name) << "(";
4968  if (f.name_and_type.type->IsSubtypeOf(
4969  TypeOracle::GetTaggedType()) &&
4970  !f.name_and_type.type->IsSubtypeOf(TypeOracle::GetSmiType())) {
4971  factory_impl << "*" << f.name_and_type.name
4972  << ", write_barrier_mode";
4973  } else {
4974  factory_impl << f.name_and_type.name;
4975  }
4976  factory_impl << ");\n";
4977  }
4978  }
4979 
4980  factory_impl << " return handle(result, factory()->isolate());\n";
4981  factory_impl << "}\n\n";
4982 
4983  factory_impl << "template EXPORT_TEMPLATE_DEFINE(V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE) "
4984  << return_type
4985  << " TorqueGeneratedFactory<Factory>::" << function_name
4986  << "(" << parameters.str() << ");\n";
4987  factory_impl << "template EXPORT_TEMPLATE_DEFINE(V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE) "
4988  << return_type << " TorqueGeneratedFactory<LocalFactory>::"
4989  << function_name << "(" << parameters.str() << ");\n";
4990 
4991  factory_impl << "\n\n";
4992  }
4993  }
4994 
4995  for (const StructType* type : structs_used_in_classes) {
4996  CurrentSourcePosition::Scope position_activator(type->GetPosition());
4997  std::ostream& header =
4998  GlobalContext::GeneratedPerFile(type->GetPosition().source)
4999  .class_definition_headerfile;
5000  if (type != TypeOracle::GetFloat64OrUndefinedOrHoleType()) {
5001  GenerateStructLayoutDescription(header, type);
5002  }
5003  }
5004  }
5005  WriteFile(output_directory + "/" + factory_basename + ".inc",
5006  factory_header.str());
5007  WriteFile(output_directory + "/" + factory_basename + ".cc",
5008  factory_impl.str());
5009  WriteFile(output_directory + "/" + forward_declarations_filename,
5010  forward_declarations.str());
5011 }
5012 
5013 namespace {
5014 void GeneratePrintDefinitionsForClass(std::ostream& impl, const ClassType* type,
5015  const std::string& gen_name,
5016  const std::string& gen_name_T,
5017  const std::string template_params) {
5018  impl << template_params << "\n";
5019  impl << "void " << gen_name_T << "::" << type->name()
5020  << "Print(std::ostream& os) {\n";
5021  impl << " this->PrintHeader(os, \"" << type->name() << "\");\n";
5022  auto hierarchy = type->GetHierarchy();
5023  std::map<std::string, const AggregateType*> field_names;
5024  for (const AggregateType* aggregate_type : hierarchy) {
5025  for (const Field& f : aggregate_type->fields()) {
5026  if (f.name_and_type.name == "map" || f.index.has_value() ||
5027  !CanGenerateFieldAccessors(f.name_and_type.type)) {
5028  continue;
5029  }
5030  std::string getter = f.name_and_type.name;
5031  if (aggregate_type != type) {
5032  // We must call getters directly on the class that provided them,
5033  // because a subclass could have hidden them.
5034  getter = aggregate_type->name() + "::TorqueGeneratedClass::" + getter;
5035  }
5036  if (f.name_and_type.type->IsSubtypeOf(TypeOracle::GetSmiType()) ||
5037  !f.name_and_type.type->IsSubtypeOf(TypeOracle::GetTaggedType())) {
5038  impl << " os << \"\\n - " << f.name_and_type.name << ": \" << ";
5039  if (f.name_and_type.type->StructSupertype()) {
5040  // TODO(turbofan): Print struct fields too.
5041  impl << "\" <struct field printing still unimplemented>\";\n";
5042  } else {
5043  impl << "this->" << getter;
5044  switch (f.synchronization) {
5045  case FieldSynchronization::kNone:
5046  impl << "();\n";
5047  break;
5048  case FieldSynchronization::kRelaxed:
5049  impl << "(kRelaxedLoad);\n";
5050  break;
5051  case FieldSynchronization::kAcquireRelease:
5052  impl << "(kAcquireLoad);\n";
5053  break;
5054  }
5055  }
5056  } else {
5057  impl << " os << \"\\n - " << f.name_and_type.name << ": \" << "
5058  << "Brief(this->" << getter;
5059  switch (f.synchronization) {
5060  case FieldSynchronization::kNone:
5061  impl << "());\n";
5062  break;
5063  case FieldSynchronization::kRelaxed:
5064  impl << "(kRelaxedLoad));\n";
5065  break;
5066  case FieldSynchronization::kAcquireRelease:
5067  impl << "(kAcquireLoad));\n";
5068  break;
5069  }
5070  }
5071  }
5072  }
5073  impl << " os << '\\n';\n";
5074  impl << "}\n\n";
5075 }
5076 } // namespace
5077 
5078 void ImplementationVisitor::GeneratePrintDefinitions(
5079  const std::string& output_directory) {
5080  std::stringstream impl;
5081  std::string file_name = "objects-printer.cc";
5082  {
5083  IfDefScope object_print(impl, "OBJECT_PRINT");
5084 
5085  impl << "#include <iosfwd>\n\n";
5086  impl << "#include \"src/objects/all-objects-inl.h\"\n\n";
5087 
5088  NamespaceScope impl_namespaces(impl, {"v8", "internal"});
5089 
5090  for (const ClassType* type : TypeOracle::GetClasses()) {
5091  if (!type->ShouldGeneratePrint()) continue;
5092  DCHECK(type->ShouldGenerateCppClassDefinitions());
5093  const ClassType* super = type->GetSuperClass();
5094  std::string gen_name = "TorqueGenerated" + type->name();
5095  std::string gen_name_T =
5096  gen_name + "<" + type->name() + ", " + super->name() + ">";
5097  std::string template_decl = "template <>";
5098  GeneratePrintDefinitionsForClass(impl, type, gen_name, gen_name_T,
5099  template_decl);
5100  }
5101  }
5102 
5103  std::string new_contents(impl.str());
5104  WriteFile(output_directory + "/" + file_name, new_contents);
5105 }
5106 
5107 std::optional<std::string> MatchSimpleBodyDescriptor(const ClassType* type) {
5108  std::vector<ObjectSlotKind> slots = type->ComputeHeaderSlotKinds();
5109  if (!type->HasStaticSize()) {
5110  slots.push_back(*type->ComputeArraySlotKind());
5111  }
5112 
5113  // Skip the map slot.
5114  size_t i = 1;
5115  while (i < slots.size() && slots[i] == ObjectSlotKind::kNoPointer) ++i;
5116  if (i == slots.size()) return "DataOnlyBodyDescriptor";
5117  bool has_weak_pointers = false;
5118  size_t start_index = i;
5119  for (; i < slots.size(); ++i) {
5120  if (slots[i] == ObjectSlotKind::kStrongPointer) {
5121  continue;
5122  } else if (slots[i] == ObjectSlotKind::kMaybeObjectPointer) {
5123  has_weak_pointers = true;
5124  } else if (slots[i] == ObjectSlotKind::kNoPointer) {
5125  break;
5126  } else {
5127  return std::nullopt;
5128  }
5129  }
5130  size_t end_index = i;
5131  for (; i < slots.size(); ++i) {
5132  if (slots[i] != ObjectSlotKind::kNoPointer) return std::nullopt;
5133  }
5134  size_t start_offset = start_index * TargetArchitecture::TaggedSize();
5135  size_t end_offset = end_index * TargetArchitecture::TaggedSize();
5136  // We pick a suffix-range body descriptor even in cases where the object size
5137  // is fixed, to reduce the amount of code executed for object visitation.
5138  if (end_index == slots.size()) {
5139  return ToString("SuffixRange", has_weak_pointers ? "Weak" : "",
5140  "BodyDescriptor<", start_offset, ">");
5141  }
5142  if (!has_weak_pointers) {
5143  return ToString("FixedRangeBodyDescriptor<", start_offset, ", ", end_offset,
5144  ">");
5145  }
5146  return std::nullopt;
5147 }
5148 
5149 void ImplementationVisitor::GenerateBodyDescriptors(
5150  const std::string& output_directory) {
5151  std::string file_name = "objects-body-descriptors-inl.inc";
5152  std::stringstream h_contents;
5153 
5154  for (const ClassType* type : TypeOracle::GetClasses()) {
5155  std::string name = type->name();
5156  if (!type->ShouldGenerateBodyDescriptor()) continue;
5157 
5158  bool has_array_fields = !type->HasStaticSize();
5159  std::vector<ObjectSlotKind> header_slot_kinds =
5160  type->ComputeHeaderSlotKinds();
5161  std::optional<ObjectSlotKind> array_slot_kind =
5162  type->ComputeArraySlotKind();
5163  DCHECK_EQ(has_array_fields, array_slot_kind.has_value());
5164 
5165  h_contents << "class " << name << "::BodyDescriptor final : public ";
5166  if (auto descriptor_name = MatchSimpleBodyDescriptor(type)) {
5167  h_contents << *descriptor_name << " {\n";
5168  h_contents << " public:\n";
5169  } else {
5170  h_contents << "BodyDescriptorBase {\n";
5171  h_contents << " public:\n";
5172 
5173  h_contents << " template <typename ObjectVisitor>\n";
5174  h_contents
5175  << " static inline void IterateBody(Tagged<Map> map, "
5176  "Tagged<HeapObject> obj, int object_size, ObjectVisitor* v) {\n";
5177 
5178  std::vector<ObjectSlotKind> slots = std::move(header_slot_kinds);
5179  if (has_array_fields) slots.push_back(*array_slot_kind);
5180 
5181  // Skip the map slot.
5182  slots.erase(slots.begin());
5183  size_t start_offset = TargetArchitecture::TaggedSize();
5184 
5185  size_t end_offset = start_offset;
5186  ObjectSlotKind section_kind;
5187  for (size_t i = 0; i <= slots.size(); ++i) {
5188  std::optional<ObjectSlotKind> next_section_kind;
5189  bool finished_section = false;
5190  if (i == 0) {
5191  next_section_kind = slots[i];
5192  } else if (i < slots.size()) {
5193  if (auto combined = Combine(section_kind, slots[i])) {
5194  next_section_kind = *combined;
5195  } else {
5196  next_section_kind = slots[i];
5197  finished_section = true;
5198  }
5199  } else {
5200  finished_section = true;
5201  }
5202  if (finished_section) {
5203  bool is_array_slot = i == slots.size() && has_array_fields;
5204  bool multiple_slots =
5205  is_array_slot ||
5206  (end_offset - start_offset > TargetArchitecture::TaggedSize());
5207  std::optional<std::string> iterate_command;
5208  switch (section_kind) {
5209  case ObjectSlotKind::kStrongPointer:
5210  iterate_command = "IteratePointer";
5211  break;
5212  case ObjectSlotKind::kMaybeObjectPointer:
5213  iterate_command = "IterateMaybeWeakPointer";
5214  break;
5215  case ObjectSlotKind::kCustomWeakPointer:
5216  iterate_command = "IterateCustomWeakPointer";
5217  break;
5218  case ObjectSlotKind::kNoPointer:
5219  break;
5220  }
5221  if (iterate_command) {
5222  if (multiple_slots) *iterate_command += "s";
5223  h_contents << " " << *iterate_command << "(obj, "
5224  << start_offset;
5225  if (multiple_slots) {
5226  h_contents << ", "
5227  << (i == slots.size() ? "object_size"
5228  : std::to_string(end_offset));
5229  }
5230  h_contents << ", v);\n";
5231  }
5232  start_offset = end_offset;
5233  }
5234  if (i < slots.size()) section_kind = *next_section_kind;
5235  end_offset += TargetArchitecture::TaggedSize();
5236  }
5237 
5238  h_contents << " }\n\n";
5239  }
5240 
5241  h_contents << " static inline int SizeOf(Tagged<Map> map, "
5242  "Tagged<HeapObject> raw_object) {\n";
5243  if (type->size().SingleValue()) {
5244  h_contents << " return " << *type->size().SingleValue() << ";\n";
5245  } else {
5246  // We use an UncheckedCast here because this is used for concurrent
5247  // marking, where we shouldn't re-read the map.
5248  h_contents << " return UncheckedCast<" << name
5249  << ">(raw_object)->AllocatedSize();\n";
5250  }
5251  h_contents << " }\n\n";
5252 
5253  h_contents << "};\n";
5254  }
5255 
5256  WriteFile(output_directory + "/" + file_name, h_contents.str());
5257 }
5258 
5259 namespace {
5260 
5261 // Generate verification code for a single piece of class data, which might be
5262 // nested within a struct or might be a single element in an indexed field (or
5263 // both).
5264 void GenerateFieldValueVerifier(const std::string& class_name, bool indexed,
5265  std::string offset, const Field& leaf_field,
5266  std::string indexed_field_size,
5267  std::ostream& cc_contents, bool is_map) {
5268  const Type* field_type = leaf_field.name_and_type.type;
5269 
5270  bool maybe_object =
5271  !field_type->IsSubtypeOf(TypeOracle::GetStrongTaggedType());
5272  const char* object_type = maybe_object ? "MaybeObject" : "Object";
5273  const char* tagged_object_type =
5274  maybe_object ? "Tagged<MaybeObject>" : "Tagged<Object>";
5275  const char* verify_fn =
5276  maybe_object ? "VerifyMaybeObjectPointer" : "VerifyPointer";
5277  if (indexed) {
5278  offset += " + i * " + indexed_field_size;
5279  }
5280  // Name the local var based on the field name for nicer CHECK output.
5281  const std::string value = leaf_field.name_and_type.name + "__value";
5282 
5283  // Read the field.
5284  if (is_map) {
5285  cc_contents << " " << tagged_object_type << " " << value
5286  << " = o->map();\n";
5287  } else {
5288  cc_contents << " " << tagged_object_type << " " << value
5289  << " = TaggedField<" << object_type << ">::load(o, " << offset
5290  << ");\n";
5291  }
5292 
5293  // Call VerifyPointer or VerifyMaybeObjectPointer on it.
5294  cc_contents << " Object::" << verify_fn << "(isolate, " << value << ");\n";
5295 
5296  // Check that the value is of an appropriate type. We can skip this part for
5297  // the Object type because it would not check anything beyond what we already
5298  // checked with VerifyPointer.
5299  if (field_type != TypeOracle::GetObjectType()) {
5300  cc_contents << " CHECK(" << GenerateRuntimeTypeCheck(field_type, value)
5301  << ");\n";
5302  }
5303 }
5304 
5305 void GenerateClassFieldVerifier(const std::string& class_name,
5306  const ClassType& class_type, const Field& f,
5307  std::ostream& h_contents,
5308  std::ostream& cc_contents) {
5309  const Type* field_type = f.name_and_type.type;
5310 
5311  // We only verify tagged types, not raw numbers or pointers. Structs
5312  // consisting of tagged types are also included.
5313  if (!field_type->IsSubtypeOf(TypeOracle::GetTaggedType()) &&
5314  !field_type->StructSupertype())
5315  return;
5316  // Protected pointer fields cannot be read or verified from torque yet.
5317  if (field_type->IsSubtypeOf(TypeOracle::GetProtectedPointerType())) return;
5318  if (field_type == TypeOracle::GetFloat64OrUndefinedOrHoleType()) return;
5319 
5320  std::string field_start_offset;
5321  if (f.index) {
5322  field_start_offset = f.name_and_type.name + "__offset";
5323  std::string length = f.name_and_type.name + "__length";
5324  cc_contents << " intptr_t " << field_start_offset << ", " << length
5325  << ";\n";
5326  cc_contents << " std::tie(std::ignore, " << field_start_offset << ", "
5327  << length << ") = "
5328  << Callable::PrefixNameForCCOutput(
5329  class_type.GetSliceMacroName(f))
5330  << "(o);\n";
5331 
5332  // Slices use intptr, but TaggedField<T>.load() uses int, so verify that
5333  // such a cast is valid.
5334  cc_contents << " CHECK_EQ(" << field_start_offset << ", static_cast<int>("
5335  << field_start_offset << "));\n";
5336  cc_contents << " CHECK_EQ(" << length << ", static_cast<int>(" << length
5337  << "));\n";
5338  field_start_offset = "static_cast<int>(" + field_start_offset + ")";
5339  length = "static_cast<int>(" + length + ")";
5340 
5341  cc_contents << " for (int i = 0; i < " << length << "; ++i) {\n";
5342  } else {
5343  // Non-indexed fields have known offsets.
5344  field_start_offset = std::to_string(*f.offset);
5345  cc_contents << " {\n";
5346  }
5347 
5348  if (auto struct_type = field_type->StructSupertype()) {
5349  for (const Field& struct_field : (*struct_type)->fields()) {
5350  if (struct_field.name_and_type.type->IsSubtypeOf(
5351  TypeOracle::GetTaggedType())) {
5352  GenerateFieldValueVerifier(
5353  class_name, f.index.has_value(),
5354  field_start_offset + " + " + std::to_string(*struct_field.offset),
5355  struct_field, std::to_string((*struct_type)->PackedSize()),
5356  cc_contents, f.name_and_type.name == "map");
5357  }
5358  }
5359  } else {
5360  GenerateFieldValueVerifier(class_name, f.index.has_value(),
5361  field_start_offset, f, "kTaggedSize",
5362  cc_contents, f.name_and_type.name == "map");
5363  }
5364 
5365  cc_contents << " }\n";
5366 }
5367 
5368 } // namespace
5369 
5370 void ImplementationVisitor::GenerateClassVerifiers(
5371  const std::string& output_directory) {
5372  std::string file_name = "class-verifiers";
5373  std::stringstream h_contents;
5374  std::stringstream cc_contents;
5375  {
5376  IncludeGuardScope include_guard(h_contents, file_name + ".h");
5377  IfDefScope verify_heap_h(h_contents, "VERIFY_HEAP");
5378  IfDefScope verify_heap_cc(cc_contents, "VERIFY_HEAP");
5379 
5380  h_contents << "#include \"src/base/macros.h\"\n\n";
5381 
5382  cc_contents << "#include \"torque-generated/" << file_name << ".h\"\n\n";
5383  cc_contents << "#include \"src/objects/all-objects-inl.h\"\n";
5384 
5385  IncludeObjectMacrosScope object_macros(cc_contents);
5386 
5387  NamespaceScope h_namespaces(h_contents, {"v8", "internal"});
5388  NamespaceScope cc_namespaces(cc_contents, {"v8", "internal"});
5389 
5390  cc_contents
5391  << "#include \"torque-generated/test/torque/test-torque-tq-inl.inc\"\n";
5392 
5393  // Generate forward declarations to avoid including any headers.
5394  h_contents << "class Isolate;\n";
5395  h_contents << "template<typename T>\nclass Tagged;\n";
5396  for (const ClassType* type : TypeOracle::GetClasses()) {
5397  if (!type->ShouldGenerateVerify()) continue;
5398  h_contents << "class " << type->name() << ";\n";
5399  }
5400 
5401  const char* verifier_class = "TorqueGeneratedClassVerifiers";
5402 
5403  h_contents << "class V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE " << verifier_class << "{\n";
5404  h_contents << " public:\n";
5405 
5406  for (const ClassType* type : TypeOracle::GetClasses()) {
5407  std::string name = type->name();
5408  std::string cpp_name = type->TagglifiedCppTypeName();
5409  if (!type->ShouldGenerateVerify()) continue;
5410 
5411  std::string method_name = name + "Verify";
5412 
5413  h_contents << " static void " << method_name << "(" << cpp_name
5414  << " o, Isolate* isolate);\n";
5415 
5416  cc_contents << "void " << verifier_class << "::" << method_name << "("
5417  << cpp_name << " o, Isolate* isolate) {\n";
5418 
5419  // First, do any verification for the super class. Not all classes have
5420  // verifiers, so skip to the nearest super class that has one.
5421  const ClassType* super_type = type->GetSuperClass();
5422  while (super_type && !super_type->ShouldGenerateVerify()) {
5423  super_type = super_type->GetSuperClass();
5424  }
5425  if (super_type) {
5426  std::string super_name = super_type->name();
5427  cc_contents << " o->" << super_name << "Verify(isolate);\n";
5428  }
5429 
5430  // Second, verify that this object is what it claims to be.
5431  cc_contents << " CHECK(Is" << name << "(o, isolate));\n";
5432 
5433  // Third, verify its properties.
5434  for (const auto& f : type->fields()) {
5435  GenerateClassFieldVerifier(name, *type, f, h_contents, cc_contents);
5436  }
5437 
5438  cc_contents << "}\n";
5439  }
5440 
5441  h_contents << "};\n";
5442  }
5443  WriteFile(output_directory + "/" + file_name + ".h", h_contents.str());
5444  WriteFile(output_directory + "/" + file_name + ".cc", cc_contents.str());
5445 }

5447 void ImplementationVisitor::GenerateEnumVerifiers(
5448  const std::string& output_directory) {
5449  std::string file_name = "enum-verifiers";
5450  std::stringstream cc_contents;
5451  {
5452  cc_contents << "#include \"src/compiler/code-assembler.h\"\n";
5453  for (const std::string& include_path : GlobalContext::CppIncludes()) {
5454  cc_contents << "#include " << StringLiteralQuote(include_path) << "\n";
5455  }
5456  cc_contents << "\n";
5457 
5458  NamespaceScope cc_namespaces(cc_contents, {"v8", "internal", ""});
5459 
5460  cc_contents << "class EnumVerifier {\n";
5461  for (const auto& desc : GlobalContext::Get().ast()->EnumDescriptions()) {
5462  std::stringstream alias_checks;
5463  cc_contents << " // " << desc.name << " (" << desc.pos << ")\n";
5464  cc_contents << " void VerifyEnum_" << desc.name << "("
5465  << desc.constexpr_generates
5466  << " x) {\n"
5467  " switch(x) {\n";
5468  for (const auto& entry : desc.entries) {
5469  if (entry.alias_entry.empty()) {
5470  cc_contents << " case " << entry.name << ": break;\n";
5471  } else {
5472  // We don't add a case for this, because it aliases another entry, so
5473  // we would have two cases for the same value.
5474  alias_checks << " static_assert(" << entry.name
5475  << " == " << entry.alias_entry << ");\n";
5476  }
5477  }
5478  if (desc.is_open) cc_contents << " default: break;\n";
5479  cc_contents << " }\n";
5480  cc_contents << alias_checks.str();
5481  cc_contents << " }\n\n";
5482  }
5483  cc_contents << "};\n";
5484  }
5485 
5486  WriteFile(output_directory + "/" + file_name + ".cc", cc_contents.str());
5487 }

5489 void ImplementationVisitor::GenerateExportedMacrosAssembler(
5490  const std::string& output_directory) {
5491  std::string file_name = "exported-macros-assembler";
5492  std::stringstream h_contents;
5493  std::stringstream cc_contents;
5494  {
5495  IncludeGuardScope include_guard(h_contents, file_name + ".h");
5496 
5497  h_contents << "#include \"src/compiler/code-assembler.h\"\n";
5498  h_contents << "#include \"src/execution/frames.h\"\n";
5499  h_contents << "#include \"torque-generated/csa-types.h\"\n";
5500 
5501  for (const std::string& include_path : GlobalContext::CppIncludes()) {
5502  cc_contents << "#include " << StringLiteralQuote(include_path) << "\n";
5503  }
5504  cc_contents << "#include \"torque-generated/" << file_name << ".h\"\n";
5505 
5506  for (SourceId file : SourceFileMap::AllSources()) {
5507  cc_contents << "#include \"torque-generated/" +
5508  SourceFileMap::PathFromV8RootWithoutExtension(file) +
5509  "-tq-csa.h\"\n";
5510  }
5511 
5512  NamespaceScope h_namespaces(h_contents, {"v8", "internal"});
5513  NamespaceScope cc_namespaces(cc_contents, {"v8", "internal"});
5514 
5515  h_contents << "class V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE "
5516  "TorqueGeneratedExportedMacrosAssembler {\n"
5517  << " public:\n"
5518  << " explicit TorqueGeneratedExportedMacrosAssembler"
5519  "(compiler::CodeAssemblerState* state) : state_(state) {\n"
5520  << " USE(state_);\n"
5521  << " }\n";
5522 
5523  for (auto& declarable : GlobalContext::AllDeclarables()) {
5524  TorqueMacro* macro = TorqueMacro::DynamicCast(declarable.get());
5525  if (!(macro && macro->IsExportedToCSA())) continue;
5526  CurrentSourcePosition::Scope position_activator(macro->Position());
5527 
5528  cpp::Class assembler("TorqueGeneratedExportedMacrosAssembler");
5529  std::vector<std::string> generated_parameter_names;
5530  cpp::Function f = GenerateFunction(
5531  &assembler, macro->ReadableName(), macro->signature(),
5532  macro->parameter_names(), false, &generated_parameter_names);
5533 
5534  f.PrintDeclaration(h_contents);
5535  f.PrintDefinition(cc_contents, [&](std::ostream& stream) {
5536  stream << "return " << macro->ExternalName() << "(state_";
5537  for (const auto& name : generated_parameter_names) {
5538  stream << ", " << name;
5539  }
5540  stream << ");";
5541  });
5542  }
5543 
5544  h_contents << " private:\n"
5545  << " compiler::CodeAssemblerState* state_;\n"
5546  << "};\n";
5547  }
5548  WriteFile(output_directory + "/" + file_name + ".h", h_contents.str());
5549  WriteFile(output_directory + "/" + file_name + ".cc", cc_contents.str());
5550 }

5554 void CollectAllFields(const std::string& path, const Field& field,
5555  std::vector<std::string>& result) {
5556  if (field.name_and_type.type->StructSupertype()) {
5557  std::string next_path = path + field.name_and_type.name + ".";
5558  const StructType* struct_type =
5559  StructType::DynamicCast(field.name_and_type.type);
5560  for (const auto& inner_field : struct_type->fields()) {
5561  CollectAllFields(next_path, inner_field, result);
5562  }
5563  } else {
5564  result.push_back(path + field.name_and_type.name);
5565  }
5566 }

5570 void ImplementationVisitor::GenerateCSATypes(
5571  const std::string& output_directory) {
5572  std::string file_name = "csa-types";
5573  std::stringstream h_contents;
5574  {
5575  IncludeGuardScope include_guard(h_contents, file_name + ".h");
5576  h_contents << "#include \"src/compiler/code-assembler.h\"\n\n";
5577 
5578  NamespaceScope h_namespaces(h_contents, {"v8", "internal"});
5579 
5580  // Generates headers for all structs in a topologically-sorted order, since
5581  // TypeOracle keeps them in the order of their resolution
5582  for (const auto& type : TypeOracle::GetAggregateTypes()) {
5583  const StructType* struct_type = StructType::DynamicCast(type.get());
5584  if (!struct_type) continue;
5585  h_contents << "struct " << struct_type->GetGeneratedTypeNameImpl()
5586  << " {\n";
5587  for (auto& field : struct_type->fields()) {
5588  h_contents << " " << field.name_and_type.type->GetGeneratedTypeName();
5589  h_contents << " " << field.name_and_type.name << ";\n";
5590  }
5591  h_contents << "\n std::tuple<";
5592  bool first = true;
5593  for (const Type* lowered_type : LowerType(struct_type)) {
5594  if (!first) {
5595  h_contents << ", ";
5596  }
5597  first = false;
5598  h_contents << lowered_type->GetGeneratedTypeName();
5599  }
5600  std::vector<std::string> all_fields;
5601  for (auto& field : struct_type->fields()) {
5602  CollectAllFields("", field, all_fields);
5603  }
5604  h_contents << "> Flatten() const {\n"
5605  " return std::make_tuple(";
5606  PrintCommaSeparatedList(h_contents, all_fields);
5607  h_contents << ");\n";
5608  h_contents << " }\n";
5609  h_contents << "};\n";
5610  }
5611  }
5612  WriteFile(output_directory + "/" + file_name + ".h", h_contents.str());
5613 }
5614 
5615 void ReportAllUnusedMacros() {
5616  for (const auto& declarable : GlobalContext::AllDeclarables()) {
5617  if (!declarable->IsMacro() || declarable->IsExternMacro()) continue;
5618 
5619  Macro* macro = Macro::cast(declarable.get());
5620  if (macro->IsUsed()) continue;
5621 
5622  if (macro->IsTorqueMacro() && TorqueMacro::cast(macro)->IsExportedToCSA()) {
5623  continue;
5624  }
5625  // TODO(gsps): Mark methods of generic structs used if they are used in any
5626  // instantiation
5627  if (Method* method = Method::DynamicCast(macro)) {
5628  if (StructType* struct_type =
5629  StructType::DynamicCast(method->aggregate_type())) {
5630  if (struct_type->GetSpecializedFrom().has_value()) {
5631  continue;
5632  }
5633  }
5634  }
5635 
5636  std::vector<std::string> ignored_prefixes = {"Convert<", "Cast<",
5637  "FromConstexpr<"};
5638  const std::string name = macro->ReadableName();
5639  const bool ignore =
5640  StartsWithSingleUnderscore(name) ||
5641  std::any_of(ignored_prefixes.begin(), ignored_prefixes.end(),
5642  [&name](const std::string& prefix) {
5643  return StringStartsWith(name, prefix);
5644  });
5645 
5646  if (!ignore) {
5647  Lint("Macro '", macro->ReadableName(), "' is never used.")
5648  .Position(macro->IdentifierPosition());
5649  }
5650  }
5651 }
